(2141, 422, 'Ryan Hunter', 'retsinis@yahoo.com', '', '171.159.192.10', '2014-09-17 13:59:24', '2014-09-17 20:59:24', 'I know they are small snips, but, you really kind of put the valley down as some sort of after thought back water. I mean bringing up the Porn Industry? really? While that might make sensational headlines, if no one mentioned it, you wouldn''t know it was here at all. Not like they are shooting these scenes on Ventura Blvd. The SFV is hardly just a "suburb of Los Angeles" maybe back in the 60''s it was, but were it not incorporated as part of Los Angeles, and was actually a city unto itself (many that live here, myself included, hope that happens some day) it would be the 5th largest city in the united states. (see links) I''ve read both of your East &amp; West Blog posts about the valley, and it reads like someone who was really surprised we had culture here. Don''t get me wrong, you point out some of our gems in the craft beer scene, but while light brevity, the tone, and introductory chose of words about the valley are sort of condescending, just my opinion and impression. Obviously businesses are investing here, from small start ups, to large chains, in the craft beer scene, so maybe keep that audience in mind, you know, the 1.5 million of us that grew up in the SFV, and have called it home for over 30 years, do spend money, own homes, pay taxes, here, and actually are "regulars" to these great bars your reviewing. \r\n \r\nhttp://www.point2homes.com/US/Neighborhood/CA/Los-Angeles/San-Fernando-Valley-Demographics.html\r\n\r\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_United_States_cities_by_population', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 9.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/5.0)', '', 0, 0),
(2143, 422, 'Mack Magnone', 'mdmagnone@gmail.com', 'http://www.hoppedla.com', '75.85.29.193', '2014-09-17 16:28:37', '2014-09-17 23:28:37', 'Hey, Ryan. Thanks for the comment, and as someone who was born and raised in the Valley, I can certainly see where you''re coming from. The context of the articles are touching solely on the emerging SFV craft beer scene in the last couple years where it hasn''t been before. Believe it or not, many people still identify our home with the porn industry and my mentioning of it simply plays into that stereotype and quickly disbands from it. And yes, there are A LOT of people living here (hence the highly populated note), but the Valley is what it is. There are many ways to define "culture", but most of us that live here actually are surprised at the growing craft beer culture in this area, given the sheer number of destinations that have opened recently or have adopted the craft beer concept. So, rest assured, I''m keeping the Valley kids in mind. Sorry if the intro offended you in any way, but the goal wasn''t to appease ones perspective of the Valley. The goal was simply to bring to the people of LA the wonderful places that they can soak their palates in delicious hop bombs. Cheers, Ryan.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_9_4) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/37.0.2062.120 Safari/537.36', '', 2141, 2),
(2148, 422, 'Nimai', 'nimai.kearney@gmail.com', '', '171.159.64.10', '2014-09-18 10:53:08', '2014-09-18 17:53:08', 'I can see a bit of where Ryan is coming from. I think everyone wants this growth to continue, and for the valley to become a destination (were better off then we were 5 years ago) and maybe, just maybe, also be known for beer. Personally, I think this current up swing in the growing, and emerging craft beer bar growth, as well as the breweries (Macleod, Pac City, San Fernando Brewing, and Hand Brewing) is due to pent up demand, as well as a the current wave across the country in craft  beer in general. (as well as the eat, drink, support local culture as well)  \r\n\r\nFor me, I saw it once there were Bevmo''s from Van Nuys, Northridge, and Canoga Park, followed by a Total Wine in Northridge, and then the slow and growing liquor stores becoming "bottle shops" due to demand. Add in the adding of tap lines and many bars, distribution, and now, especially over the last 3 years, craft beer specific focused spots, and here we are. Great to see these business. I patron many of them, and hope to see them all thrive, and more of them. \r\n\r\nSome spots to add. The Rabbit Hole in West Hills. Another spot is Wades Wines, and their Malibu Sundowner tasting room ( &amp; brewery) It is not really the SFV, but is on the edge of LA County. It''s also just a block down from the LAB &amp; Lady face ale house (all three are on Agoura Road) of lesser note is Wolf Creek (not on my best list, but it is an option, also on Agoura Road) Figeroua Mountain is also currently in construction of a spot on Russel Ranch Road in Westlake Village too, FYI.', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (compatible; MSIE 9.0; Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; Trident/5.0)', '', 0, 0),
(2149, 536, 'Socal Smoove', 'vmeade@hotmail.com', '', '198.134.52.72', '2014-09-18 11:47:21', '2014-09-18 18:47:21', 'The Bagby Beer Company in Oceanside recently opened. \r\n\r\nI have yet to visit myself, but the owner, Jeff Bagby, had an impressive resume while at Port Brewing and the new digs looks dope.\r\n\r\nhttp://www.bagbybeer.com/\r\n\r\nhttp://sandiego.eater.com/archives/2014/09/05/the-beer-is-here-bagby-beer-co-opens-in-oceanside.php', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; WOW64; rv:24.0) Gecko/20100101 Firefox/24.0', '', 0, 0),
(2150, 422, 'Mack Magnone', 'mdmagnone@gmail.com', 'http://www.hoppedla.com', '75.85.29.193', '2014-09-18 11:53:20', '2014-09-18 18:53:20', 'Hey, Nimai. Looks like we''re on the same page. I am LOVING that the Valley is on the rise of becoming more of a destination, and the news keeps pouring in that new spots are being planned to open, such as Public School 818 taking over the space at Sepulveda and Ventura that housed Sisley Italian Kitchen for many years. If I had a bet, I''d say the movement will continue into west into Encino as news about Sweeney''s Ale House rings through the community. Thanks for the additional suggestions. I love Wade''s Wines, but wanted to stay true to the SFV perimeter. Of course, you can catch Gary''s blog post about Wade''s here: http://localhost:8888/wades-wines-westlake. Personally, I haven''t been to The Rabbit Hole. In your opinion, is that a craft beer destination?', 0, '1', 'Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; Intel Mac OS X 10_9_4) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/37.0.2062.120 Safari/537.36', '', 2148, 2),
