(22945, 1930, 'Mack Magnone', 'mdmagnone@gmail.com', 'http://www.hoppedla.com', '75.83.37.124', '2014-09-17 09:15:05', '2014-09-17 16:15:05', 'Great comment, Vince. And I did think about putting the Pub at Golden Road in there, but decided against it (not because it''s not deserving). I really just wanted to stick to beer bars. I did feel that MacLeod''s tasting room ought to be shared based on its relative newness to the Valley.', 0, '1', '', '', 22943, 4),
(22946, 1930, 'Ed K', 'egk@att.net', '', '206.82.244.11', '2014-09-18 15:46:32', '2014-09-18 22:46:32', 'I guess no one goes to Laurel Tavern anymore because its always so crowded!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(22947, 1930, 'Nimai', 'nimai.kearney@gmail.com', '', '171.161.160.10', '2014-10-22 09:34:22', '2014-10-22 16:34:22', 'Another new one , two doors down from The Woodman, called "1 up" (video gaming reference) it''s filled with vintage early 80''s arcade games. Has about 10-12 craft beer taps. Opened about 3 weeks ago.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(22948, 1930, 'David', 'Theresadiaz2941@sbcglobal.net', '', '104.11.68.126', '2015-03-25 21:51:00', '2015-03-26 04:51:00', 'Golden nugget pub in Simi Valley.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(22949, 1930, 'Mack Magnone', 'mdmagnone@gmail.com', 'http://www.hoppedla.com', '23.241.77.194', '2015-03-26 21:51:13', '2015-03-27 04:51:13', 'Nice call, David. I''d say we should do a craft beer guide to Simi Valley, but besides the Golden Nugget, Rusty''s Bar and Grill, and The Dugout, who else is pouring the good stuff out there? I''m all ears! I wanna stop by GN on my way back from Enegren one of these days.', 0, '1', '', '', 22948, 4),
(22950, 1930, 'Your Guide to the Best Beer Bars in Hollywood - Hopped LA', '', 'http://hoppedla.com/your-guide-to-the-best-beer-bars-in-hollywood/', '206.130.117.200', '2015-08-04 17:37:09', '2015-08-05 00:37:09', '[&#8230;] of course, made it to our guide to the best beer bars in the East SFV and for good reason. It&#8217;s a good place to grab a beer. The burgers are fantastic as well, [&#8230;]', 0, '1', '', 'pingback', 0, 0),
(22951, 1930, 'Your Guide to the Best Beer Bars in Long Beach - Hopped LA', '', 'http://hoppedla.com/your-guide-to-the-best-beer-bars-in-long-beach/', '206.130.117.200', '2015-11-29 22:17:16', '2015-11-30 06:17:16', '[&#8230;] is another one that seems obvious, especially since their Burbank location showed up on our SFV East guide. Simmzy&#8217;s has a great spot in the Belmont Shores area of Long Beach, and incorporates a [&#8230;]', 0, '1', '', 'pingback', 0, 0),
(22952, 1930, 'Your Guide to the Best Beer Bars in the SFV (West) - Hopped LA', '', 'http://hoppedla.com/best-beer-bars-in-the-sfv-west/', '206.130.117.200', '2015-12-25 02:25:46', '2015-12-25 10:25:46', '[&#8230;] have a guide to the East SFV, but this edition of Hopped LA&#8217;s guide to the best beer bars takes you on a journey of the [&#8230;]', 0, '1', '', 'pingback', 0, 0),
(22953, 1933, 'Your Guide to the Best Beer Bars in the San Fernando Valley (East) - Hopped LA', '', 'http://hoppedla.com/best-beer-bars-san-fernando-valley-east/', '206.130.117.200', '2015-03-23 22:52:58', '2015-03-24 05:52:58', '[&#8230;] Public School 818 opened in early March and so far the buzz has been good. The kicked off their opening with a tap list that could satisfy the hop heads, but I wouldn&#8217;t count on it being a go-to spot if you&#8217;re looking for IPAs. They do have a great house IPA brewed by Fig Mountain called School House IPA that is worth a try. [&#8230;]', 0, '1', '', 'pingback', 0, 0),
(22954, 1269, 'Lloyd Brown', '1CraftBeerGuy@gmail.com', 'http://craftbeerguy.com/', '23.240.19.131', '2015-04-24 10:23:04', '2015-04-24 17:23:04', 'Thank you for the mention.', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
(22955, 1935, 'Your Guide to the Best LA Beer Week Events in 2015 - Hopped LA', '', 'http://hoppedla.com/la-beer-week-2015/', '206.130.117.200', '2015-06-15 23:04:16', '2015-06-16 06:04:16', '[&#8230;] going to be awesome and you&#8217;re gonna want to put this on your calendar. You may have heard we recently teamed up with Karl Strauss to brew a special LABW collab beer, Hoppywood &amp; Bine. Well on Friday, June 19th we officially release the beer to the public. The Karl Strauss team is [&#8230;]', 0, '1', '', 'pingback', 0, 0),
(22956, 1935, 'KARL Invades LA Beer Week with an Exclusive Collab &amp; a Slew of Special Releases | Karl Strauss Brewing Company Blog Karl Strauss Brewing Company Blog', '', 'http://www.karlstrauss.com/blog/karl-invades-la-beer-week-with-an-exclusive-collab-a-slew-of-special-releases/', '208.113.234.55', '2015-06-17 12:54:20', '2015-06-17 19:54:20', '[&#8230;] Teaming up with the guys from HoppedLA we created &#8220;Hoppywood and Bine&#8221; India Pale Lager. We wanted to deliver something that  really fit the LA personality. A beer with a light body, high drinkability, and a platform for showcasing a strong West Coast hop profile. Brewed with Chinook, Citra, and Mosaic hops plus a healthy dry-hop with even more Mosaic, the final product packs a ton of hoppy bitterness . You can read all about the awesome collaboration experience at HoppedLA.com and come out to join us for it&#8217;s debut at our LABW Preview and Release Event at City Tavern in Culver City on 6/19. Check out the full list of where we&#8217;ll be pouring &#8220;Hoppywood and Bine&#8221; as well as all our other LABW events below. [&#8230;]', 0, '1', '', 'pingback', 0, 0),
(22957, 1486, 'Jim', 'Jamnjg@yahoo.com', '', '24.251.193.90', '2015-09-02 07:57:43', '2015-09-02 14:57:43', 'Way to go cuz!', 0, '1', '', '', 0, 0),
