(289, 2, '2014-06-20 11:33:43', '2014-06-20 18:33:43', 'The melting pot that is Downtown Los Angeles seems to be taking quite the turn for the better. Pershing Square looks green and immaculate, there''s a ton of new construction going on, and it''s a got a shit-load of great places for craft beer. Excuse my French.\r\n\r\nIf you''re looking for a perfect place for a craft beer bar crawl, then these bars are it as they are all in walking distance of each other. And you know what? I''ll even give you the proper order in which to do them. Here''s your walking guide to the best beer bars in Downtown LA:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/citytavern.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-309 size-full" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/citytavern.png" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="460" height="491" /></a>\r\n<h2><strong><a href="http://www.citytaverndtla.com/" target="_blank">1. City Tavern</a></strong></h2>\r\n<em>735 S. Figueroa St. #133 Los Angeles, Ca 90017</em>\r\n\r\nCity Tavern is the hidden gem once you descend into Fig at 7th''s circular abyss. Of course, if you''ve been to City Tavern before, you know that they are serious about craft beer. Grab a pint or milk jug (two pints) of Haven''s Double Hubble while it''s still there, and some food if you''d like. The pastrami burger is amazing, but if you''re willing to wait until the end of the bar crawl...you will be rewarded.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-310 size-full" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la.png" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="800" height="531" /></a>\r\n<h2><strong><a href="http://www.publicschool612.com/" target="_blank">2. Public School 612</a> </strong></h2>\r\n<i>612 S. Flower St. Los Angeles, Ca 90017</i>\r\n\r\nOne of three Public School locations, 612 takes up a favorable corner with it''s diner-like exterior. But don''t let that fool you, there are some hoppy brews on tap in here. If you haven''t wrecked your palate already, order a Sculpin and hit up the happy hour menu if you made it in time. $4 fare like tacos, truffle fries, and street dogs ought to hit the spot. But like I said before - if you can hold off, then hold off.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la1.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-312" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la1.png" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="550" height="485" /></a>\r\n<h2><a href="http://sixthstreettavern.com/" target="_blank"><strong>3. Sixth Street Tavern</strong></a></h2>\r\n<em>630 W. 6th St. Los Angeles, Ca 90017</em>\r\n\r\nWhen I came here, they had Alpine''s Hoppy Birthday on tap, sooo yeah, I was into this place. Not only do they make tasty cocktails, but the beer list is expansive with options from breweries like Angel City, Craftsman, Alpine, and Deschutes. If you must eat now, just snack on the Rockenwagner pretzel. That should hold you over. Afterwards, you can pop into Library Bar next door, but chances are you won''t find the beer you''re looking for. Off to the next one.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la2.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-314 size-full" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la2.png" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="646" height="370" /></a>\r\n<h2><a href="http://springstla.com/" target="_blank"><strong>4. Spring Street Bar</strong></a></h2>\r\n<em>626-B S. Spring St. Los Angeles, Ca 90014</em>\r\n\r\nSpring Street Bar is also categorized as a deli, and that''s because they''ve got killer sandwiches. They also have 26 taps of frothy, delicious beer. Start with El Segundo''s Citra and end it with Deschutes Fresh Squeezed IPA, and it''s on to the next one.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la3.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-318 size-full" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la3.png" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="768" height="815" /></a>\r\n<h2><strong><a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz/the-black-sheep-los-angeles" target="_blank">5. The Black Sheep</a></strong></h2>\r\n<em>126 E 6th St. Los Angeles, Ca 90013</em>\r\n\r\nThe beer list is short here, but there''s bound to one that you can finish your night off on. Depending on how busy it is, it might be tough to get a table. Also, it can get crowded because you have to order at the counter. So, what''s the big draw? The burgers and sausages. Thick, juicy, and packed full of flavor, this could be the place you can finally grab a bite to eat. But let''s say you didn''t find a good, hoppy beer on the menu and you''ve waited to eat?\r\n\r\nThen, walk out that door and make a direct left into the historic Cole''s, where your reward awaits. At this point, you can stick to the beer list or slip into a warm Old Fashioned - a Cole''s staple. Not only are they known for the Old Fashioned, but their Original French Dip is AMAZING and that''s what you''re going to order.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la1.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-316" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la1.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="600" height="600" /></a>\r\n\r\nOf course, if you want to start off with cocktails, then just flip this beer crawl in reverse and work backwards. You''ll feel equally as good at the end of night, although you''ll probably be craving another French Dip. I know I did.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la2.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-320 size-full" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la2.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="475" height="356" /></a>\r\n<h2><strong>Honorable Mention: <a href="http://buzzwinebeershop.com/" target="_blank">BUZZ wine beer shop</a></strong></h2>\r\n<em>460 S. Spring St. Ste. C Los Angeles, Ca 90013</em>\r\n\r\nThis one gets the honorable mention because it''s not a bar. It''s a specialty wine and bottle shop that HAS a tasting bar in the back. They hold numerous wine and beer tastings throughout the week, so it''s a great place to talk shop and sip the good stuff. Then, you can take a few bottles home to cap off the night.\r\n\r\nHave you been to any of these places mentioned above? Did I miss a good beer spot along the way here? Whatever the case, join the convo in the comments below or on Twitter at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. Thanks for reading.', 'Your Guide to the Best Beer Bars in Downtown LA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la', '', '', '2014-09-14 19:42:23', '2014-09-15 02:42:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=289', 0, 'post', '', 1),
