(422, 2, '2014-07-24 14:51:32', '2014-07-24 21:51:32', 'The San Fernando Valley - a highly populated suburb of Los Angeles whose stark claim to fame was being referred to as the "porn capital of the world". While that title is now debatable due to LA''s growing regulations on the industry, a new movement is coming to light. I am, of course, talking about the LA craft beer movement. As months go by, we''re starting to see a growing interest in saturating this once barren area into beer bar destination.\r\n\r\nThis edition of Hopped LA''s guide to the best beer bars takes you on a journey of the best beer bars in the SFV west of the 405. Get your notepads out, people. You''re going to want to write this down.\r\n\r\n<strong><a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/pedlars-fork-beer-bars-in-the-sfv.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-424 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/pedlars-fork-beer-bars-in-the-sfv-300x200.jpg" alt="pedlars-fork-beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="300" height="200" /></a></strong>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.pedalersfork.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Pedalers Fork</strong></a> <em>(Calabasas) </em>\r\n\r\nAlong the Arroyo Calabasas tributary sits Pedalers Fork, a restaurant/coffee shop/bike shop that suffers from the best kind of identity crisis. Oh, and they have 30+ taps of all craft beer, with a good amount dedicated to the hops we love.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/the-local-peasant-beer-bars-in-the-sfv.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-427 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/the-local-peasant-beer-bars-in-the-sfv-300x300.jpg" alt="the-local-peasant-beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="300" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.thelocalpeasant.com/" target="_blank"><strong>The Local Peasant</strong></a> <i>(Woodland Hills)</i>\r\n\r\nThe spacious, West Valley counterpart boasts a HUGE, open interior with communal-style tables for groups, or booths for a more intimate experience. The taps go almost all the way around the center bar here, presenting a high probability that you''ll find a hoppy brew you''ll like. The last time I visited, it was an order of Alpine''s Hoppy Birthday and a seat out on the expansive patio that did the trick.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Screen-Shot-2014-07-24-at-1.16.20-PM.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-443 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Screen-Shot-2014-07-24-at-1.16.20-PM-298x300.png" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="298" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://hookburger.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Hook Burger</strong></a> <em>(Woodland Hills)</em>\r\n\r\nAt first I was hesitant to include Hook Burger on the list. That was until I remembered that they are one of the very few places that have been graced with distribution by Agoura''s <a href="http://www.ladyfaceale.com/" target="_blank">Ladyface Ale Companie</a> - and that Ladyface IPA is pretty good. Go here mainly for the delish burgers, but rest easy knowing you can grab a Ladyface or Eagle Rock brew.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-429 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv-300x300.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="300" height="300" /></a><a href="http://theirbar.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Instant Replay</strong></a> <em>(Canoga Park)</em>\r\n\r\nYou probably wouldn''t have heard of IR Bar without me telling you, but if you have - kudos. This unassuming dive bar looks like it''s been around for awhile, but that doesn''t mean the beer is old. They''re rotating nine taps of all different sorts, but the IPAs are not ignored.\r\n\r\nCurrently, you''ll be happy to find Stone''s Unapologetic and Noble''s Big Whig filling up glasses.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv1.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-433 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv1-300x225.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="300" height="225" /></a><a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz/taps-valley-gastropub-northridge" target="_blank"><strong>Taps Valley Gastropub</strong></a> <em>(Northridge)</em>\r\n\r\nYou all remember Hot''s Tacos, right? Oh, you don''t? That''s no surprise, as that place came and went without a worry, and was subsequently replaced by Taps Valley Gastropub. The location next to an LA Fitness makes you have that internal struggle between exercise or beer drinking, but we know the latter always wins.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv2.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-439 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv2-300x225.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="300" height="225" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.yardhouse.com/ca/northridge-restaurant/" target="_blank"><strong>Yard House</strong></a> <em>(Northridge)</em>\r\n\r\nIf you''ve been to a Yard House location before, then you know what it''s all about: a bunch of beer taps, some alright food, and yard sticks. Just make sure you have a designated driver before you decide to chug that yard full of Dogfish Head 90-Minute.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv3.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-441 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv3-300x225.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="300" height="225" /></a><a href="http://www.crazyharrysbar.com" target="_blank"><strong>Crazy Harry''s Bar</strong></a> <em>(Winnetka)</em>\r\n\r\nA few years ago, this Mid-Valley beer bar opened up during a time when the inhabitants of Winnetka weren''t necessarily itching for craft beer. Holding their ground and waiting out the storm, Crazy Harry''s Bar has developed a great following due to their 80/80 beer club, <a title="Deschutes Brewery Takes Over Crazy Harry’s Bar" href="http://localhost:8888/deschutes-brewery-crazy-harrys-bar/" target="_blank">their constant tap takeovers</a>, and bar manager Jay''s affinity for developing good relationships with his distributors.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv4.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-442 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv4-295x300.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="295" height="300" /></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/BigMamasPapasPizzeriaTarzana" target="_blank"><strong>BMPP Tavern &amp; Lounge</strong></a> <em>(Tarzana)</em>\r\n\r\nWhat the heck is BMPP, you ask? Likely, you''ve heard of the pizza parlor franchise Big Mama''s and Papa''s, only this time they are cashing in on the craft beer. Along Ventura Blvd. in Tarzana, this spot opened up to cater to the West SFV and they are delivering good beer. Albeit, you won''t find the whales here, you can hopefully settle for one of the solid IPAs they have on tap.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv5.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-446 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv5-300x225.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="300" height="225" /></a><a href="http://www.wholefoodsmarket.com/stores/tarzana" target="_blank"><strong>Vine 39 inside Whole Foods Market</strong></a> <em>(Tarzana)</em>\r\n\r\nAfter the <a title="Meet Vine 39, Tarzana’s Newest Craft Beer &amp; Wine Bar" href="http://localhost:8888/vine39-whole-foods-tarzana/" target="_blank">grand re-opening of Whole Foods'' specialty beer and wine bar, Vine 39</a>, the people of Tarzana were blessed with great wine, new menu items, and several taps of craft beer. I''ll even give a nod to their great selection of bottled beer, as <a href="http://instagram.com/p/qzhtn9CJ0V" target="_blank">I picked up some of Bear Republic''s Cafe Racer 15 the other day</a>. Drop by for a pint or two on draft, or grab your favorite bottle and have them open it up for you, you''re bound to have a good time either way.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Screen-Shot-2014-07-24-at-1.38.53-PM.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-447 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Screen-Shot-2014-07-24-at-1.38.53-PM-298x300.png" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="298" height="300" /></a><a href="http://prohibitionburgers.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Prohibition Burgers &amp; Beer</strong></a> <em>(Encino)</em>\r\n\r\nI want to like Prohibition very badly, but I usually leave there unsatisfied either by their burgers, but mostly by the hoppy beer selection (or lack thereof). They make the list simply because of what they offer, but more often not, the tap list will leave a lot to be desired. Granted they''ll have some good IPAs in 22oz. bottles, but forking up more money than you want to for a solid IPA or IIPA may not be part of your plan.\r\n\r\nKeep in mind my bias towards tap lists that are IPA heavy.\r\n\r\n<strong> <a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-449 size-medium" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv-300x300.png" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="300" height="300" /></a>Honorable Mention: <a href="http://www.greenjug.com/" target="_blank">Green Jug Fine Wines and Spirits</a></strong> <em>(Woodland Hills)</em>\r\n\r\nThis is not a beer bar (although they do have a bar inside for <a href="http://www.greenjug.com/shopcontent.asp?type=calendar" target="_blank">their scheduled tastings</a>), but this is hands down the BEST bottle shop in the west part of the San Fernando Valley. One of the few spots that gets regular shipments of Pliny the Elder and other hard-to-get beers, Green Jug is owned by welcoming and very knowledgable people that are sure to connect you to the tasty brews you love.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWell, that does it for the West San Fernando Valley, but don''t worry, we''ll be coming back with the must-stop spots on the OTHER side of the 405 Freeway to complete our guide to the best beer bars in the SFV.\r\n\r\nDid I miss a cool beer bar that you think should be on our list? Let me know in the comments or on Twitter at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. Cheers!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Your Guide to the Best Beer Bars in the SFV (West)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-beer-bars-in-the-sfv-west', '', 'http://localhost:8888/deschutes-brewery-crazy-harrys-bar/\nhttp://localhost:8888/vine39-whole-foods-tarzana/', '2014-09-15 15:27:53', '2014-09-15 22:27:53', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=422', 0, 'post', '', 8),
