(626, 2, '2014-09-12 10:04:08', '2014-09-12 17:04:08', 'Welcome back, hop heads.\r\n\r\nWhen I brought you the <a href="http://localhost:8888/best-beer-bars-in-the-sfv-west/" target="_blank">best beer bars of the West SFV</a> a few weeks ago, I was actually quite impressed at the number of craft beer destinations that were populating my list. However, I knew that it was only the beginning, because before craft beer won the west - it conquered the east.\r\n\r\nThe East SFV is a growing mecca for craft beer in the Valley given that the first craft breweries and tasting rooms have opened up and Sherman Oaks has a new stretch of spots along Ventura Blvd., dubbed "restaurant row". So, without further adieu, let''s see where you can dive head first into hops east of the dreaded 405.\r\n<h3>The Best Beer Bars in the San Fernando Valley (East)</h3>\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east9.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-635 size-medium" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east9-300x199.png" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east9" width="300" height="199" /></a><a href="http://www.macleodale.com/" target="_blank"><strong>MacLeod Ale Brewing Co.</strong></a> <em>(Van Nuys)</em>\r\n\r\nMacLeod Ale is one of the <a href="http://localhost:8888/first-breweries-sfv/" target="_blank">first micro-breweries to open in the Valley</a> after Pac City, but pulls off their launch much cleaner. Specializing in cask-conditioned British ales, they make the Hopped LA list due to their expansive tasting room featuring games, darts, homemade crackers made from spent grain, and bring-your-own cheese nights; and of course, their ability to brew their ales right here at home.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east1.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-627 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east1-300x225.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east1" width="300" height="225" /></a><a href="http://www.bluedogbeertavern.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Blue Dog Beer Tavern</strong></a> <em>(Sherman Oaks)</em>\r\n\r\nBlue Dog and I have some history, and while their weekly tap list could use tweaking here and there, I have no bad things to say about their Chi Chi Burger. But this is a beer blog, so enough about that. Blue Dog was one of the first to bring craft beer to this little pocket and remains a very popular hang out, especially if your pup is tagging along. Hop heads can be satisfied by Green Flash West Coast IPA on tap and some different bottle selections. But that Chi Chi Burger though...\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east2.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-628 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east2-300x199.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east2" width="300" height="199" /></a><a href="http://www.onthethirty.com/" target="_blank"><strong>On The Thirty</strong></a> <em>(Sherman Oaks)</em>\r\n\r\nLocated along Sherman Oaks'' restaurant row, On The Thirty brings a more casual vibe to the neighborhood and thirty types of craft beer to your palate. The food specialty here is pizza, but check their menu for more tasty items like the Lobster Roll. Pair them with The Dudes Double Trunk or El Segundo''s White Dog IPA while you catch the NFL Sunday Ticket this season. I''ll be guy in the corner pissed off at his fantasy team.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east14.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-640 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east14-300x159.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east14" width="300" height="159" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://tippleandbrine.com/" target="_blank"><b>Tipple &amp; Brine</b></a> <em>(Sherman Oaks)</em>\r\n\r\nAnother spot along restaurant row, Tipple and Brine focuses on quality, local fare and that mission translates to the beers. You won''t find a huge tap list here, but you''ll be able to order something decent to go with your oysters. For an after-dinner libation, head out back and upstairs to Tunnel Bar Cocktail Lounge which sits on top of T&amp;B.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east13.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-641 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east13-300x208.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east13" width="300" height="208" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.theoakstavern.com/The_Oaks_Tavern/Home.html" target="_blank"><strong>The Oaks Tavern</strong></a> <em>(Sherman Oaks)</em>\r\n\r\nDuring my time residing in Sherman Oaks, this space underwent a few different changes, finally landing onto a craft beer concept that makes me resent leaving that area before it opened. The Oaks is super casual, featuring darts, pool, positive social interactions, and a wall full o'' taps. Tuesdays and Thursdays are karaoke nights, so grab a pint of Belching Beaver''s Beavers Milk and belt out your best rendition of "Don''t Stop Believin''".\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east15.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-667 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east15-300x211.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east15" width="300" height="211" /></a><a href="http://tipsycowla.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Tipsy Cow</strong></a> <em>(Sherman Oaks)</em>\r\n\r\nAnother new spot along restaurant row, Tipsy Cow is all about burgers, beer, and milkshakes. In fact, the decor almost reminds me of an upscale diner. They are tapping into the local brew scene, as well as the surrounding VTA and SD counties, so the usual suspects can be found behind the bar. Additionally, those milkshakes can be made boozy, so if you''re not feelin'' like beer, you have options. Did I mention the burgers are grand?\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east3.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-629 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east3-300x149.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east3" width="300" height="149" /></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/thewoodmanla" target="_blank"><strong>The Woodman</strong></a> <em>(Sherman Oaks)</em>\r\n\r\nThe Woodman is another new gastropub along "The Row", and comes from the owners of The Surly Goat in West Hollywood. This place is so new that it doesn''t even have a website yet. If you''ve been to The Surly Goat, then you know that they pour some serious beer. The same goes for The Woodman with it''s upscale fare like rabbit empanadas and Thai coconut curry mussels.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east5.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-631 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east5-300x182.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east5" width="300" height="182" /></a><a href="http://thelocalpeasants.com/" target="_blank"><strong>The Local Peasant</strong></a> <em>(Sherman Oaks)</em>\r\n\r\nThe Sherman Oaks counterpart is, of course, the original and still holds that same exclusive charm it did when it first opened. Providing a more intimate setting than it''s west Valley location, you''ll still find your favorite food items and a list of beers that''ll suit your tastes. Currently, you can sip on Lagunitas Little Sumpin'' Extra DIPA and Deschutes Fresh Squeezed IPA to name a couple.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east8.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-634 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east8-300x166.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east8" width="300" height="166" /></a><a href="http://www.boneyardbistro.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Boneyard Bistro</strong></a> <em>(Sherman Oaks)</em>\r\n\r\nAnother popular Sherman Oaks spot, Boneyard can get pretty crowded - and for good reason. They have great (but expensive) food, a full bar with experienced bartenders, and an impressive haul of craft beer. If you dare see Pliny the Elder on tap in this neck of the woods, it will more than likely be here. Currently, they''re pouring Noble Ale Works'' Chinook Showers from their limited release Showers series and Eel River''s Emerald Triangle.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east6.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-632 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east6-300x200.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east6" width="300" height="200" /></a><strong><a href="http://tuningforkgastropub.com/" target="_blank">Tuning Fork</a></strong> <em>(Studio City)</em>\r\n\r\nTuning Fork is a nice gem in Studio City that opened up a few years ago. It gained a following fairly quickly and it''s now serving the likes of celebs and locals alike. Their beer selection is pretty big, but it''s mostly in bottles and cans. Not a bad thing, however, as that selection alone presents many Golden Road, Pizza Port, and Lagunitas options. So, order an All or Nothing Burger and a Wolf Among Weeds, and we''ll stick a fork in ya.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east7.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-633 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east7-300x225.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east7" width="300" height="225" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.stoutburgersandbeers.com/" target="_blank">Stout Burgers and Beer</a></strong> <em>(Studio City)</em>\r\n\r\nStout makes our list as they offer a fairly comfortable selection of craft beer on tap, making it possible for you to find something you like. Whether it be as solid as a Stone IPA or the off-chance that Avery''s Maharaja is on that night, you''ll hopefully end the night with a stomach full of burgers and beer. And what could honestly be better than that? Well, sex, of course.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east10.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-649 size-medium" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east10-300x225.png" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east10" width="300" height="225" /></a><a href="http://tonysda.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Tony''s Darts Away</strong></a> <em>(Burbank)</em>\r\n\r\nTony''s is a no-brainer if you are a fan of LA craft beer, and it''s my pleasure if I''m introducing this spot to you for the first time. Before it became the TDA that you see today, it used to be a dive bar of the same name. LA beer dude, Tony Yanow, took over the space, kept the name (coincidentally the same as his), and gave craft beer a new life in Los Angeles. Specializing in California brews and plump, signature sausages, Tony''s Darts Away is your friendly, neighborhood hangout where friends meet friends and strangers become friends. Make it a point to stop by on their yearly anniversary parties where Golden Road brews up a special to-die-for "Darts Away IPA".\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east11.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-650 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east11-300x199.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east11" width="300" height="199" /></a><a href="http://www.storytavernburbank.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Story Tavern</strong></a> <em>(Burbank)</em>\r\n\r\nThis craftsman-style pub sits on San Fernando Blvd. just a stone''s throw away from downtown Burbank. It''s also just down the road from a Gordon Biersch Brewery Restaurant (but who cares about that). Story Tavern presents itself like an ordinary pub that boasts such fare as Shepard''s Pie, and a handful of beer engines that pump from nearby casks. Don''t worry, though, as the craft beer taps have a few different locations behind the bar giving you over 20 options to choose from. Make this a stop when you head out this way to visit Tony''s Darts Away.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east16.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-682 size-medium" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east16-300x199.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east16" width="300" height="199" /></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/glendaletap" target="_blank"><strong>Glendale Tap</strong></a> <em>(Glendale)</em>\r\n\r\nGlendale Tap opened a couple years ago to an area of LA that wasn''t ripe with craft beer bars, aside from the Pub at Golden Rub and Links &amp; Hops. Still going strong today, Glendale Tap is armed with 52 taps and pouring your favorites from Ballast Point, El Segundo Brewing Co., Deschutes, and more.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east12.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-651 size-medium" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east12-300x200.png" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east12" width="300" height="200" /></a><strong>Honorable Mention: <a href="http://localhost:8888/valley-beverage-co/" target="_blank">Valley Beverage Co.</a></strong>\r\n\r\nYup, it''s another bottle shop. But it''s not just any other bottle shop - it''s the giant of the east SFV where Green Jug is that of the west. Any trip to Valley Beverage Co. will ensure you don''t leave empty handed as their beer selection is fantastic. They are also one of the few places in town to grab bottles of the hard-to-find whales that grace the shelves in the back (meaning you need to ask for them). The downside is that EVERYBODY knows when the shipments come in, which means if you don''t get here fast then that beer you wanted...is already gone. Don''t worry, wait a few days until Vendome of Toluca Lake gets the same beer in and you''ll probably get your hands on it. <a href="http://localhost:8888/vendome-liquors-toluca-lake/" target="_blank">Get our take on Vendome in our "#InsideTheBottleShop" series.</a>\r\n\r\nIt seems I''ve already done some good today for all of my Valley kids out there. I''ve laid out the road map for you, and now leave you to find the hoppy treasures that await. So, go forth and prosper, my friends. In other words, GET HOPPED.\r\n\r\nDid I miss a good spot? I''m definitely not above correction. Alternatively, did I introduce you to a new place you can''t wait to check out? Whatever the case, let me know in the comments or tweet me at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a> or <a href="http://www.twitter.com/mackdmag" target="_blank">@mackdmag</a>. Thanks for reading!', 'Your Guide to the Best Beer Bars in the San Fernando Valley (East)', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-beer-bars-san-fernando-valley-east', '', 'http://localhost:8888/first-breweries-sfv/\nhttp://localhost:8888/valley-beverage-co/\nhttp://localhost:8888/vendome-liquors-toluca-lake/', '2014-09-17 09:01:41', '2014-09-17 16:01:41', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=626', 0, 'post', '', 9),
