(767, 2, '2014-12-04 09:35:47', '2014-12-04 17:35:47', '<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/la-ipa-fest-2014.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-778" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/la-ipa-fest-2014.jpg" alt="la-ipa-fest-2014" width="1920" height="740" /></a>We''re all well aware that the LA IPA Fest 2014 is coming up this weekend and we''re all REAL excited, right? Of course we are here at Hopped LA because hoppy ass brews are what we''re all about. As it turns out, so are you. And if you''re one of those people that looked at the recently unveiled tap list and wondered how to navigate, you''re not alone. Here''s the LA IPA Fest 2014 Tap List with notes on the beers that you must have.\r\n<h1>LA IPA Fest 2014 Tap List</h1>\r\n<strong>21st Amendment</strong> – Brew Free or Die IPA\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>Bagby Beer Co </strong>– Dork Squad</span></h3>\r\n<em>We''re calling out this Oceanside, CA IPA for the dank aroma and piney flavor. If your palate is on point, you may even taste a little grapefruit.</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Brewery at Abigaile</strong> – TBA\r\n\r\n<strong>Alesmith</strong> – Alesmith IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Alpine</strong> – Nelson\r\n\r\n<strong>Anderson Valley</strong> – Hop Ottin’\r\n\r\n<strong>Anchor</strong> – Zymaster #7 Potrero Hill Sour Mash IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Ballast Point</strong> – Sculpin\r\n\r\n<strong>Beach City Brewery</strong> – Kickout IPA\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>Beachwood BBQ &amp; Brewing </strong>– Resinator IPA</span></h3>\r\n<i>I love what Beachwood does with IPAs and this one is no different. They are packing in Chinook, Warrior, Simcoe, Amarillo, and a secret experimental variety of hops into this West Coast style leaving it with plenty of resin-y aromatics and 99+ IBUs. </i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Bear Republic</strong> – Racer 5\r\n\r\n<strong>Bottle Logic</strong> – Recursion\r\n\r\n<strong>Bravery Brewing + Transplants Brewing</strong> – Plant Trance IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Cellarmaker</strong> – Hop Killah\r\n\r\n<strong>Cismontane</strong> – Hop Dumpster\r\n\r\n<strong>Coronado Brewing</strong> – Islander\r\n\r\n<strong>Drake’s Brewing</strong> – 7X70\r\n\r\n<strong>Eagle Rock Brewery</strong> – Populist\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>El Segundo Brewing Co. </strong>– Mayberry IPA</span></h3>\r\n<em>El Segundo''s Mayberry IPA delivers on color, aroma, and taste. This beer<em> is nice on the eyes w</em>ith its bronze-orange color, and your first inhale of a floral bouquet aroma will give you evidence of juicy, tropical notes. Once you taste, the evidence becomes conclusive. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Faction Brewing</strong> – Fall IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Firestone Walker</strong> – Union Jack\r\n\r\n<strong>Golden Road Brewing</strong> – Wolf Among Weeds\r\n\r\n<strong>Green Flash</strong> – Soul Style\r\n\r\n<strong>Hangar 24</strong> – Betty IPA\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>Highland Park Brewery </strong>– Neon IPA</span></h3>\r\n<em>Full disclosure: I haven''t had Neon IPA yet, BUT Highland Park Brewery really nailed it with their 1Up IPA. That alone will make me want to try this one and see if this brewery is on the right track. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Institution Ales</strong> – Institution IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Ironfire</strong> – 51/50\r\n\r\n<strong>Iron Springs</strong> – JC Flyer\r\n\r\n<strong>Island Brewing</strong> – Island IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Karl Strauss</strong> – Tower 10\r\n\r\n<strong>Kern River Brewing</strong> – Just Outstanding\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>Kinetic Brewing </strong>– Hops Angeles</span></h3>\r\n<em>Their attempt at the ubiquitous West Coast Style in their Propulsion IPA left me wanting more, and Hops Angeles might be the answer. This up-and-coming brewery is one to look out for.</em>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_781" align="alignnone" width="600"]<a href="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/la-ipa-fest-20141.jpg"><img class="wp-image-781 size-full" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/la-ipa-fest-20141.jpg" alt="la-ipa-fest-2014" width="600" height="600" /></a> And now a picture of a delicious looking IPA.[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>King Harbor</strong> – El Azaccorado\r\n\r\n<strong>Ladyface Ale Companie</strong> – Ladyface IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Lagunitas</strong> – Lagunitas Sucks\r\n\r\n<strong>Lost Abbey</strong> – Merry Taj\r\n\r\n<strong>Magnolia Brewery</strong> – Proving Ground\r\n\r\n<strong>Modern Times</strong> – Blazing World\r\n\r\n<strong>Monkey Paw</strong> – Lab Monkey\r\n\r\n<strong>Mother Earth</strong> – BooKoo\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>Noble Ale Works </strong>– I Love It!</span></h3>\r\n<em>This is another one I''ll be trying on Saturday, because Noble is the reigning champ from last year''s LA IPA Fest , and they almost always hit it out of the park whenever they brew a special IPA. And with a name like "I Love It!"...how can you not? </em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Ohana Brewing</strong> – Hashtag Hops\r\n\r\n<strong>Pizza Port Bressi Ranch</strong> – Barney\r\n\r\n<strong>Pizza Port Carlsbad</strong> — Raceway IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Pizza Port Ocean Beach</strong> — The Burning of Rome\r\n\r\n<strong>Pizza Port San Clemente</strong> — El Camino IPA\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>Pizza Port Solana Beach </strong>– Citra-R-Ama</span></h3>\r\n<em>Wait a minute, did I just hear "Citra"? You betcha. Five Pizza Port locations are bringing up the goods, but Solana Beach knows how to bring Hopped LA to its knees. This citra-focused IPA pours a nice golden color and packs an aroma that screams...you guessed it: citrus. Don''t expect to get hit with much malt or sweetness. This baby finishes dry. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Port Brewing</strong> – Wipeout\r\n\r\n<strong>Russian River Brewing</strong> – Pliny the Elder\r\n\r\n<strong>Santa Clara Valley</strong> – Electric Tower\r\n\r\n<strong>Smog City Brewing</strong> – Hop Tonic\r\n\r\n<strong>Societe Brewing</strong> – The Pupil\r\n\r\n<strong>Speakeasy</strong> – Big Daddy\r\n\r\n<strong>St. Archer</strong> – St. Archer IPA\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>Stone Brewing </strong>– Lupulin Loop</span></h3>\r\n<em>This single-hop IPA series is making a welcomed appearance at this year''s IPA Fest and for good reason. They''re pretty damn good. I''m a big fan of the single-hopped style and am looking forward to seeing which varietal they chose for this festival. </em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Tap It</strong> – Tap It IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Telegraph</strong> – Telegraph IPA\r\n<h3><span style="color: #ec432e;"><strong>Three Weav3rs </strong>– Expatriate IPA</span></h3>\r\n<i>I have to give the shout out to Three Weav3rs, because we''re big fans of the direction the brewery is heading. Their Stateside Session IPA is phenomenal, and the Expatriate is up there too. If you haven''t been exposed to this brewery yet, now is the time. </i>\r\n\r\n<strong>Tustin Brewing</strong> – Old Town\r\n\r\n<strong>Wicks Brewing</strong> – Battle Cry IPA\r\n\r\n<strong>Wolf Creek Brewery</strong> – Lone Wolf\r\n\r\n<strong>Sierra Nevada</strong> – Neomexicanus\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>LA IPA Fest 2014 Event Details</h2>\r\n<strong>Where:</strong> Mohawk Bend - 2141 Sunset Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90026\r\n\r\n<strong>When:</strong> Saturday, December 6, 2014. Doors open at 9:30am\r\n\r\nFor more information on the event, visit the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1519429408313252/" target="_blank">Los Angeles IPA Festival event page</a> on Facebook.\r\n\r\nHead on over to <a href="http://thefullpint.com/events/los-angeles-ipa-fest-returns-dec-6-taplist-judges-revealed/" target="_blank">The Full Pint</a> to see the official judges list and how the competition works.\r\n\r\nLet us know you''ll be there by tweeting at us <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. Of course, we''ll be using the official hashtag: #LAIPAfest2014.', 'LA IPA Fest 2014 Tap List - What You Need To Know', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'la-ipa-fest-2014-tap-list', '', '\nhttp://thefullpint.com/events/los-angeles-ipa-fest-returns-dec-6-taplist-judges-revealed/', '2014-12-04 10:26:57', '2014-12-04 18:26:57', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=767', 0, 'post', '', 0),
