(831, 1, '2014-12-23 19:27:38', '2014-12-24 03:27:38', 'Still figuring out your New Year''s Eve plans? Hopped LA has you covered so you can ring in the New Year with a glass of something cold, hoppy, and delicious when the clock strikes midnight. Here are the top 2014 NYE events in LA to get your craft beer on.\r\n<h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1567543673482333/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-832 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/goldenroadnye-e1419390690836.png" alt="Golden Road Brewing New Year''s Eve 2014" width="698" height="438" /></a>\r\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1567543673482333/" target="_blank"><strong>Golden Road Brewing - Burbank / Glendale</strong></a></h3>\r\nThe crew at Golden Road is throwing a special reservation-only 3-course dinner which includes a special pour of barrel-aged beer and a midnight beer toast for $40. If you''re the type of risk taker who doesn''t wanna make reservations on New Year''s Eve, then you can also show up to the brewery and enjoy your favorite GRB brews on tap and order food off their regular pub menu on a first come, first serve basis. PLUS, live music from Pretty Dirty &amp; Funky will be filling the airwaves. If you''re a vegan, dancer, an IPA drinker (of course you are), or just a lover of fun, then this party is right up your alley.\r\n\r\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1567543673482333/" target="_blank"><em>https://www.facebook.com/events/1567543673482333/</em></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1567543673482333/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-833 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/tonysdartsawaynye-e1419390738343.png" alt="Tony''s Darts Away New Year''s Eve 2014" width="698" height="698" /></a>\r\n<strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1567543673482333/" target="_blank">Tony''s Darts Away - Burbank</a></strong></h3>\r\nMr. Yanow''s plan to rule NYE continues with <a href="https://twitter.com/search?f=realtime&amp;q=%23newyearsattonys&amp;src=typd" target="_blank">#NewYearsAtTonys</a>, featuring an all-you-can-eat version of their famous sausage &amp; vegan friendly menu, a custom beer glass, and a guaranteed seat (which can be a rare find at Tony''s!). Oh, I almost forgot the best part - bottomless beer which will include Pliny the Elder, Smog City''s Mai Tai Hoptonic, Societe''s The Pupil, plus dozens more. The $75 ticket also comes with a raffle ticket which gives you the chance to win a specialty bottle that''s hand-picked from Tony''s personal beer cellar. This event will sell out, so act fast!\r\n\r\n<em>818-253-1710</em>\r\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1566584406891665/" target="_blank"><em>https://www.facebook.com/events/1566584406891665/</em></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1566584406891665/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-834 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/ladyfacenye-e1419390789982.jpg" alt="Ladyface Alehouse New Year''s Eve 2014" width="698" height="677" /></a>\r\n<strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1566584406891665/" target="_blank">Ladyface Alehouse &amp; Brasserie - Agoura Hills</a></strong></h3>\r\nPre-game at Ladyface, make it your midnight toasting spot, or have dinner and stay the whole night. Whatever you plan on doing, Ladyface will have live music from Drewin Young and the J''s, a midnight toast of a special 7% Scotch Ale, and of course Ladyface''s awesome French brasserie menu. If you''re staying all night, guarantee your spot by reserving a table for two for $75 or a table for four for $100, which includes a bottle of ale or champagne. If you''re looking for a classier craft beer NYE experience, this is it.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.ladyfaceale.com/events.html" target="_blank"><em>http://www.ladyfaceale.com/events.html</em></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href="http://www.ladyfaceale.com/events.html" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-835 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/goodbeercompanynye.jpg" alt="Good Beer Company New Year''s Eve 2014" width="526" height="526" /></a>\r\n<strong><a href="http://www.ladyfaceale.com/events.html" target="_blank">The Good Beer Company - Downtown Santa Ana</a></strong></h3>\r\nThe Good Beer Company is one of Orange County''s newest breweries located in the heart of Downtown Santa Ana and they''re throwing an epic NYE craft beer bash. The festivities include live music all night, food delivered straight to the tap room, and their delicious lineup of craft beers (including new beers released all night, special dry hopped variations, and never-before-tasted wild ales). If you want to close out 2014 with a bang in a small brewery setting, The Good Beer Company in Santa Ana is your best bet.\r\n\r\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/395633077266540/" target="_blank"><em>https://www.facebook.com/events/395633077266540/</em></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/395633077266540/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-836 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/storytavernnye.jpg" alt="Story Tavern New Year''s Eve 2014" width="372" height="480" /></a>\r\n<strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/395633077266540/" target="_blank">Story Tavern - Burbank</a></strong></h3>\r\nAffectionately known as "Dr. Burbank''s No Good..Actually Very Good New Year''s Party" is Story Tavern''s answer to the end of 2014. The event features two awesome drinking options for the evening, "The Flight of Destiny", which includes two taster flights featuring a full 40 ounces of awesome: Port Brewing''s Santa''s Little Helper, St. Bernardus'' Christmas Ale, Drake''s Jolly Roger, Eagle Rock''s Jubilee, Sierra Nevada''s Celebration, Anchor''s Christmas, Avery''s Tweak, and Epic''s Smoked and Oaked, all for $32 at the door or $28 online. Or you can go with "No Good..Actually Very Good", which includes four draft beers, ciders, wine, or mixed drinks for $40 at the door or $35 online. You''ll also be able to order food off their delicious comfort food pub menu and play games on the various shuffleboard, ping pong, and fooseball tables around the bar. Great beer, fun games, how could you go wrong?\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.storytavernburbank.com/december-31st-story-tavern-and-dr-burbanks-no-good-actually-very-good-new-years-party-730-pm/" target="_blank"><em>http://www.storytavernburbank.com/december-31st-story-tavern-and-dr-burbanks-no-good-actually-very-good-new-years-party-730-pm/</em></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href="http://www.storytavernburbank.com/december-31st-story-tavern-and-dr-burbanks-no-good-actually-very-good-new-years-party-730-pm/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-837 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/angelcitynye.jpg" alt="Angel City Brewery New Year''s Eve 2014" width="403" height="403" /></a>\r\n<strong><a href="http://www.storytavernburbank.com/december-31st-story-tavern-and-dr-burbanks-no-good-actually-very-good-new-years-party-730-pm/" target="_blank">Angel City Brewery- Downtown LA</a></strong></h3>\r\nDowntown''s favorite (and only) brewery is ringing in the new year with "No Cover New Years", an open party at their Arts District warehouse featuring all their core and 2014 specialty brews, food trucks in their front courtyard, live music in their Beer Hall, free party favors for the first 150 guests, and a special New year''s toast at midnight. If you''re looking to get your craft beer fix in DTLA on NYE, Angel City is where you''ll wanna be.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://angelcitybrewery.com/events/nye-15-angel-city-brewery/" target="_blank"><em>http://angelcitybrewery.com/events/nye-15-angel-city-brewery/</em></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><a href="http://angelcitybrewery.com/events/nye-15-angel-city-brewery/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-838 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/crazyharrysnye-e1419390841835.jpg" alt="Crazy Harry''s New Year''s Eve 2014" width="698" height="262" /></a>\r\n<strong><a href="http://angelcitybrewery.com/events/nye-15-angel-city-brewery/" target="_blank">Crazy Harry''s Bar - Winnetka</a></strong></h3>\r\nIf you''re planning to hang in the Valley this New Year''s Eve, Crazy Harry''s is making it nice and easy for you: All You Can Drink Beer Pass for $40.00. They haven''t posted the tap list yet, but you can bet they''ll have some delicious, hoppy beers flowing. You''ll probably want to take care of food on your own, but after a few double IPAs, you might not even care. Keep it simple, keep it fun, keep it in the Valley, and go to Crazy Harry''s.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.crazyharrysbar.com/index.php/calendar/icalrepeat.detail/2014/12/31/496/-/crazy-harry-s-new-years-eve-party" target="_blank"><em>http://www.crazyharrysbar.com/index.php/calendar/icalrepeat.detail/2014/12/31/496/-/crazy-harry-s-new-years-eve-party</em></a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Got any other LA NYE craft beer event suggestions? Leave them in the comments below or Tweet us at <a href="http://twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. If you attend any of these, be sure to post a picture to our <a href="http://facebook.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">Facebook page</a>!</strong>', 'Celebrate New Year''s Eve 2014 at These 7 LA Craft Beer Events', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'la-new-years-craft-beer-2014', '', '', '2014-12-23 23:22:33', '2014-12-24 07:22:33', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=831', 0, 'post', '', 0),
