(1081, 1, '2015-01-31 13:17:29', '2015-01-31 21:17:29', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1083" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/superbowlcraftbeer.png" alt="Craft Beer Superbowl Los Angeles" width="1200" height="628" />Superbowl and beer. There are very few things that go as perfect together. But instead of sipping on that watered down fizzy yellow stuff like your pops used to, you deserve a real beer. Something with flavor. Something with substance. Something with a ton of piney, juicy, fruity, delicious HOPS.\r\n\r\nHere are 14 spots around LA (and OC, and SB) that you can get your craft beer on while watching the big game.\r\n<h3><strong>38 Degrees Ale House &amp; Grill - Alhambra</strong></h3>\r\nOnce again, 38 Degrees is giving craft beer lovers a haven to watch the big game.38 taps, 8 TVs, a special super bowl food menu, and some themed beer flights like a fresh IPA flight and a barrel-aged flight. Alhambra ain''t too far of an Uber ride, so 38 Degrees should definitely be on your list.\r\n<h3><strong>Blue Palms Brewhouse - Hollywood</strong></h3>\r\nIn addition to their normal brewhouse space and 24 taps, Blue Palms is taking over the historic Fonda Theater next door with additional tables and a giant screen showing the game. No reservations, first come, first served.\r\n<h3><strong>The Daily Pint - West LA</strong></h3>\r\nThe Daily Pint is hosting their annual Superbowl party featuring complimentary BBQ food and a huge 12 foot big screen TV, and one of the best tap lists on the West side. This is the best option for Santa Monica and Venice residents.\r\n<h3><strong>Brewster''s at Four Points LAX - Inglewood</strong></h3>\r\n16 taps, 100 bottles, excellent gastropub food menu, and 16 TVs. Add $5 draft beers and 50% off appetizers to that and you''ve got yourself a Superbowl party.\r\n<h3><strong>The Factory Gastrobar - Long Beach</strong></h3>\r\nPats vs. Hawks. Hops vs. Malt. You''re at Hopped LA so we already know what team you''re on. The Factory is putting it to the test. The Hops team is loaded up with heavy hop hitters like Avery Maharaja, Ballast Point Grapefruit Sculpin, and Sierra Nevada''s Hop Hunter, while the Malt team is weighed down with thicker, breadier options like Progress Brewing''s Mustang Beglian Tripel and Bear Republic''s Red Rocket. During the pre-game (2:30-3:30PM) all beers are $4 and wings are 50% off, then after kick-off, beers will be $5 and all food will be 25% until the end of the game. Go Team Hops!\r\n<h3><strong>The Pub at Golden Road - Burbank/Glendale</strong></h3>\r\nGolden Road is back at it again this Superbowl Sunday with $30 all you can drink beers, the big game on surround sound on the 7 TVs around the bar. Stay till the end to try your luck on the raffle prizes throughout the game. First come, first served.\r\n<h3><strong>Tuning Fork - Studio City</strong></h3>\r\nThe 18 taps of craft beer and ideal location along Ventura Blvd in Studio City might be enough to bring you in. But the "All-Or-Nothing Halftime Challenge" might be the real kicker. Contestants will have 5 minutes to take down Chef Jay''s All-Or-Nothing Burger to get it on the house. If you fail, don''t worry, you''ll still receive a free gift and half off your burger for attempting.\r\n<h3><strong>Bottle Logic Brewing - Anaheim</strong></h3>\r\nAnaheim residents rejoice! Your favorite neighborhood brewery is serving up something special this Superbowl. In addition to the game playing on their giant projector screen and their regular line up awesome beers, Bottle Logic is featuring two special brews to let Pats and Hawks fans show their team pride. Boston Tea Party is a session IPA with black currant and tropical iced tea and Seattle Roasters is a session IPA with Balboa iced coffee blend. I haven''t tasted either, but I already know they scored a touchdown with these two.\r\n<h3><strong>The Woodman - Sherman Oaks</strong></h3>\r\nIf you haven''t figured out already, we love The Woodman in Sherman Oaks. And that''s before we found out about this All You Can Eat &amp; Drink deal they''ve got going on for Superbowl. You better come hungry and thirsty because for $75 you can eat and drink anything you want. Plus they have TVs all over the place. If you''re looking to stay in the Valley, The Woodman might be your spot. Get your tickets here: tinyurl.com/o9orjvx\r\n<h3><strong>Telegraph Brewing - Santa Barbara</strong></h3>\r\nDon''t say we''re not thinking of you Santa Barbara drinkers. Telegraph Brewery is offering up an alternative to the noisy sports bar and opening up their tasting room, offering beer specials, bringing in tacos from the Si Senor food truck, and playing the big game.\r\n<h3><strong>City Tavern - Downtown LA</strong></h3>\r\nOne of our favorite beer bars in DTLA will have the game playing on their 8 TVs with full sound and happy hour throughout the game, which includes $10 32oz craft beer growlers from their 28 taps, $4 well drinks, $6 wines, $7 specialty cocktails, and $3.50-$6.00 small bites. Get there early to grab your spot and enjoy full brunch and bottomless drinks from 11am-3pm and $5 parking at Fig@7th.\r\n<h3><strong>Dog Haus Biergarten - Pasadena</strong></h3>\r\nThe gourmet hot dog chain''s Pasadena outpost is featuring$2.50-$4.00 beer specials from their craft beer taps all day. You can even bring your non-beer drinking friends to enjoy their Build your own Bloody Mary bar, $4 well drinks, $2 off specialty cocktails, $1 off wines, and $1 burger sliders.\r\n<h3><strong>King Harbor Brewing - Redondo Beach</strong></h3>\r\nKing Harbor and Barley Hops Grill are teaming up to give Redondo Beach residents a great option this Superbowl Sunday. For $30 pre-sale and $35 at the door, you get unlimited access to the BBQ buffet and 3 beers, plus $1 off all additional beers. Beer, BBQ, Superbowl, what can be better?\r\n<h3><strong>Phantom Carriage - Carson</strong></h3>\r\nMultitask this Superbowl Sunday and check out LA''s newest brewery and watch the Superbowl at the same time. Phantom Carriage will have the game playing on a 60" 4k TV and a 130" projection screen while serving up food specials and releasing another new beer. Come thirsty.', '14 Awesome LA Craft Beer Spots to Watch the Superbowl', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'craft-beer-superbowl-los-angeles', '', '', '2015-01-31 13:18:29', '2015-01-31 21:18:29', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=1081', 0, 'post', '', 0),
