(1087, 1, '2015-02-09 22:02:55', '2015-02-10 06:02:55', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1088" src="http://localhost:8888/wp-content/uploads/2015/02/pty2015.png" alt="Pliny the Younger Los Angeles 2015" width="1200" height="628" />\r\n\r\nPliny the Younger season is here and Los Angeles is about to get reaaaaaal hoppy! Whether you''re a PtY vet or you''re still searching for your first taste of Russian River''s golden nectar, this is your guide to finding out where to drink Pliny the Younger Triple IPA in Los Angeles &amp; Orange County in 2015.\r\n\r\n<em>Last Updated: February 12th, 2015</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">The Salted Pig - Riverside</span></strong></h3>\r\n<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Monday, February 16th. 11:00am</strong></span>\r\n\r\nThe Salted Pig in Riverside will follow up their successful tapping of Pliny the Younger last year with the 2015 edition. Get there early, a line will form and tickets will be distributed. $8 for a 8oz pour, limit one per customer. <a href="https://www.facebook.com/thesaltedpig/photos/a.660853280613346.1073741825.145527572145922/910981335600538/" target="_blank">Here''s their Facebook post for more info.</a> Do it up!\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Hollingshead''s Delicatessan - Orange</strong></span></h3>\r\n<em><strong>Monday, February 16th, 10:00am</strong></em>\r\n\r\nOnce again, Orange, CA''s Hollingshead''s Deli will be tapping the delicious Younger along with several other Russian River brews. The keg taps at 10am but you can be sure Orange County hop heads will be flocking there, so get there a little early to make sure you start your week off on the right foot.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tustin Brewing Company - Tustin</strong></span></h3>\r\n<em><strong>Wednesday, February 18th, 11am</strong></em>\r\n\r\nAs part of Tustin Brewing Co''s Russian River Week, they''ll be tapping their keg of Pliny the Younger on Wednesday the 18th. Here''s the deal: the $8 tickets go on sale right at 11am when they open up. Plan on getting there early, as the line will definitely be long by that point. They won''t be tapping the keg until 3pm, so you can choose to hang around or leave and come back later that day to redeem your ticket for an 8oz pour of the delicious triple IPA. You know the drill, one ticket per person, no saving spots in line. Everyone deserves a taste!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Beachwood BBQ &amp; Brewing - Long Beach &amp; Seal Beach</strong></span></h3>\r\n<em><strong>Tuesday, February 24th - Thursday, March 5th</strong></em>\r\n\r\nOn January 20th, Beachwood began selling tickets to their 4th Annual Pliny Fights Cancer Charity Raffle. Basically, you can buy as many tickets as you want for $5 apiece until February 21st at 10pm. Then on February 23rd 130 tickets will be drawn at random while being livestreamed on the Four Brewers podcast. Winners can redeem their Pliny the Younger pour between February 24th and March 5th. Support your love for craft beer and the work of the Melanoma Research Foundation and head down to your local Beachwood location to buy your tickets today! <a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeachwoodBBQ/photos/a.221655001193148.64657.116567235035259/998262143532426/?type=1" target="_blank">Check out this flyer for more details.</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>38 Degrees Ale House &amp; Grill - Alhambra</strong></span></h3>\r\n<strong><em>Saturday, February 21st, 2015, 11:30am</em></strong>\r\n\r\nOne of LA''s best beer bars is at it again this year with their special Russian River flight featuring tasters of their all around amazing beers plus the coveted Pliny the Younger. Their staff will start passing out tickets when the line forms and doors will open at 11:30am. <a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1395158724125785/" target="_blank">Check out their Facebook event for more details.</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Mohawk Bend - Echo Park</strong></span></h3>\r\n<em><strong>Saturday, February 21st, 2015, 9:30am</strong></em>\r\n\r\nIt''s official, Pliny the Younger will once again be gracing the taps at Echo Park''s amazing craft beer spot, Mohawk Bend. Starting at 9:30am, they''ll be passing out tickets to all those who were smart enough to start lining up early. Once tickets are passed out, you can hang around, grab some beers and some food and wait for the staggered pouring of the Younger starting at 11am. Sounds like a plan to me!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Haven Gastropub - Orange</strong></span></h3>\r\n<em><strong>Sunday, February 22nd, 2015, 9:00am</strong></em>\r\n\r\nHaven Gastropub in Old Towne Orange is hosting a Sunday morning beer brunch featuring a special Russian River flight as well as 1 full pour of Pliny the Younger per person. Come for the beer, stay for the brunch, and take full advantage of their $3 brunch beers from 9-11am once you''ve finished with your Pliny. Get there early because they''ve already started giving away the first 10 spots in line. <a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/378144195680001/" target="_blank">Check out their Facebook event for more details.\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tony''s Darts Away - Burbank</strong></span><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/378144195680001/" target="_blank">\r\n</a></h3>\r\n<em><strong>End of February, Early March - Date &amp; Time TBD</strong></em>\r\n\r\nWe''ve gotten word that Tony''s will once again be pouring Younger this year, however we do not have confirmed date. We''ll update this post as soon as we get more details on their tapping.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Blue Palms Brewhouse - Hollywood</strong></span></h3>\r\n<em><strong>Date &amp; Time TBD</strong></em>\r\n\r\nBlue Palms has confirmed that they indeed WILL be tapping Pliny the Younger at some point over the next month or so. Like last year, it will again be a charity event, but other than that, the details are scarce. We''ll keep you guys updated as soon as we get word.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Other Possible 2015 Pliny the Younger Locations</strong></span></h3>\r\nThe following locations have not confirmed whether they''ll be pouring Pliny the Younger this year, but they did serve it up in 2014, so it''s likely that most of them may be pouring it again at some point over the next month or so.\r\n\r\n<em>Verdugo Bar - Glassell Park</em>\r\n<em>Barbara''s at the Brewery - Lincoln Heights</em>\r\n<em>Father''s Office - Culver City &amp; Santa Monica</em>\r\n<em>Library Alehouse - Santa Monica</em>\r\n<em>The Surly Goat - West Hollywood</em>\r\n<em>Boneyard Bistro - Sherman Oaks</em>\r\n<em>The Daily Pint - West Los Angeles</em>\r\n<em>Lucky Baldwins - Pasadena &amp; Sierra Madre</em>\r\n<em>The Bottle Room - Whittier</em>\r\n<em>Eureka Burger - Claremont</em>\r\n\r\nFor more awesome Pliny the Younger 2015 coverage, check out <a href="http://thefullpint.com/events/hopwatch-2015-find-pliny-younger-socal/" target="_blank">The Full Pint</a>.', '#PlinyWatch: Your 2015 Guide to Finding Pliny The Younger in LA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'plinywatch-2015', '', '\nhttp://thefullpint.com/events/hopwatch-2015-find-pliny-younger-socal/', '2015-02-14 23:00:55', '2015-02-15 07:00:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/?p=1087', 0, 'post', '', 0),
