(1269, 4, '2015-04-22 22:35:36', '2015-04-23 05:35:36', 'The craft beer community in LA is a great one. At almost any bar, brewery, or beer event that you go to, there are people who are fun, friendly, and super passionate about beer and ready to offer up suggestions and advice for you to discover more cool beer experiences. Los Angeles'' beer bloggers are comprised of these awesome people. Below, in alphabetical order, are the BEST craft beer blogs in LA that we follow on a daily basis to catch up on any news, events, openings, and new beer releases that we may have missed out on.\n<h3></h3>\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><a href="http://www.beerguyla.com/" target="_blank">\n</a><a href="http://www.beerguyla.com/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1273 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/beerguyla-e1429767505768.jpg" alt="Beer Guy LA" width="500" height="83" /></a></h3>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://www.beerguyla.com/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Beer Guy LA</span></a></strong></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeerGuyLA" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/beerGuyLA" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/beerguyla/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nBeer Guy LA is a beer blog started in 2012 by Jeff Prosser, with occasional contributions from his buddies Dave and Dane. On this blog, you''re going to find updates on news and events, and you''ll also find interesting beer reviews. They update at least a couple times a month and keep their social channels pretty active. Beer Guy LA gives a good first-person perspective on the LA beer scene from three different dudes, so check them out and give them a follow.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3 style="text-align: left;"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a href="http://www.beeroftomorrow.com/" target="_blank">\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-1274 size-medium" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/beeroftomorrow-300x300.png" alt="Beer of Tomorrow" width="300" height="300" />\nBeer of Tomorrow</a></strong></span></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeerOfTomorrow" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/beeroftomorrow" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/beeroftomorrow/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nBeer of Tomorrow is the personal craft beer blog of LA Times beer writer and Beer Paper LA Managing Editor, John Verive. You''d think a guy with writing responsibilities on two other big outlets would neglect his personal blog, but that is NOT the case. Headed up with his wife, Julie, the Verives take the art of craft beer journalism to the next level, promoting the big guys as well as the small ones. If you are trying to stay on top of the latest in LA beer, Beer of Tomorrow is one site you''re gonna want to follow.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a href="http://beerpaperla.com/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1275" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/beerpaperla.png" alt="beerpaperla" width="515" height="83" />\nBeer Paper LA</a></strong></span></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/BeerPaperLA" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/beerpaperla" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/beerpaperla/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nStarted by craft beer fiends Aaron Carroll and Rob Wallace in 2013, Beer Paper LA is probably LA''s most legitimate craft beer focused publication, with distribution of its paper edition at breweries and beer bars around LA and OC, their online edition, as well as their brand new podcast. They''ve also got an all-star cast of contributors, including the aforementioned John Verive as Managing Editor, Sarah Bennett from LA Weekly as Associate Editor, Head Writer Daniel Drennon, and contributors Kip Barnes and Sean Inman, among others. Make sure you keep your eyes open for their latest copy at your favorite neighborhood beer spot, and if you don''t see it, tell someone from the BPLA crew and I''m sure they''ll start keeping stock there.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a href="http://www.beersearchparty.com/" target="_blank">\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-1276 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/beersearchparty-e1429767546874.jpg" alt="Beer Search Party" width="450" height="293" />\nBeer Search Party</a></strong></span></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/pages/Beer-Search-Party/109752517459?ref=ts" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/BeerSearchParty" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/beersearchparty/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nBeer Search Party is the product of writer Sean Inman. I have to applaud Sean for his work on his blog as well as at Beer Paper LA. This guy churns out a TON of interesting beer content - from local news, nationwide industry news, beer reviews, new openings, events, and fun beer drinking tips. If you''re looking for a lot of content on a ton of various beer topics, Beer Search Party is where you want to go. And hopefully, Sean won''t slow down!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://www.beersinparadise.com/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1277" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/beersinparadise.jpg" alt="Beers in Paradise" width="240" height="141" />\nBeers in Paradise</strong></span></a></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/beersinparadise" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/beersinparadise" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/beersinparadise/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nOk, so I don''t know too much about Beers in Paradise, except that its run by a few different guys and they update occasionally. I''d say they''re much more active on social media than the blog itself, but that doesn''t mean you should ignore it. They''re active in the LA beer scene and will post about events and news that you should probably know about. Give them a look.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a href="http://bierkast.com/" target="_blank">\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-1278 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/bierkast-e1429767565416.jpg" alt="Bierkast" width="350" height="305" />\nBierkast</a></strong></span></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/Bierkast" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/bierkast" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/bierkast/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nBierkast is the craft beer blog of Kip Barnes, one of #LAbeer''s most active supporters. Not only is he the founder of Bierkast, Kip is also a founding member of the LA Beer Bloggers group, the author of 2014''s The Beer Lover''s Guide to Southern California, a member of the Pacific Gravity Homebrew Club, and the co-founder of Los Angeles Ale Works. Kip, along with a number of contributors, post frequently to the blog, usually at least several times per month. He also keeps LA updated on the Bierkast social media channels. Kip''s brewing experience gives a welcome perspective to the happenings in the LA beer scene, and from what we hear, his brewery LA Ale  Works has some exciting things in the works. If you''re not following Kip and Bierkast, then you''re missing out on a big component of the LA craft beer scene.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://www.cabrewmasters.com/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1279" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/californiabrewmasters.png" alt="California BrewMasters" width="235" height="119" />\nCalifornia BrewMasters</strong></span></a></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/cabrewmasters?fref=ts" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/cabrewmasters" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/cabrewmasters" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nCalifornia BrewMasters is a book and blog by photographer Nick Gingold which combines interviews and portrait photography of some of the state''s best brewers and craft beer figures. Funded via Kickstarter and released in 2014, you can find the California BrewMasters book both online and in some of its featured breweries. As for Nick, you can find him around town at some of LA''s coolest beer spots and events, camera in hand and providing some of the more in-depth and visual LA craft beer coverage around.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://caskalela.com/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1280 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/caskalela-e1429767582147.png" alt="Cask Ale LA" width="300" height="300" />\nCask Ale LA</strong></span></a></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/caskalela" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/caskalela" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/caskalela/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nTo say Aaron Champion loves cask ale is an understatement. After moving to Los Angeles from Toronto, Aaron realized that cask ale was pretty hard to come by in these parts. That''s why he founded Cask Ale LA, so that all of us drinkers around town could learn about the cool bars, breweries, and events pouring cask ales. While we usually prefer our beers a bit hoppier, colder, and more carbonated, cask ale is a traditional style that every beer drinker should get to know. And following Cask Ale LA is how you make that happen.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://craftbeerguy.com/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1281" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/craftbeerguy.png" alt="Craft Beer Guy" width="200" height="185" />\nCraft Beer Guy</strong></span></a></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/TheCraftBeerGuy" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/1CraftBeerGuy" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/craft.beer.guy/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nLloyd Brown from Craft Beer Guy gets the award for most valuable domain name in the LA beer blogging scene. You can only assume he was early to the game with a name like CraftBeerGuy.com. Lloyd specializes in LA''s South Bay beer scene, sharing his photography from local events and interesting news from the local beer scene. His blog isn''t incredibly active, but he is all over social media, so there is plenty of content to take in. If you want to stay updated on the South Bay beer scene (and who doesn''t!), follow Craft Beer Guy. He also organizes weekend brewery walks in the South Bay, where a group of beer lovers wander from brewery to brewery enjoying the beautiful LA weekend.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><a href="http://thefullpint.com/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1282" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/thefullpint.png" alt="thefullpint" width="550" height="106" />\nThe Full Pint</a></strong></span></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/thefullpint" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/TheFullPint" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/thefullpint/" target="_blank">Instagram\n</a>\n\nFounded in 2007, The Full Pint covers all of Southern California''s craft beer scene, including news, reviews, events, and op-ed pieces on industry trends. The main writers include Danny, Jonny, and Franny and they work hard to cover almost anything and everything craft beer related through So Cal. They post almost daily and are super active on social media so make sure you follow them wherever you get your beer news!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="https://instagram.com/girlswholikebeer/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1283 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/girlswholikebeer-e1429767600301.jpg" alt="Girls Who Like Beer" width="300" height="300" />\nGirls Who Like Beer</strong></span></a></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/GirlsWhoLikeBeer" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/girlslikebeer" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/girlswholikebeer/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nLocal graphic designer, craft beer lover, and co-founder of the LA Beer Bloggers group, Kelly Erickson runs a really well-written and well-designed blog called Girls Who Like Beer. She does a great job keeping local beer drinkers up to date on the best events and new brewery openings around LA, and also sprinkles in some non-LA beer content from time to time as well. Guys, even though it''s called Girls Who Like Beer, don''t be afraid to check this beer blog out - you might just miss out on something awesome!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://www.la-beer-blog.com/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1284" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/labeerblog.jpeg" alt="LA Beer Blog" width="256" height="256" />\nLA Beer Blog</strong></span></a></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/LosAngelesBeerBlog?_rdr" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/labeerblog" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/labeerblog/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nStarted in 2012, LA Beer Blog is the brainchild of Josh Sellers. These days he might not keep the blog super updated, but he remains very active on social media, posting interesting news and photos of the beers he''s enjoying each week. Josh knows what''s up when it comes to #LAbeer, so give LA Beer Blog a follow and don''t miss his updates.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><a href="http://blog.ocbeerblog.com/" target="_blank"><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1286 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/ocbeerblog-e1429767615967.jpg" alt="OC Beer Blog" width="500" height="144" />\nOC Beer Blog</strong></span></a></h3>\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/ocbeerblog" target="_blank">Facebook</a> | <a href="https://twitter.com/OCBeerBlog" target="_blank">Twitter</a> | <a href="https://instagram.com/ocbeerblog/" target="_blank">Instagram</a>\n\nSo I know we''re talking about LA bloggers here, but OC is just a stone''s throw away and their breweries are also pumping out some amazing beers. That''s why you need to know about OC Beer Blog. Greg Nagel is the MAN when it comes to the Orange County craft beer scene. If there is an OC brewer, bottle shop owner, or bartender that has a say in their local beer program, Greg probably knows them. You''ll see him at every OC beer event, and he even organizes the highly successful Firkfest, which just wrapped up its 2nd annual event last month. Want to stay up on everything OC beer? Then you''ll need to follow OC Beer Blog immediately!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><strong>There you have it! The 13 best blogs covering the LA craft beer scene. Did we leave anyone off the list? Let us know in the comments or Tweet us at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a> and we''ll make sure to add them!</strong></h3>', '13 of the Best LA Craft Beer Blogs You Need to Follow', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-la-beer-blogs', '', '', '2015-04-22 22:35:36', '2015-04-23 05:35:36', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1269', 0, 'post', '', 1),
