(1466, 4, '2014-07-24 14:51:32', '2014-07-24 21:51:32', 'The San Fernando Valley - a highly populated section of Los Angeles that gained notoriety by the sprawling celebrity ranch homes of yore, old Western flicks, and much more. But as the years have gone by, a new movement is coming to light. I am, of course, talking about the LA craft beer movement. Amongst the diversity, neighborhoods, existing charm, oh, and that massive Budweiser facility, there is growing interest in saturating the SFV into a craft beer destination.\n\nWe have a <a href="http://hoppedla.com/best-beer-bars-san-fernando-valley-east/">guide to the East SFV</a>, but this edition of Hopped LA''s guide to the best beer bars takes you on a journey of the best beer bars in the SFV west of the 405. Get your notepads out, people. You''re going to want to write this down.\n\n<em>Last updated: January 2016</em>\n<h2>Breweries</h2>\n<h3><img class="alignnone wp-image-1775" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/craft-beer-sfv.jpg" alt="craft-beer-sfv" width="600" height="400" /><strong><a href="http://www.handbrewedbeer.com/" target="_blank">Hand-Brewed Beer</a></strong></h3>\n<div class="mod" data-md="1002" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQkCkIlAEoBDAR">\n<div class="_eFb">\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQghwIlQEoADAR"><em><span class="_Xbe"><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Hand-Brewed+Beer,+LLC/@34.2482235,-118.593791,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x205c827ec1a6c965?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQ_BIIiAEwDQ" target="_blank">9771 Variel Ave, Chatsworth, CA 91311</a></span></em></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQghwIlQEoADAR"></div>\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQghwIlQEoADAR">Hand-Brewed in one of new nano-breweries that opened up in Chatsworth. There''s no tasting room, but you''ll find Hand-Brewed at all the local festivals and some select bars around town. Even though it''s still a small operation, <a href="http://www.handbrewedbeer.com/#!beers/clg4" target="_blank">they''re brewing quite a few one-offs and seasonal beers in addition to their core lineup</a>.</div>\n&nbsp;\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQghwIlQEoADAR"></div>\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQghwIlQEoADAR"></div>\n<div class="mod" data-md="1006" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQkCkIlgEoBTAS"></div>\n<div class="mod" data-md="1006" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQkCkIlgEoBTAS"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1776" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/818-brewing.jpg" alt="818-brewing" width="600" height="800" /></div>\n<h3 class="mod" data-md="1006" data-ved="0ahUKEwjE7YnfsYzKAhVC_WMKHaCcDNIQkCkIlgEoBTAS"><strong><a href="http://818brewing.com/home/" target="_blank">8one8 Brewing</a></strong></h3>\n<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/8one8+Brewing/@34.2334042,-118.5885492,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x27b78fa9ba87f908?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi_gOC7sozKAhUNwGMKHdV5DhIQ_BIIazAN" target="_blank"><em>8951 De Soto Ave, Canoga Park, CA 91304</em></a>\n\nWe were able to have a first look at 8one8 Brewing when <a href="http://hoppedla.com/first-breweries-sfv/" target="_blank">we visited Pac City Brewery</a> back in June of 2014. It wasn''t the best first impression due to Pac City''s cold box having issues, so we gave 8one8 a pass then. Since that time, they''ve been committed to getting their brewery up and running, and getting their beers into the hands of the people. So far, they''ve been well-received with their Matador Red and Good Day IPA, and we''re excited to see them continue to bring their brews to the 818 and beyond.\n<h2>Beer Bars/Tasting Rooms</h2>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/pedlars-fork-beer-bars-in-the-sfv.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-424" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/pedlars-fork-beer-bars-in-the-sfv-300x200.jpg" alt="pedlars-fork-beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="400" /></a></strong><a href="http://www.pedalersfork.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Pedalers Fork</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Pedalers+Fork/@34.1573681,-118.638918,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x9d87422847c5e261" target="_blank">23504 Calabasas Rd, Calabasas, CA 91302</a></em>\n\nAlong the Arroyo Calabasas tributary sits Pedalers Fork, a restaurant/coffee shop/bike shop that suffers from the best kind of identity crisis. Oh, and they have 30+ taps of all craft beer, with a good amount dedicated to the hops we love.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/the-local-peasant-beer-bars-in-the-sfv.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-427" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/the-local-peasant-beer-bars-in-the-sfv-300x300.jpg" alt="the-local-peasant-beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="600" /></a><a href="http://www.thelocalpeasant.com/" target="_blank"><strong>The Local Peasant</strong></a></h3>\n<div class="mod" data-md="1002" data-ved="0ahUKEwi-trqMqIzKAhVLw2MKHZaXA8cQkCkIlwEoBTAP">\n<div class="_eFb">\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwi-trqMqIzKAhVLw2MKHZaXA8cQghwImAEoADAP"><em><span class="_Xbe"><a href="http://22901 Ventura Blvd, Woodland Hills, CA 91364" target="_blank">22901 Ventura Blvd, Woodland Hills, CA 91364</a></span></em></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="mod" data-md="1006" data-ved="0ahUKEwi-trqMqIzKAhVLw2MKHZaXA8cQkCkImQEoBjAQ"></div>\nThe spacious, West Valley counterpart boasts a HUGE, open interior with communal-style tables for groups, or booths for a more intimate experience. The taps go almost all the way around the center bar here, presenting a high probability that you''ll find a hoppy brew you''ll like. The last time I visited, it was an order of Alpine''s Hoppy Birthday and a seat out on the expansive patio that did the trick.\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Screen-Shot-2014-07-24-at-1.16.20-PM.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-443" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Screen-Shot-2014-07-24-at-1.16.20-PM-298x300.png" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="604" /></a>\n<h3><a href="http://hookburger.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Hook Burger</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Hook+Burger/@34.1830901,-118.60637,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x53487cb7efa9c96e?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiy9Lr3qIzKAhUC6WMKHeLGDgAQ_BIIggEwCg" target="_blank">6201 Topanga Canyon Blvd, Woodland Hills, CA 91367</a></em>\n\nAt first I was hesitant to include Hook Burger on the list. That was until I remembered that they are one of the very few places that have been graced with distribution by Agoura''s <a href="http://www.ladyfaceale.com/" target="_blank">Ladyface Ale Companie</a> - and that Ladyface IPA is pretty good. Go here mainly for the delish burgers, but rest easy knowing you can grab a Ladyface or Eagle Rock brew.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-429" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv-300x300.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="600" /></a><a href="http://theirbar.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Instant Replay</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Instant+Replay/@34.2086297,-118.605456,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x16566eb40dcb8f19?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiW-ILXqYzKAhUPzGMKHbtgAv0Q_BIIcjAK" target="_blank">21927 Saticoy St, Canoga Park, CA 91304</a></em>\n\nYou probably wouldn''t have heard of IR Bar without me telling you, but if you have - kudos. This unassuming dive bar looks like it''s been around for awhile, but that doesn''t mean the beer is old. They''re rotating nine taps of all different sorts, but the IPAs are not ignored.\n\nCurrently, you''ll be happy to find Stone''s Unapologetic and Noble''s Big Whig filling up glasses.\n\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-1783" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/hq-gastropub.jpg" alt="hq-gastropub" width="600" height="600" />\n<h3><strong><a href="http://hqgastropub.com/" target="_blank">HQ Gastropub</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/HQ+Gastropub/@34.1669599,-118.5903418,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x119f20f240ef826c?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjNo6XmuozKAhUQ0GMKHaHIChsQ_BIIbDAK" target="_blank">20969 Ventura Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 91364</a></em>\n\nHQ is a relatively new player to the game that brings a rock ''n'' roll concept to the elevated pub venue. The beer list brings you everything from Alpine''s Hoppy Birthday to Bear Republic''s Racer 5, and a lot in between. The chatter we''ve heard in the beginning was the price range, but that shouldn''t affect the beers too much. Dine on some shared plates and knock back a few pints. You''ll be alright.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv1.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-433" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv1-300x225.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="450" /></a><a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz/taps-valley-gastropub-northridge" target="_blank"><strong>Taps Valley Gastropub</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Taps+Valley+Gastropub/@34.2585287,-118.5392796,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x683ce07c5bf299aa" target="_blank">18673 Devonshire St, Northridge, CA 91324</a></em>\n\nYou all remember Hot''s Tacos, right? Oh, you don''t? That''s no surprise, as that place came and went without a worry, and was subsequently replaced by Taps Valley Gastropub. The location next to an LA Fitness makes you have that internal struggle between exercise or beer drinking, but we know the latter always wins.\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv2.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-439" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv2-300x225.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="450" /></a>\n<h3><a href="http://www.yardhouse.com/ca/northridge-restaurant/" target="_blank"><strong>Yard House</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Yard+House/@34.239272,-118.5559964,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x4153e5b648ac0951" target="_blank">9301 Tampa Ave, Northridge, CA 91324</a></em>\n\nIf you''ve been to a Yard House location before, then you know what it''s all about: a bunch of beer taps, some alright food, and yard sticks. Just make sure you have a designated driver before you decide to chug that yard full of Dogfish Head 90-Minute.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv3.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-441" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv3-300x225.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="450" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.crazyharrysbar.com" target="_blank">Crazy Harry''s Bar</a> </strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Crazy+Harry''s+Bar/@34.208188,-118.571555,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xad89c3ccac71872f" target="_blank">20112 Saticoy St, Winnetka, CA 91306</a></em>\n\nA few years ago, this Mid-Valley beer bar opened up during a time when the inhabitants of Winnetka weren''t necessarily itching for craft beer. Holding their ground and waiting out the storm, Crazy Harry''s Bar has developed a great following due to their 80/80 beer club and <a title="Deschutes Brewery Takes Over Crazy Harry’s Bar" href="http://hoppedla.com/deschutes-brewery-crazy-harrys-bar/" target="_blank">their constant tap takeovers</a>.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv4.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-442" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv4-295x300.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="608" /></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/BigMamasPapasPizzeriaTarzana" target="_blank"><strong>BMPP Tavern &amp; Lounge</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Big+Mama''s+%26+Papa''s+Pizzeria/@34.172972,-118.55896,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x68d76962ae1d4503" target="_blank">19527 Ventura Blvd, Tarzana, CA 91356</a></em>\n\nWhat the heck is BMPP, you ask? Likely, you''ve heard of the pizza parlor franchise Big Mama''s and Papa''s, only this time they are cashing in on the craft beer. Along Ventura Blvd. in Tarzana, this spot opened up to cater to the West SFV and they are delivering good beer. Albeit, you won''t find the whales here, you can hopefully settle for one of the solid IPAs they have on tap.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv5.jpg"><img class="alignleft wp-image-446" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv5-300x225.jpg" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="450" /></a><a href="http://www.wholefoodsmarket.com/stores/tarzana" target="_blank"><strong>Vine 39 inside Whole Foods Market</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Whole+Foods+Market/@34.1705649,-118.541079,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x5b05fb01a16086f7?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjVlOqUrIzKAhVO6WMKHY6NDLIQ_BIIezAK" target="_blank">18700 Ventura Blvd #190, Tarzana, CA 91356</a></em>\n\nAfter the <a title="Meet Vine 39, Tarzana’s Newest Craft Beer &amp; Wine Bar" href="http://hoppedla.com/vine39-whole-foods-tarzana/" target="_blank">grand re-opening of Whole Foods'' specialty beer and wine bar, Vine 39</a>, the people of Tarzana were blessed with great wine, new menu items, and several taps of craft beer. I''ll even give a nod to their great selection of bottled beer, as <a href="http://instagram.com/p/qzhtn9CJ0V" target="_blank">I picked up some of Bear Republic''s Cafe Racer 15 the other day</a>. Drop by for a pint or two on draft, or grab your favorite bottle and have them open it up for you, you''re bound to have a good time either way.\n<h3><strong> <a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv.png"><img class="alignleft wp-image-449" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/beer-bars-in-the-sfv-300x300.png" alt="beer-bars-in-the-sfv" width="600" height="600" /></a>Honorable Mention: <a href="http://www.greenjug.com/" target="_blank">Green Jug Fine Wines and Spirits</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Green+Jug+Fine+Wine+%26+Spirits/@34.1858863,-118.6432607,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x99cb2b48c983745c?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwj7ntvVrIzKAhVV52MKHRCnDy4Q_BIIdDAM" target="_blank">6307 Platt Ave, Woodland Hills, CA 91367</a></em>\n\nThis is not a beer bar (although they do have a bar inside for <a href="http://www.greenjug.com/shopcontent.asp?type=calendar" target="_blank">their scheduled tastings</a>), but this is hands down the BEST bottle shop in the west part of the San Fernando Valley. One of the few spots that gets regular shipments of Pliny the Elder and other hard-to-get beers, Green Jug is owned by welcoming and very knowledgable people that are sure to connect you to the tasty brews you love.\n\nWell, that does it for the West San Fernando Valley, but don''t worry, we''ll be coming back with the must-stop spots on the OTHER side of the 405 Freeway to complete our guide to the best beer bars in the SFV.\n\nDid I miss a cool beer bar that you think should be on our list? Let me know in the comments or on Twitter at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. Cheers!\n\n&nbsp;', 'Your Guide to the Best Craft Beer Spots in the West SFV', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-craft-beer-spots-in-the-west-sfv', '', '', '2014-07-24 14:51:32', '2014-07-24 21:51:32', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=422', 0, 'post', '', 9),
(1467, 4, '2014-11-24 13:07:13', '2014-11-24 21:07:13', 'Picture this: you''re a craft beer fiend and it just so happens that you''ve made your way out to Pasadena. It doesn''t matter why you''re out there. You could''ve been dragged out for some shopping or to catch a show at the Pasadena Playhouse, but the fact of matter is you need some fine, delicious craft beer...STAT. Fear not, hop heads, I''ve got your guide to the best beers bars in Pasadena right here.\n<h1>The Best Beer Bars in Pasadena</h1>\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/stone-company-store-craft-beer-in-pasadena1.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-733" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/stone-company-store-craft-beer-in-pasadena1.png" alt="stone-company-store-craft-beer-in-pasadena1" width="800" height="534" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://www.stonebrewing.com/" target="_blank">Stone Company Store</a></h2>\n<address><em>220 S Raymond Ave #103, Pasadena, CA 91105</em></address>The Stone Company Store is a welcomed craft beer destination for Stone lovers in Los Angeles. Aside from having your favorite flagships in stock, they''ll also fill your growlers up with the specialty brews such as Bourbon Barrel Aged Arrogant Bastard and Go To with Lemon Peel and Vanilla Bean. Sample some of the beers that you don''t usually see on the retail shelves while you get that growler filled and you''ll be good to go.\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/slaters-5050-pasadena.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-739" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/slaters-5050-pasadena.png" alt="slaters-5050-pasadena" width="800" height="533" /></a>\n<h2><a href="https://slaters5050.com/locations/pasadena/" target="_blank">Slater''s 50/50</a></h2>\n<address>61 N Raymond Ave, Pasadena, CA 91103</address>Chances are that you are no stranger to Slater''s, whether you''ve been to their locations in San Diego or Orange County. Just as you might expect, the Old Town Pasadena location serves up everything you love about their burgers and craft beer selection. Each location procures their selection from regional breweries and beyond, which means you''ll likely find a number of brews that suit your palate. Currently on tap is Alpine''s Hoppy Birthday, El Segundo''s Blue House IPA, and Ohana''s #hashtag Hops IPA.\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/congregation-ale-house-pasadena.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-741" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/congregation-ale-house-pasadena.png" alt="congregation-ale-house-pasadena" width="708" height="471" /></a><a href="http://congregationalehouse.com/" target="_blank">Congregation Ale House</a></h2>\n<address>300 S Raymond Ave, Pasadena, CA 91105</address>Congregation is another multi-location spot, and is a perfect go-to if you just can''t seem to make up your mind.  They offer a wide range of beer on tap, but let''s just focus on the hoppy ones. Right now, you''ll see the likes of Alpine Nelson, New Belgium''s Hop the Pond, and Epic''s Hopulent on nitro.\n\n<address><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/lucky-baldwins-pub-pasadena.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-742" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/lucky-baldwins-pub-pasadena.png" alt="lucky-baldwins-pub-pasadena" width="800" height="600" /></a></address>\n<h2><a href="http://www.luckybaldwins.com/" target="_blank">Lucky Baldwin''s Pub</a></h2>\n<address>17 S Raymond Ave. Pasadena, CA 91105</address>Lucky Baldwin''s Pub is a Pasadena staple and it would be absolutely blasphemous for me to leave it off this list. While the tap list is populated by mostly British-style and Belgian ales, the sheer number of taps ensures that hop heads can stroll in and order Stone''s Enjoy By, Sierra Nevada''s Pale Ale, and Mother Earth''s Triple Crown IPA.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/lucky-baldwins-trappiste-pasadena.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-743" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/lucky-baldwins-trappiste-pasadena.png" alt="lucky-baldwins-trappiste-pasadena" width="785" height="490" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://www.luckybaldwins.com/" target="_blank">Lucky Baldwins Trappiste Pub &amp; Cafe</a></h2>\n<address>1770 E Colorado Blvd, Pasadena, CA 91106</address>Next up is Lucky Baldwin''s Trappiste Pub &amp; Cafe, which isn''t all that far from their other pub''s location. This one has a cozier vibe than the original, but pretty much delivers on the same type of product with an emphasis on Belgian-style ales. The one thing I will say for those of you looking for hops, Lucky Baldwin''s Trappiste Pub &amp; Cafe currently has a better beer selection than the original given that Alpine''s Duet and Russian River''s Blind Pig join the party.\n\n<address> </address><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/the-blind-donkey-pasadena.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-744" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/the-blind-donkey-pasadena.png" alt="the-blind-donkey-pasadena" width="900" height="598" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://pasadena.theblinddonkey.com/" target="_blank">The Blind Donkey</a></h2>\n<address>53 E Union St, Pasadena, CA 91103</address>Our boy, Ryan Sweeney, is behind this one which means you can bank on this being a good spot. It''s got a decent craft beer selection (currently pouring Firestone''s Easy Jack, Russian River''s Blind Pig, and Deschutes'' Hope Henge), but it''s got an even better cocktail and whiskey lineup. So, if you feel like pivoting from beer, this is your destination.\n\n<address> </address><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/dog-haus-biergarten-pasadena.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-745" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/dog-haus-biergarten-pasadena.png" alt="dog-haus-biergarten-pasadena" width="800" height="533" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://www.doghaus.com/" target="_blank">Dog Haus Biergarten</a></h2>\n<address>93 E Green St, Pasadena, CA 91105</address>This is where things take a turn for the absolute WURST. The food at Dog Haus is awesome, from their "Haus Dogs" to their bratwurst sausages and burgers, and all of these items pair nicely with the beer on tap. If you''re going anytime soon, perhaps a pint of Pizza Port''s Swami''s IPA or Stone''s Enjoy By will do the trick.\n\n<address> </address><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/kings-row-pasadena.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-746" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/kings-row-pasadena.png" alt="kings-row-pasadena" width="800" height="533" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://www.kingsrowpub.com/" target="_blank">King''s Row Gastropub</a></h2>\n<address>20 E Colorado Blvd, Pasadena, CA 91103</address>King''s Row has a pretty cool vibe with communal-style tables, TVs that are perfect for catching the games, and a good amount of craft beer on tap. King''s Row has really stepped it up from a year or so ago because now they''re bringing in kegs of Three Weav3rs, an interesting American IPA from Canadian mircro-brewers Fernie Brewing Company, and Sierra Nevada''s Electric Ray IPL.\n\n<address> </address><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/mission-wine-spirits-pasadena.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-747" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/mission-wine-spirits-pasadena.png" alt="mission-wine-spirits-pasadena" width="800" height="532" /></a>\n<h2><a href="https://www.missionliquor.com/" target="_blank">Honorable Mention: Mission Wine &amp; Spirits</a></h2>\n<address>1785 E Washington Blvd, Pasadena, CA 91104</address>I have a habit of sticking in a retail shop at the end of these guides, because when it''s time to go home it''s always good to stop for some party favors. Also, if the retail shop conducts spirit, wine, and beer tastings, it scores bonus points. That''s Mission Wine &amp; Spirits for you and it''s worth a look if only to see what''s on the shelves.\n<h2>The Guide Doesn''t Have to End</h2>\nI mean, I''m tapped out of destination places to find craft beer in Pasadena, but you probably know of another one that I may have missed. Additionally, let me know your opinion on the ones that I listed either in the comments below or on Twitter at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>.\n\nThanks for reading!', 'Your Guide to the Best Craft Beer Spots in Pasadena', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'pasadena-beer-bars-2', '', '', '2014-11-24 13:07:13', '2014-11-24 21:07:13', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=730', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1486, 4, '2015-08-27 22:16:31', '2015-08-28 05:16:31', '<img class="alignnone wp-image-1494 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ps213-exterior1-e1440736376463.jpg" alt="Public School 213 in Downtown LA" width="600" height="450" />\nIt''s no secret the LA beer scene is pretty young. A lot of the cool beer bars we enjoy now have only popped up within the last couple of years. <a href="http://www.psontap.com/" target="_blank">Public School</a> may have been an early test of Downtown LA''s craft beer scene in 2011, but Grill Concepts restaurant group has gone all in, opening up two new LA outposts last year and, most recently, a complete overhaul of their original DTLA location.\n\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-1490 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ps213-exterior2-e1440735554253.jpg" alt="Downtown LA Craft Beer" width="600" height="652" />\nThe timing for the Downtown school-themed gastropub, renamed Public School 213, couldn''t be better, with the DTLA craft beer scene in the middle of a big boom. We saw <a href="http://www.citytaverndtla.com/" target="_blank">City Tavern</a> open up shop last year over at FIGat7th. Then in May, <a href="http://www.barreldownla.com/" target="_blank">Barrel Down</a> opened up their craft beer hall in the heart of the 7th Street Corridor. In June we saw the opening of the long-anticipated <a href="http://www.mumfordbrewing.com/" target="_blank">Mumford Brewing</a> in the Arts District, joined by <a href="http://www.boomtownbrew.com/" target="_blank">Boomtown Brewery</a>, who have already begun distributing to a handful of bars around LA and have a tasting room space currently under construction. That''s not all though. We''re still waiting on Iron Triangle Brewing, Brian Lenzo''s (Blue Palms) and Cedd Moses'' (Cole''s, Seven Grand) Arts District Brewing headed up by former Pizza Port brewer, Devon Randall, as well as <a href="http://www.dryriverbrewing.com/" target="_blank">Dry River Brewing</a> in nearby Boyle Heights.\n\nWith all of this craft beer buzz heating up in DTLA, can Public School 213 put together an offering that will make them stand out among the crowd?\n\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-1492 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ps213-beerlist1-e1440735719515.jpg" alt="Downtown LA Beer List" width="600" height="449" />\nNew PS213 bar manager, Stephen Sylvester certainly thinks so. Having risen the ranks at Public School''s Culver City location over the last few years, Sylvester comes into DTLA knowing he''s got some work to do. His opening tap list definitely strayed toward the hoppier side, with great IPAs like Alpine''s Hoppy Birthday, Boulevard''s The Calling, Lagunitas'' CitruSinensis, Knee Deep''s Breaking Bud, and Smog City''s Amarilla Gorilla. After experiencing the more balanced tap lists at other Public School locations, us hop heads sure weren''t complaining.\n\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-1491 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ps213-stephen1-e1440735641559.jpg" alt="PS213 Bar Manager" width="600" height="513" />Sylvester''s future plans at Public School 213 include rotating in various sours, especially from his favorite brewery, The Bruery, highlighting offerings from all the local DTLA breweries, and planning regular tap takeovers and beer dinners with the rest of LA''s awesome brewers.\n\nCombine that with a daily happy hour, occasional live music, weekend brunch, a fun yet upscale vibe, and a killer food menu, and you''ve got a craft beer spot that will hold its own against the increasingly crowded DTLA beer bar scene. Go check them out and if you see us, come say hello, because we''ll definitely be back there.', 'As the DTLA Craft Beer Scene Evolves, Public School 213 Evolves With It', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'public-school-213', '', '', '2015-08-27 22:16:31', '2015-08-28 05:16:31', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1486', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1519, 4, '2015-11-22 14:20:21', '2015-11-22 22:20:21', '<h2><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536 aligncenter" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" /></h2>\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can''t go to all of them, doesn''t mean you can''t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we''ve found for the week of Monday November 23rd to Sunday November 29th, 2015.\n\nKnow of an event that''s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we''ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Monday, November 23rd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>King Harbor Musical Tap Takeover at Tuning Fork Gastropub</strong>\n<em>Studio City, 6pm</em></h3>\nKing Harbor Brewing Company is coming to Tuning Fork in Studio City with a new spin on the tap takeover. The goal is to make a creative “musical-beer connection” with the songs playing on the speakers and the beer in your glass to win prizes! For example, let''s say you''re drinking King Harbor''s Abel Brown and "Brown Eyed Girl" is being played. Call it out and win swag from the brewery and Tuning Fork. All King Harbor Beers are just $5 during the event and include their flagship IPA, their single hop pale ale The Quest, their porter Storms a Brewin, their amber ale Day Drinker, and their coffee brown ale Abel Brown.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday, November 24th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Cismontane Tap Takeover at the Bottle Room</strong>\n<em>Whittier, 7pm</em></h3>\nRancho Santa Margarita''s Cismontane Brewing comes into The Bottle Room in Whittier with a lineup of their great beers, including Smoking Santiago a smoked Scotch ale, Cali IPA an IPA with all California grown hops, their 5th Anniversary 5 Grain Saison, and Black’s Nocturne a big imperial oatmeal stout aged in Makers Mark barrels. The Bottle Room''s Chef Tony will also be putting together some recommended food pairings with the beers.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday, November 25th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Deschutes Steal the Glass Night at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nEureka Tasting Kitchen in Hawthorne is back again with their weekly Steal the Glass Night. This week features Pinedrops from Deschutes, a really tasty 6.5% citrusy and piney IPA, plus you get a Deschutes pint glass, so not a bad deal.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday, November 27th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Black Friday VIP Event at Bravery Brewing</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 2pm</em></h3>\nBravery Brewing is throwing a VIP event on Black Friday featuring early admission to the brewery, a free growler fill, the tapping of a VIP cask with a 4oz taster included, a raffle for gift cards and brewery merch, and heavily discounted beers, bottles, growlers, growler fills, glassware, and shirts. <a href="http://braverybrewingbf.brownpapertickets.com/" target="_blank">Grab your $25 ticket here</a>.\n<h3><strong>Goose Island Bourbon County Bottle Release & Tap Takeover Event at Whole Foods Market, Playa Vista</strong>\n<em>Playa Vista, 4pm</em></h3>\nGoose Island''s annual release of Bourbon County Brand Stout hits Los Angeles on Black Friday, and Whole Foods in Playa Vista is one of just 20 locations nationwide invited to celebrate the official day after Thanksgiving release. The festivities begin at 2pm with the bottle release and a tap takeover in their Astro Pub. The bottle release includes Bourbon County Brand Stout (limit 3), Bourbon County Barley Wine (limit 1), Bourbon County Coffee (limit 1), Bourbon County Regal Rye (limit 1), and Bourbon County Rare (limit 1). The tap takeover includes Bourbon County 2013, 2014 & 2015 vertical, Lolita & Sophie. Be sure to arrive early, because this event will be packed, but note they will not be permitting overnight lineups. For questions, email Raul.Moran@wholefoods.com.\n<h3><strong>Bourbon County Tap Takeover at Brew Kitchen Ale House</strong>\n<em>Los Alamitos, 5pm</em></h3>\nGoose Island is taking over the taps at Brew Kitchen Ale House in Los Alamitos with Bourbon County Stout on Black Friday. Expect some BCBS variants, some other Goose Island brews, as well as some special smoked versions of the beer and limited release crystal Bourbon County snifter glasses for purchase.\n<h3><strong>Bourbon County Night at Federal Bar</strong>\n<em>North Hollywood, 6pm</em></h3>\nBourbon County is back and you can celebrate on Black Friday at Federal Bar in NoHo. The Lineup: 2015 Bourbon County Stout, 2014 Bourbon County Stout, 2014 Bourbon County Vanilla Rye, 2013 Bourbon County Stout, Lolita, Matilda, Sophie, Goose IPA, 312 Urban Wheat, 312 Pale Ale, Honkers, and Winter Ale.\n<h3><strong>Goose Island Bourbon County Black Friday at The Surly Goat</strong>\n<em>West Hollywood, 6pm</em></h3>\nGoose Island is migrating to The Surly Goat with a flock of rarities on Black Friday, including Bourbon County Stout 2015, Bourbon County Stout 2014, Bourbon County Stout 2013, Bourbon County Barley Wine 2015, Bourbon County Barley Wine 2014, Bourbon County Barley Wine 2013, Bourbon County Coffee, Bourbon County Regal Rye, Lolita, Matilda, Sofie, Illinois, Goose IPA, and Class of ’88. They''ll also be raffling off a bottle of the highly coveted Rare Bourbon County Brand Stout, with proceeds benefiting The Trevor Project charity.', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Nov 23, 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-nov-23', '', '', '2015-11-22 14:20:21', '2015-11-22 22:20:21', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1519', 0, 'post', '', 0);
