(1522, 4, '2015-11-29 22:16:57', '2015-11-30 06:16:57', 'A few weeks back, we were gearing up for a trip down the coast for San Diego Beer Week and started out the drive on the 405-S. If you''re anything like me, you think about how great it would be to grab a beer in LA''s craft-heavy South Bay or Long Beach.\r\n\r\nOf course, when you''re limited with time and want to beat the traffic, your only logical choice is to just hit Beachwood. But what if your final destination is Long Beach and you''re in the mood for craft? Then, we''ve got a list for you. Here are our picks for the best beer spots in Long Beach.\r\n<h2>Breweries</h2>\r\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/beachwood-sign.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1058" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/beachwood-sign.png" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="471" /></a></h3>\r\n<h3><strong><a href="http://beachwoodbbq.com/brewery.html" target="_blank">Beachwood BBQ and Brewing </a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=beachwood+bbq+and+brewing&amp;oq=beachwood+bbq+and+brewing&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57j0l5.4501j0j4&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;es_sm=91&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=beachwood+bbq+and+brewing+long+beach&amp;rflfq=1&amp;rlha=0&amp;tbm=lcl&amp;rlfi=hd:;si:12889466007995526197" target="_blank">210 E 3rd St, Long Beach, CA 90802</a></em>\r\n\r\nHere''s an obvious choice, and for good reason. If you didn''t know already, Beachwood brews awarding winning beers every year and they don''t seem to slow down. Couple that with their fantastic BBQ, and you''ve got yourself what some would call Heaven. Beachwood pumps out a number of different IPAs such as Melrose, Hop Ninja, Amalgamator, and their new Greenshift, but they also brew a variety of styles impeccably. Be on the look out for sour and wild ale releases from their new Beachwood Blendery.\r\n<h2>Beer Bars/Tasting Rooms</h2>\r\n<h3><a style="line-height: 1.5;" href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach1.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1523" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach1.jpg" alt="craft-beer-long-beach1" width="700" height="466" /></a><strong style="line-height: 1.5;"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/Stateside-Crafts-1469916446558350/" target="_blank">Stateside Crafts</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/4242+Atlantic+Ave,+Long+Beach,+CA+90807/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80dd339f06156c13:0xff7744104360541f?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjk6fyY6KTJAhUJ1mMKHcqwBeMQ8gEIHTAA" target="_blank">4242 Atlantic Ave, Long Beach, CA 90807</a></em>\r\n\r\nIf you''ve read our neighborhood guides in the past, then you know that we will include retail locations that have a tasting room component. Stateside Crafts is one of them and does a nice job at curating an eye-catching tap list with plenty of beers to take home. The latest Untappd check-ins include El Segundo''s Hop Tanker, Knee Deep''s Breaking Bud, and Smog City''s Kumquat Saison.\r\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-22-at-11.51.47-AM.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1524 size-full" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-22-at-11.51.47-AM.png" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="504" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.publicbeerwineshop.com/#/" target="_blank">Public Beer Wine Shop</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/121+W+4th+St,+Long+Beach,+CA+90802/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80dd313812ba7f71:0xd682ccaf59617f5c?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjTqs6n6KTJAhVSzWMKHeETAeQQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">121 W 4th St, Long Beach, CA 90802</a></em>\r\n\r\nWe''re going back-to-back with another bottle shop/tasting room, and Public Beer Wine Shop is no stranger to the LBC crowd. Their helpful staff with help you find the beer you''re looking for, and their taps will fill your glasses with the likes of Noble''s Naughty Sauce, El Segundo''s Mayberry IPA, and Almanac''s Dogpatch Sour.\r\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1526" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach.jpg" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="475" /></a><strong><a href="http://congregationalehouse.com/" target="_blank">Congregation Ale House</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Congregation+Ale+House+Long+Beach+Chapter/@33.769485,-118.190858,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xb940a89d419aaead" target="_blank">201 E Broadway, Long Beach, CA 90802</a></em>\r\n\r\nCongregation''s proximity to Beachwood makes it somewhat of a destination spot, and they do a good job at satisfying your palate with good food and brews. The Long Beach chapter is currently pulling in some solid beers from The Bruery, Russian River, and Stone, including their new Sorry Not Sorry Imperial IPA. Additionally, it''s that time of year that Goose Island''s Bourbon County Brand Stout hits the market and you''ll be happy to know that Congregation pours some variations of that as well.\r\n<h3></h3>\r\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach2.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1527" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach2.jpg" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="525" /></a><strong><a href="https://www.cohnrestaurants.com/bobeaukitchenrooftap" target="_blank">BO-beau kitchen + roof tap</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/BO-beau+kitchen+%2B+roof+tap/@33.7689721,-118.1920242,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x7a58fc3d003628da?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi7pOjQ66TJAhXNKogKHVgRAlQQ_BIIgwEwDQ" target="_blank">144 Pine Ave, Long Beach, CA 90802</a></em>\r\n\r\nBo-beau is a cool French spot that is a pretty ideal for a date and satisfies your food, spirit, and beer appetite very well. They even have an impressive rooftop lounge for good measure. But, hey, you want to know about the beers on tap, so let''s talk about that. They aren''t bringing in anything to write home about, but we figure the hop heads will be fine with pounding down a few Kook DIPA''s from Pizza Port or Saint Archer''s Hop Hash (which I dig).\r\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach3.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1528" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach3.jpg" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="524" /></a></h2>\r\n<h3><strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/TheFactoryLB/" target="_blank">The Factory Gastrobar</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Factory+Gastrobar/@33.8309301,-118.1847608,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x6cc9de083448858c?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwibq97D7KTJAhVULIgKHbITB8YQ_BIIfDAK" target="_blank">4020 Atlantic Ave, Long Beach, CA 90807</a></em>\r\n\r\nThe Factory should be on anyone''s craft beer list as a mellow, comfortable spot to grab a nice brew and enjoy some great food in peace. Some recent Untappd check-ins show they are bringing in some local brews like Artifex''s No Name IPA and Smog City''s Hoptonic, but they''re also paying attention to solid offerings such as Lagunita''s Born Yesterday Pale Ale.\r\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1529" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach.png" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="459" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.simmzys.com/" target="_blank">Simmzy''s Pub</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Simmzy''s/@33.7597865,-118.1332699,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xbedbe6d08597ee83?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjn6abV7qTJAhUE6mMKHVEgCOMQ_BIIgwEwCg" target="_blank">5271 E 2nd St, Long Beach, CA 90803</a></em>\r\n\r\nSimmzy''s is another one that seems obvious, especially since their Burbank location showed up on our <a href="http://hoppedla.com/best-beer-bars-san-fernando-valley-east/" target="_blank">SFV East guide</a>. Simmzy''s has a great spot in the Belmont Shores area of Long Beach, and incorporates a friendly vibe with its open layout and communal table set up. So, grab a chair and order beers such as Surf Brewery''s South Swell DIPA, Bootlegger''s Far Out IPA, and Tape Deck from Monkish.\r\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-22-at-12.37.04-PM.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1530" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-22-at-12.37.04-PM.png" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="845" /></a></h2>\r\n<h3><strong><a href="http://www.wbr3.com/" target="_blank">Weiland Brewery Restaurant</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=weiland+brewery+restaurant+long+beach+beer&amp;biw=1308&amp;bih=662&amp;source=lnms&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi81tKx8KTJAhXXLYgKHSW5D9gQ_AUIBSgA&amp;dpr=1.1#q=weiland+brewery+restaurant+long+beach+beer&amp;rflfq=1&amp;tbm=lcl&amp;rlfi=hd:;si:9921304387259841235" target="_blank">4354 Atlantic Ave, Long Beach, CA 90807</a></em>\r\n\r\nYou may have heard of Weiland Brewery Underground in Downtown LA, and this location happens to be one of their restaurant locations. From what we hear, the food is good and the beer won''t leave you overly disappointed. They are pouring some of your expected breweries like Lagunitas, Stone, and Dogfish Head, but it''s nice to try some of their own brews as well. The Weiland IPA is middle of the road, but still solid enough to pair with your burger.\r\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach4.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1531" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach4.jpg" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="465" /></a><strong><a href="http://longbeach.theblinddonkey.com/" target="_blank">The Blind Donkey</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Blind+Donkey/@33.7690903,-118.1865869,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x2930a68ded61e382?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwif1YPc8aTJAhUT4GMKHbG1A-QQ_BIIdDAK" target="_blank">149 Linden Ave, Long Beach, CA 90802</a></em>\r\n\r\nThe Blind Donkey''s Long Beach location deserves some love as well, and not only because the <a href="http://hoppedla.com/pasadena-beer-bars/" target="_blank">Pasadena location landed on another guide of ours</a>. Good ol'' Ryan Sweeney is still pulling in some amazing beers into the Goat Group spots, and while The Blind Donkey doesn''t deem itself a "craft beer bar", the taps of Alpine''s Pure Hoppiness, Beachwood''s Brews Dickinson, and Firestone Walker''s Agrestic tell you differently.\r\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-22-at-12.45.41-PM.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1532" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/Screen-Shot-2015-11-22-at-12.45.41-PM.png" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="918" height="511" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.quinnslongbeach.com/" target="_blank">Quinn''s Pub &amp; Grill</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Quinn''s+Pub+%26+Grill/@33.7606855,-118.1349067,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xabe28d3b0cc606d2?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi1pI2v86TJAhUE1WMKHetNDuMQ_BIIeTAK" target="_blank">200 Nieto Ave, Long Beach, CA 90803</a></em>\r\n\r\nI have to admit that I almost overlooked Quinn''s due to their Irish pub label, but I would''ve been sorely mistaken. Grab a seat at the bar and get a pour of great beers from Stone''s Enjoy By series and Bear Republic''s Hop Shovel to SanTan''s Mr. Pineapple and Victory''s Hop Ticket Black IPA.\r\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach5.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1533" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach5.jpg" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="497" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.pikelongbeach.com/" target="_blank">Pike Restaurant &amp; Bar</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=the+pike+long+beach&amp;oq=the+pike+long+beach&amp;aqs=chrome.0.0l6.2231j0j4&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;es_sm=91&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=the+pike+long+beach&amp;rflfq=1&amp;rlha=0&amp;tbm=lcl&amp;rlfi=hd:;si:1897313298033636590" target="_blank">1836 E 4th St, Long Beach, CA 90802</a></em>\r\n\r\nThis guide is in no way ordered by how great the venue is, but Pike would be towards the bottom nonetheless. It''s simply a place that you can grab a craft beer, whether it''s a Stone IPA or a Ballast Point Sculpin. The fish tacos are fantastic, so it wouldn''t be the worst thing in the world to pair one of those IPAs up.\r\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach6.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1534" style="border: 2px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/craft-beer-long-beach6.jpg" alt="craft-beer-long-beach" width="700" height="479" /></a></h2>\r\n<h3><strong><a href="http://letsdobrix.com/" target="_blank">Brix at the Shore</a></strong></h3>\r\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Brix+at+the+Shore/@33.7583919,-118.1309993,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xfb49aa4495daa184?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjixtPc9KTJAhUX92MKHcTWAeQQ_BIIggEwCg" target="_blank">5372 E 2nd St, Long Beach, CA 90803</a></em>\r\n\r\nBrix at the Shore is our final spot on the list and claims to deliver a "New York Experience" presumably because of the deli sandwiches. But there is nothing New York about the beer with some tasty options from your favorite west coast breweries. So, savor a thick pastrami sandwich and wash it down with beers from Smog City, Barley Forge, and Acoustic Ales.\r\n\r\nWith a number of new places opening up all over Los Angeles, there''s a good chance that I missed one that belongs on this list. If so, let me know in the comments below. Additionally, if you want to chat about the Long Beach craft beer scene,  also drop us a line below or hit us up on Twitter at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. Cheers!\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Your Guide to the Best Craft Beer Spots in Long Beach', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'your-guide-to-the-best-beer-bars-in-long-beach', '', '', '2016-03-08 12:14:44', '2016-03-08 20:14:44', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1522', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1546, 4, '2015-11-22 20:51:49', '2015-11-23 04:51:49', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1558" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/thanksgiving-ipas.jpg" alt="Thanksgiving IPAs in LA" width="1200" height="628" />\nThanksgiving dinner is the perfect occasion for drinking and pairing lots of various styles of beer. From light and spicy saisons, to caramelly clean amber ales, to rich and roasty stouts, they all have their places throughout the traditional Thanksgiving festivities.\n\nAs a devoted hop head, sometimes you can''t help but keep on cracking open those session, single, double, Belgian, black, or red IPAs, especially given the amazing selection we have access to here in LA. Here are 9 awesome IPAs you can pick up around LA right now to celebrate your Thanksgiving holiday the right way. The hoppy way.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1551 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/celebration-e1448246679386.jpg" alt="Sierra Nevada Celebration" width="600" height="604" />\n<strong>Sierra Nevada Brewing Company - Celebration Fresh Hop IPA</strong></h2>\nThis fresh hop IPA is a classic holiday beer from the always awesome Sierra Nevada, and is one of the few hop-forward holiday beers out there. Aided by the solid lineup of C-hops, this American style IPA has a nice piney-citrus bitterness with just enough malty sweetness for balance.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1552 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/alpine-brews-e1448247063162.jpg" alt="Alpine Duet, Hoppy Birthday, Nelson, Pure Hoppiness" width="600" height="600" /></h2>\n<span style="font-size: 10px;">(Image credit: <a href="https://instagram.com/mrksliquor/" target="_blank">@mrksliquor</a>)</span>\n<h2><strong>Alpine Beer Company - Hoppy Birthday, Duet, Nelson &amp; Pure Hoppiness</strong></h2>\nIn the past, we''ve seen Alpine''s coveted hoppy brews up in LA from time to time, but in the past couple weeks it seems we''ve seen the widest distribution yet since Green Flash purchased the East San Diego County brewery.\n\nYou really can''t go wrong with any of these beers. Hoppy Birthday is the lowest ABV of the group at just over 5% but doesn''t hold back on the intense citrus flavors. Duet doesn''t disappoint at 7% with tastes of rich citrus and piney resin. Nelson is a 7% golden rye IPA that is a Nelson Sauvin lovers dream. Then there''s the 8% Double IPA, Pure Hoppiness, bursting with flavors of pineapple grapefruit with a lot of dry bitterness.\n\nHoppy Birthday, Duet, and Nelson all come in 22oz bombers, while Pure Hoppiness comes in a 12oz six pack priced at a whopping $20. Trust me, the high price tag is worth it.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1553 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/noble-i-love-it-e1448248315479.jpg" alt="Noble Ale Works - I Love It" width="600" height="600" />\n<strong>Noble Ale Works - I Love It! California IPA</strong></h2>\nWe''ve written about I Love It a lot on this site. And there''s a great reason for that. Noble Ale Works'' 2014 LA IPA Fest winner is just a damn good IPA. Actually it''s better than damn good. What would you call that? Fucking amazing? That works for me. It''s intensely tropical on the aroma and taste, has a hint of sweetness, and is so well balanced. Grab it, you won''t be disappointed.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1554 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/greenshift-e1448248599826.jpg" alt="Beachwood Brewing - Greenshift Double IPA" width="600" height="600" />\n<strong>Beachwood BBQ &amp; Brewing - Greenshift IPA</strong></h2>\nWhen Beachwood releases an IPA, you get it. No questions asked. This one is a big 10% Double IPA with a major citrus component, malty sweetness, and some astringency from the alcohol. You won''t want to start your day with this one, but when you''ve warmed up with a couple of the beers above, this one will go down really nicely.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1555 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/blood-junkie-e1448248988817.jpg" alt="Three Weavers - Blood Junkie" width="600" height="600" />\n<strong>Three Weavers Brewing Company - Blood Junkie Imperial Red Ale</strong></h2>\nBrand new and bottled just days ago, Three Weavers'' Blood Junkie is the freshest beer on this list. It''s also the only Imperial Red Ale, which means it''s a hefty 8.7% that has a smooth caramelly sweetness that is completely offset by huge bitter citrus flavors made possible by the double dry hop combo of Mosaic, Simcoe, Summit &amp; HBC 342. It pours a dark blood red and is a great hoppy brew for the Fall season. Swing by their tasting room to pick up some bottles with the sick custom artwork or a fill up one of Three Weavers'' branded growlers.\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-1556 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/broken-skull-e1448249233255.jpg" alt="El Segundo - Broken Skull" width="600" height="600" /><span style="font-size: 10px;">(Image credit: <a href="https://www.instagram.com/threebzine_podcast/" target="_blank">@threebzine_podcast</a>)</span>\n<h2><strong>El Segundo Brewing Company - Broken Skull IPA</strong></h2>\nEl Segundo''s newest IPA made in collaboration with none other than Stone Cold Steve Austin is a super dry classic 6.7% IPA with sticky and resiny flavors from the Cascade and Chinook hops complemented by bright citrus and tropical flavors from the Citra hops. This is a highly drinkable IPA that you''ll be able to drink all day and even share with friends and family members that aren''t quite the hop head that you are.\n\nLook out for all these beers are your neighborhood bottle shop. We recommend places like Valley Beverage Company in Sherman Oaks, Green Jug Liquor in West Hills, the Toluca Lake, Beverly Hills, Studio City, and Fullerton outposts of Vendome Wine &amp; Spirits, The Heights Deli in Lincoln Heights, Select Beer Store in Redondo Beach, Southland Beer in Koreatown, Sunset Beer Co in Echo Park, the Boyle Heights and Pico Rivera outposts of Ramirez Liquor, Craft Beer Cellar in Eagle Rock, and Stearns Liquor in Long Beach. There are a ton more options, so if you need a bottle shop recommendation, <a href="http://twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">hit us up on Twitter</a> and we''ll steer you in the right direction!', '9 Awesome IPAs to Celebrate Thanksgiving in LA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'thanksgiving-ipas', '', '', '2015-11-22 20:51:49', '2015-11-23 04:51:49', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1546', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1583, 4, '2015-11-29 20:59:00', '2015-11-30 04:59:00', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can''t go to all of them, doesn''t mean you can''t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we''ve found for the week of Monday November 30th to Sunday December 6th, 2015.\n\nKnow of an event that''s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we''ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday December 1</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Avery Brewing Night at Tustin Brewing Co</strong>\n<em>Tustin, 6:30pm</em></h3>\nBarrel Aged Beer month at Tustin Brewing is kicking off with a bang featuring a bunch of barrel aged brews from Avery Brewing Company. In bottles will be The Beast, Fortuna, Raspberry Sour, Rufus Corvus, Rumpkin, Samael’s, Tectum et Elix, Uncle Jacob’s Stout &amp; 5 Monks. They’ll also be pouring Rumpkin, Pumpkyn, Samael’s, and Uncle Jacob’s Stout on draft, doing some raffles for prizes, featuring some food specials and beer pairings from the Tustin Brewing crew, and doing cigar pairing out on the patio.\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony’s featuring MacLeod Ale at Tony’s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nTuesdays at Tony’s is back again featuring the delicious cask conditioned ales from MacLeod Ale Brewing Co. We haven’t seen a tap list yet, but we’ll update this as soon as we see it.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday December 2</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Nineteen &amp; Twenty at Library Alehouse</strong>\n<em>Santa Monica, 6pm</em></h3>\nSanta Monica’s best beer spot, Library Alehouse, is celebrating its TWENTIETH anniversary by celebrating Firestone Walker’s NINETEENTH anniversary. They’ll be pouring some awesome FW beers including XIX Anniversary, XVIII Anniversary, Walker’s Cuvee, Sour Opal, Bretta Weisse, Agrestic, Velvet Merkin, Sucaba, Parabola, Stickee Monkee, Helldorado, Union Jack, DBA, and Pivo Pils. Even David Walker himself will be showing up for the festivities. They’re also holding a charity raffle where if you bring in canned food, you could have the chance to win some serious bottles from the Alehouse Cellar.\n<h3><strong>Epic Brewing Steal the Glass Night at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nEureka Tasting Kitchen in Hawthorne is back again with their Steal the Glass night. This week features the awesome Big Bad Baptist Barrel Aged Imperial Stout from Epic Brewing.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday December 3</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Beer &amp; Cheese Pairing w/ Vagabond Cheese at Smog City Brewing</strong>\n<em>Torrance, 4pm</em></h3>\nSmog City and Vagabond Cheese have combined their awesomeness and put together two opportunities for you to pair Smog City’s delicious beer with Vagabond’s tasty small batch cheeses. The pairings include Mulberry Saison with Twig Farm Mixed Drum, Weird Beer with Tomme de Savoie, OE paired with Hook’s 10 year Cheddar, and OE Bourbon with Bayley Hazen Blue. <a href="http://hppd.la/1POKYZC" target="_blank">Grab your tickets online now</a> for this session or the Saturday session for $18 because this event might sell out and tickets at the door are $22.\n<h3><strong>Holiday Celebration at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nDuring the Riviera Village Holiday Stroll, Select Beer Store will be featuring some special holiday beers and will have a surprise guest…who could it be?? They’ll also have Asian BBQ Fusion from food truck Barley Hops Grill. This is a great time to pick up some bottles for holiday gifts, sip on some holiday ales, and get in the holiday spirit!\n<h3><strong>Christmas Beer Festival at Naja''s Place</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 6pm</em></h3>\nNaja’s Place is holding their annual Christmas Beer Festival. Dress up in your ugly Christmas sweater/Christmas PJ’s and enjoy $1 off your beer. And if you know anything about Naja’s Place, you know that beer selection is going to be awesome.\n<h3><strong>Eagle Rock Brewery Appreciation Night at The Glendale Tap</strong>\n<em>Glendale, 8pm</em></h3>\nThe awesome craft beer bar in Glendale, The Glendale Tap, is giving thanks to the LA brewery pioneers, Eagle Rock Brewery this Thursday night. The Eagle Rock crew will be in the house and some awesome beers will be pouring from the taps, like Deuce, their 2nd Anniversary Strong Ale, Stimulus, their Belgian-style Amber with Intelligentsia Coffee, and a bunch of their delicious core lineup. Come pay your respects to one of the OG breweries in LA that helped pave the way to the explosion happening today.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday December 4</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Alpine Kraft Bierfest 2015 at Alpine Village</strong>\n<em>Torrance, 8pm</em></h3>\nAlpine Restaurant’s fourth annual Kraft Bierfest is taking place over Friday and Saturday and will feature more than 40 craft breweries and over 100 craft beers. They’ll also be serving German-inspired food to go along with your beer. Tickets are $45 and you can buy them here: <a href="http://hppd.la/21nTdjn" target="_blank">http://hppd.la/21nTdjn</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday December 5</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Alpine Kraft Bierfest 2015</strong>\n<em>Torrance, 11am</em></h3>\nDay 2 of the Alpine Kraft Bierfest - see the details above and get your tickets here: <a href="http://hppd.la/21nTdjn" target="_blank">http://hppd.la/21nTdjn</a>\n<h3><strong>Southland Beer Grand Opening</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 12pm</em></h3>\nOne of our favorite new LA beer spots is having their official grand opening party and featuring some fantastic beers like Smog City’s The Nothing, Monkish’s Haiku de Saison, Barley Forge’s Fogue State, El Segundo’s Mayberry on cask with passionfruit, Noble’s Gosebusterqs with Magnolia Tea, Three Weavers’ Southbounder on nitro, plus a bunch more. Fill R Up Gastro Garage will be serving up their unique food menu and since Southland is also a bottle shop, you can pick up some holiday gift brews to-go!\n<h3><strong>San Diego Ho Ho at The Doughroom</strong>\n<em>Palms, 12pm</em></h3>\nThe Doughroom is celebrating the holidays by featuring some great San Diego brews, some of which don’t ever get to make their way up to LA often, if at all. Featured breweries include Toolbox, Rip Current, 32 North, Kilowatt, Modern Times, Pizza Port, and more. <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/san-diegho-ho-ho-tickets-19626157365" target="_blank">Tickets are $30</a> and include eight 5oz pours and a pizza of your choice (VIP tickets are $40, get one hour early access and ten pours). If you don''t make it down to San Diego too often, you''re gonna wanna jump on this one!\n<h3><strong>Lucky Luke Brewing Company Grand Opening</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 12pm</em></h3>\nLucky Luke, a brand new brewery out in Lancaster, is celebrating their official grand opening with a ribbon cutting ceremony starting at noon, raffles every hour, live music, food trucks, and of course their beers, which include The Squire Belgian Blonde, The Millwright Oatmeal Stout, The Idleman Session Amber, The Scrivener American Blonde, and more. Another welcome addition to the Lancaster beer scene.\n<h3><strong>Brewyard Beer Company Grand Opening</strong>\n<em>Glendale, 1pm</em></h3>\nOne of LA’s newest breweries is celebrating their grand opening celebration with a ribbon cutting ceremony, some food, live music, and of course craft beers. The taproom opens at 1pm, the ribbon cutting is at 4pm, Slammin’ Sliders will be serving up little burgers, and A Flavor of Love will be performing their R&amp;B folk tunes.\n<h3><strong>Beer &amp; Cheese Pairing w/ Vagabond Cheese at Smog City Brewing</strong>\n<em>Torrance, 3pm</em></h3>\nSession 2 of the Beer and Cheese pairing event with Vagabond Cheese. See above for the details and go ahead and <a href="http://hppd.la/1MRtHsQ" target="_blank">buy your tickets now</a> before they sell out. This is gonna be a good one!\n<h3><strong>Prohibition Repeal Day Speakeasy at Angel City</strong>\n<em>DTLA Arts District, 8pm</em></h3>\nCelebrate the 82nd anniversary of the end of “The Noble Experiment” at Angel City Brewery. They’re throwing a prohibition party in their upstairs loft space with a flight bar featuring limited release barrel aged brews and a complimentary toast brews. Prohibition-era clothing is highly encouraged and you’ll need to pay attention to their social media channels to pick up on the secret password that is necessary to get access to the speakeasy.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday December 6</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>6th Annual Christmas Beer Brunch with The Bruery at The Bottle Room</strong>\n<em>Whittier, 10am</em></h3>\nThe Bottle Room in Whittier is back with their 6th annual Christmas Beer Brunch featuring The Bruery and their amazing beers like Chocolate Rain, Melange #3, White Oak, 8 Maids-a-Milking, Bourbon Barrel Aged 6 Geese-a-Laying, Cinnamonk, Confession, Oude Tart, and more. Doors open at 10am and will be going til 3pm.\n<h3><strong>Krampus Xmas Beer Fest at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 5pm</em></h3>\nPhantom Carriage is kicking off the holiday season with an nod to the anti-Santa demon, Krampus. They’re tapping 30 holiday winter ales including Belgians, Barleywines, Stouts, Sours, mulled wine, mulled cider, and festive treats from their cafe. And if you’ve ever wanted to see a weird Christmas horror film, they’ll be showing them in their mini theater. Tasting packages will include 3, 6 &amp; 9 beer samples of your choice, no tickets necessary.', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Nov 30, 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-nov-30', '', '', '2015-11-29 20:59:00', '2015-11-30 04:59:00', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1583', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1605, 4, '2015-12-06 21:52:17', '2015-12-07 05:52:17', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can''t go to all of them, doesn''t mean you can''t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we''ve found for the week of Monday December 7th to Sunday December 13th, 2015.\n\nKnow of an event that''s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we''ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday December 8</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Figueroa Mountain Tap Takeover at Daryl’s Couch</strong>\n<em>Camarillo, 4pm</em></h3>\nJoin the Daryl''s Couch crew in welcoming Figueroa Mountain Brewing to the neighborhood with a special tap takeover event featuring their Danish Red Lager, Davy Brown Ale, Hoppy Poppy IPA, Lizards Mouth IIPA, Zero to Sexy Golden Mocha Coffee Ale, and their 5th Anniversary Rum Barrel Aged Dopplebock. Some of the team from Fig Mountain will be on hand to talk about the beers and share some brewery swag.\n<h3><strong>Bottle Flight Night Featuring Paradox Brewing Co at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nSelect Beer Store is back with a bottle flight night featuring Paradox Brewing Company''s barrel aged wild ales from Divide, CO. The flight features pours of Paradox''s Skully Barrel No. 18, 25, and 26.\n<h3><strong>Bell''s Brewing Night at The Federal</strong>\n<em>North Hollywood, 6pm</em></h3>\nThe Federal is featuring the awesome beers of Bell''s Brewing on Tuesday night, including their Amber Ale, Two Hearted Ale, Hell Hath No Fury, Winter White Ale, Christmas Ale, Expedition Stout, Le Contrebassiste, 30th Anniversary Ale, Traverse City Whiskey Barrel-Aged Porter, and Bourbon Barrel-Aged Maillards Oddysey.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday December 9</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>38 Degrees Ale House &amp; Grill Monrovia Grand Opening</strong>\n<em>Monrovia, 4pm</em></h3>\nThe wait is over! 38 Degrees is opening up their long-awaited 2nd location in Monrovia on Wednesday at 4pm. We don''t have much details, but you can expect more of what they''ve been serving up at their Alhambra location: awesome craft beers, delicious pub food, and a great comfortable bar atmosphere to enjoy them in. A welcome addition to the Monrovia area! Head on out and bring your friends.\n<h3><strong>Bravery Brewing Tap Night at Kinetic Brewing</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 4pm</em></h3>\nKinetic Brewing Company will be getting real local and featuring the brews of fellow Lancaster brewery, Bravery Brewing at their pub. They''ll be pouring Bravery''s Slowhand Cream Ale, Grapefruit Allegiance IPA, Mocharova Mocha Sweet Stout, Buster''s Brown, Old Rat, and Bourbon Barrel Aged Gunny''s Choice Quad Ale.\n<h3><strong>Anchor Christmas Ale Steal the Glass at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nEureka is back with their Steal the Glass night featuring the holiday seasonal brew, Christmas Ale, from Anchor Brewing.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday December 10</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Mission Brewing Tap Takeover at Overland Cafe</strong>\n<em>Palms, 5pm</em></h3>\nThe Overland Cafe is doing a tap takeover with Mission Brewing, including their Holiday Ale, Cortez Belgian Style Blonde, Shipwrecked Double IPA, and Carrack Imperial Red. They will also be featuring some special food and beer pairings.\n<h2><span style="color: #ec4731;"><strong>PICK OF THE WEEK:</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Holiday Party w/ Monkish, Highland Park &amp; Societe at Sunset Beer</strong>\n<em>Echo Park, 6pm</em></h3>\nTwo of LA''s best breweries, Monkish and Highland Park, have teamed up and invited Societe Brewing from San Diego to form an epic holiday party at Sunset Beer Co. Monkish and Highland Park''s beers are already top notch and add to that a lineup of Societe beers and rarely make their way up to LA and you''ve got a can''t miss event. Throw on that ugly Christmas sweater and head out there!\n<h3><strong>Karl Strauss Takeover &amp; Pairing at Don Chente</strong>\n<em>Huntington Park, 6pm</em></h3>\nGet Karl Strauss'' Columbia Street Amber, Wreck Alley Imperial Stout, and Mosaic Session Ale paired with three Mexican food dishes from Don Chente at this tap takeover event in Huntington Park.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday December 11</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Figueroa Mountain Westlake Village Taproom Grand Opening</strong>\n<em>Westlake Village, 11am</em></h3>\nFigueroa Mountain''s long-awaited taproom in Westlake Village is finally opening up this week and we couldn''t be happier. From the photos we''ve seen so far, it look like a really cool spot and will make a welcome addition to the row of craft beer spots along the 101 in Conejo Valley leading into Ventura County.\n<h3><strong>The Pine Tar Incident Day One Release at El Segundo Brewing</strong>\n<em>El Segundo, 12pm</em></h3>\nEl Segundo has a new beer releasing as part of their Day One program and it sounds awesome. Pine Tar Incident is a Black IPA with pine and spruce aromas and bitter cocoa and candied orange flavors and won a gold medal earlier this year at the San Diego International Beer Fest. Head on over to the brewery at noon for your first crack at the beer and reserve yourself a case if you''re so inclined.\n<h3><strong>Christmas with Karl at Melody Lounge</strong>\n<em>Chinatown, 6:30pm</em></h3>\nKarl Strauss is taking over Melody Lounge for a special holiday party with some delicious and rare-in-these-parts beers paired with desserts. On tap will be Columbia Street Amber, Mosaic Session Ale, Wreck Alley Imperial Stout, Peanut Butter Cup Porter, Six Suits-a-Hangin'' Imperial Brown Holiday Ale, and Control Point Raspberry Sour. Show up with a toy to donate and you''ll get the desserts for free!\n<h3><strong>Bagby Beer Tap Takeover at Blue Palms</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 7pm</em></h3>\nJeff Bagby is bringing up a bunch of his beers from Bagby Brewing in Oceanside to Blue Palms in Hollywood. And you know when Blue Palms does a tap takeover, they don''t joke around! On tap will be Farm''s for Sale Belgian Farmhouse Ale, Reconnoiter Hoppy Porter, ALT in the Family German-style Altbier, Back Garden English Pale Ale, Absolutely! American Amber Ale, Continental Cream Ale, Hop Crop 100% Wet Hopped Pale Ale, Worker Bee Golden Ale with Honey, Abockalypse German style Weizenbock, Hop Crop Extra Pale Ale on Nitro, Rye Not? Rye Pale Ale, On a Dubbel Belgian style Dubbel, Weissenhopper Hoppy German Weiss Beer, and Stout Your Engines American Stout.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday December 12</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Pocock Brewing Co. Grand Opening Celebration</strong>\n<em>Santa Clarita, 12pm</em></h3>\nOne of the LA area''s newest breweries is celebrating their grand opening on Saturday with new beers, food trucks, live music, raffles and more. Pocock is a welcome addition to Santa Clarita, so head on our and celebrate their opening. It''s all ages, so feel free to bring the whole family!\n<h3><strong>Propogation Series Bottle Release at Beachwood Blendery</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 2pm</em></h3>\nBeachwood''s Blendery is releasing the next four beers in their Propogation series, including 004 Berliner Rye, 008 Spelt Saison dry hopped w/ Hallertau Blanc, 016 Barrel-aged Saison, and 032 Barrel-aged Saison w/ Pluots. They''ll also be pouring beers on draft in their tasting room Saturday and Sunday. If you''re a fan of Beachwood''s brewery offering, you''re gonna want to get your hands on their Blendery bottles.\n<h3><strong>Craft Beer Cellar Eagle Rock Grand Opening Party</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 4pm</em></h3>\nA brand new bottle shop and tasting room in Eagle Rock is now open, pouring great brews from its taps and selling a huge variety of bottles to-go. To celebrate, they''re offering 10% off all bottles during the celebration, some special releases, merch and gift card giveaways, live music, and food. Head on down there and check them out.\n<h3><strong>Firestone Walker Tap Takeover at Public Beer Wine Shop</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nLong Beach''s best bottle shop and tasting room is having Firestone Walker take over their taps with favorites like Pivo Pils, Easy Jack, Wookey Jack, Unfiltered DBA, and Velvet Merkin 2015. They''ll also have live music starting at 8pm. Good beer, live music, sounds like a good way to spend a Saturday in Long Beach.\n<h3><strong>Dry River Brewing Night at Melody Lounge</strong>\n<em>Chinatown, 5pm</em></h3>\nJoin Boyle Heights'' only brewery, Dry River Brewing, for a night at Melody Lounge in Chinatown. They''ll be hanging out and pouring four of their beers Saturday night, so head on out and check out what they''re up to.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday December 13</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>El Segundo Main St Parade with Standard Crude &amp; Donuts at El Segundo Brewing</strong>\n<em>El Segundo, 11am</em></h3>\nThe annual Christmas Parade is heading down Main St in El Segundo and El Segundo Brewing Co is throwing a little shindig and releasing a new beer. And surprise, this one''s actually NOT an IPA! They''re releasing their 4th batch of Standard Crude Imperial Stout and also serving up a Barrel Aged version. They''ll also have donuts and will be offering $1 off beers to anyone wearing an Ugly Christmas Sweater.', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Dec 7, 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-dec-7', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1605', 0, 'post', '', 0);
