(1630, 4, '2015-12-14 00:02:28', '2015-12-14 08:02:28', 'The last couple of months saw a influx of brewery, bottle shop, and tasting room openings that have changed the way we experience craft beer in Los Angeles. As we move into winter, there is still a lot on the opening slate to be excited. Let''s round up the best craft beer spots that have opened in LA in Fall 2015.\n<h1>New Breweries</h1>\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/san-fernando-brewing.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1633" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/san-fernando-brewing.jpg" alt="san-fernando-brewing" width="700" height="394" /></a><a href="http://www.sanfernandobrewingcompany.com/#san-fernando-brewing-co" target="_blank">San Fernando Brewing Co.</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/San+Fernando+Brewing+Company/@34.2833695,-118.4320611,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xb1dcdf89db38dc9e?sa=X&amp;sqi=2&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi9q4CD09nJAhUUU2MKHXLvBa8Q_BIIdTAK" target="_blank">425 Park Ave, San Fernando, CA 91340</a></em>\n\nThe Valley welcomed another addition to the list of new breweries and San Fernando Brewing Co. is doing it right. With five core beers, upcoming seasonal offerings, and an open taproom that overlooks the brewing operation, you feel like a part of the action while sipping some great beer.\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/five-threads-brewing.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1635" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/five-threads-brewing.jpg" alt="five-threads-brewing" width="700" height="467" /></a><a href="http://www.fivethreadsbrewing.com/start/" target="_blank">Five Threads Brewing Co.</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Five+Threads+Brewing+Company/@34.1540161,-118.803611,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xb3374196292f3553?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwj2p-Gh1NnJAhUD42MKHUURAiEQ_BIIbjAK" target="_blank">31133 Via Colinas #109, Westlake Village, CA 91362</a></em>\n\nThe Conejo Valley now has more serious options for craft beer. Five Threads opened up at the end of October and has been adding new beers to the list. Growler fills encouraged!\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/fig-mountain-westlake-village.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1636" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/fig-mountain-westlake-village.jpg" alt="fig-mountain-westlake-village" width="700" height="394" /></a><a href="http://www.figmtnbrew.com/westlakevillage/" target="_blank">Figueroa Mountain Brewing Co. Westlake Village</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Shoppes+at+Westlake+Village/@34.1474615,-118.7960641,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x80e8246c00331bd9:0x8d90f0f9b4982f5a" target="_blank">30770 Russell Ranch Rd, Westlake Village, CA 91362</a></em>\n\nAfter many months of waiting, Fig Mountain''s Westlake Village location has finally opened and it looks spectacular. Sit amongst the brand new stainless steel tanks and take in the menu from the kitchen. When it''s time, enjoy the Fig Mountain brews you love like Hoppy Poppy IPA and Lizard''s Mouth Imperial IPA.\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/pocock-brewing.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1637" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/pocock-brewing.jpg" alt="pocock-brewing" width="700" height="525" /></a><a href="http://pocockbrewing.com/" target="_blank">Pocock Brewing Co.</a></h2>\n<div class="mod" data-md="1002" data-ved="0ahUKEwi35duc0NrJAhVU3GMKHSFADlsQkCkIhAEoBDAO">\n<div class="_eFb">\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwi35duc0NrJAhVU3GMKHSFADlsQghwIhQEoADAO"><em><span class="_Xbe"><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Pocock+Brewing+Company/@34.433556,-118.568683,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x69180aea96027790?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi35duc0NrJAhVU3GMKHSFADlsQ_BIIeDAK" target="_blank">24907 Ave Tibbitts Suite B, Santa Clarita, CA 91355</a></span></em></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwi35duc0NrJAhVU3GMKHSFADlsQghwIhQEoADAO"></div>\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwi35duc0NrJAhVU3GMKHSFADlsQghwIhQEoADAO">\n\nThe people of Santa Clarita are rejoicing that another brewery has joined the neighborhood and it shows that the excitement around beer extends even further north of LA proper. Pocock is brand spankin'' new with their grand opening celebration that just happened Saturday, December 12, and we can''t wait to see what the future holds.\n\n</div>\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwi35duc0NrJAhVU3GMKHSFADlsQghwIhQEoADAO"></div>\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwi35duc0NrJAhVU3GMKHSFADlsQghwIhQEoADAO"><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/brewyard-brewing.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1638" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/brewyard-brewing.jpg" alt="brewyard-brewing" width="700" height="394" /></a></div>\n<h2 class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwi35duc0NrJAhVU3GMKHSFADlsQghwIhQEoADAO"><a href="http://www.brewyardbeercompany.com/" target="_blank">Brewyard Beer Company</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Brewyard+Beer+Company/@34.167286,-118.292298,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x2508ed95754cf04b?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjZ9Kzo09rJAhVD0WMKHbnbBbUQ_BIIbjAK" target="_blank">906 Western Ave, Glendale, CA 91201</a></em>\n\nBrewyard Beer Co. fills the void between the SFV and the rest of LA with a great variety of styles on tap Wednesday through Sunday each week. The offerings range from their Black Sunrise black lager and Split Shift IPL to the Soul Cal California Common and Tropico Saison w/ passion fruit. So, yeah, you can say there is something for everybody.\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hop-saint-brewing.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1639" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/hop-saint-brewing.jpg" alt="hop-saint-brewing" width="700" height="467" /></a><a href="http://www.hopsaint.com/" target="_blank">HopSaint Brewing Company</a></h2>\n<div id="u_0_30" class="ellipsis _50f3" data-hover="tooltip"><em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/5160+W+190th+St,+Torrance,+CA+90503/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2b4ec9de751c1:0x239c2de6fdc51ada?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwj91fbm2NrJAhVKy2MKHXODCngQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">5160 W 190th St. Torrance, California</a></em></div>\n<div class="ellipsis _50f3" data-hover="tooltip"></div>\n<div class="ellipsis _50f3" data-hover="tooltip">\n\nHopSaint hit the South Bay this year further solidifying that the area is the one of the best craft beer destinations in Los Angeles. They are serving up a few great styles so far like the Cacophony IPA, and will be adding brunch and lunch to their kitchen offerings. HopSaint will be a great place to grab a beer and some food.\n\n</div>\n<div class="ellipsis _50f3" data-hover="tooltip"></div>\n<div class="ellipsis _50f3" data-hover="tooltip"><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/arts-district-brewing.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1640" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/arts-district-brewing.jpg" alt="arts-district-brewing" width="700" height="394" /></a></div>\n<h2 class="ellipsis _50f3" data-hover="tooltip"><a href="http://www.artsdistrictbrewing.com/" target="_blank">Arts District Brewing</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/828+Traction+Ave,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90013/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c63955a852f3:0x64d14e7775e1c81d?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjFxdiR2trJAhVH8mMKHaM4DP0Q8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">828 Traction Ave. Los Angeles, CA 90013</a></em>\n\nAnother big opening in December, Arts District Brewing is the latest project from 213 Hospitality who teamed up with Brian Lenzo of Blue Palms Brewhouse to pump out amazing craft beer in the Arts District. They tapped Pizza Port Solana Beach''s Devon Randall to run brewing operations, which makes this a place to pay attention to.\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1769" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/transplant-brewing.png" alt="transplant-brewing" width="700" height="370" /><a href="http://transplantsbrewing.com/" target="_blank">Transplant Brewing</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Transplants+Brewing+Company/@34.6144077,-118.1396547,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xa7ba31fb06eb7bab" target="_blank">40242 La Quinta Ln Unit 101, Palmdale, CA 93551</a></em>\n\nTransplant Brewing literally just opened to the public in Palmdale, thus, creating a reason to head out in that direction while hitting up some spots along the way. The brewery is focused on hoppy west coast style ales, but have some very intriguing specialties that include a Peep marshmallow stout and cucumber wheat ale.\n<h1>New Bars and Bottle Shops</h1>\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Screen-Shot-2015-12-13-at-11.45.35-PM.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1642" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Screen-Shot-2015-12-13-at-11.45.35-PM.png" alt="southland-beer-co" width="700" height="523" /></a><a href="http://www.southlandbeer.com/" target="_blank">Southland Beer Co. </a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Southland+Beer/@34.0583838,-118.3088809,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xa698aca682e4ea2c?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjOv_e73drJAhVH-GMKHRThAukQ_BIIbzAK" target="_blank">740 S Western Ave #112, Los Angeles, CA 90005</a></em>\n\nHidden in the corner of a nondescript strip mall in Koreatown, Southland Beer Co. makes an impression with its casual vibe and excellent tap list. From Barley Forge''s Patsy to Three Weavers'' First Rodeo, Tim and the Southland team are not playing around when it comes to bringing great beer to the Koreatown neighborhood.\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/craft-beer-cellar-eagle-rock.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1643" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/craft-beer-cellar-eagle-rock.jpg" alt="craft-beer-cellar-eagle-rock" width="700" height="700" /></a><a href="https://craftbeercellar.com/eaglerock/" target="_blank">Craft Beer Cellar Eagle Rock</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Craft+Beer+Cellar/@34.1398799,-118.1946674,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x5122dfdd5697f568?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjarK2N4NrJAhXGKWMKHTOJCYkQ_BIIZjAK" target="_blank">1353 Colorado Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90041</a></em>\n\nNo doubt you''ve heard of Craft Beer Cellar''s other locations (and with one in Torrance opening soon). Eagle Rock has one of their own boasting great attention to the bottle selection, and 8 glorious taps of craft beer.\n<h2><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/block-party.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1644" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/block-party.png" alt="block-party" width="700" height="479" /></a><a href="http://www.blockpartyhp.com/" target="_blank">Block Party</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/5052+York+Blvd,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90042/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c3ffd28cb51d:0xa353897ea6745847?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjdxrz34NrJAhUK12MKHcBICxUQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">5052 York Blvd. Los Angeles, CA 90042</a></em>\n\nBlock Party is a cool bar that serves up icy cool slushy cocktails and a take on a michelada that contains an ice cream bar on top of the beer. It also serves some great beer like Noble''s Shower Series on tap and a cooler full of bottles for you to enjoy on premise.\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/the-bellwether.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1645" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/the-bellwether.jpg" alt="the-bellwether" width="700" height="466" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://thebellwetherla.com/" target="_blank">The Bellwether</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Bellwether/@34.1466478,-118.4215995,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xa2b79ecba01a6597?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiR5pfc4trJAhUBwmMKHZoCAVEQ_BIIdzAK" target="_blank">13251 Ventura Blvd, Studio City, CA 91604</a></em>\n\nThe Fathers Office alum set their sights on Studio City and opened The Bellwether in an attractive location on Ventura Blvd. There''s a strong focus on cocktails here, but there is plenty of beer to keep the enthusiasts satisfied with offerings from Craftsman, Hangar 24, and Three Weavers.\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/bar-bandini.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1646" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/bar-bandini.jpg" alt="bar-bandini" width="700" height="394" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz/bar-bandini-los-angeles-2" target="_blank">Bar Bandini</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Bar+Bandini/@34.0773082,-118.2654713,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xac31a09145a0ed8e?sa=X&amp;sqi=2&amp;ved=0ahUKEwig5PC14trJAhVD0WMKHbnbBbUQ_BIIcjAK" target="_blank">2150 Sunset Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90026</a></em>\n\nBar Bandini is Echo Park''s newest relaxed hang out specializing in funky, natural wines and 12 taps of craft beer that will focus heavily on IPAs, sours, and saisons. The wood-lined walls give the space a cool, rustic feel with sleek bar and table tops to support the small, European-style bites.\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/everson-royce-bar.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1647" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/everson-royce-bar.png" alt="everson-royce-bar" width="700" height="479" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://www.erbla.com/splash" target="_blank">Everson Royce Bar</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/webhp?sourceid=chrome-instant&amp;ion=1&amp;espv=2&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=everson+royce+bar&amp;rflfq=1&amp;tbm=lcl&amp;rlfi=hd:;si:3371906459490486129" target="_blank">1936 E 7th St, Los Angeles, CA 90021</a></em>\n\nERB is a sweet cocktail bar near the south end of the Arts District that also boasts some phenomenal beer from Highland Park, Russian River, Noble Ale Works. You simply cannot discount a cocktail bar that also serves Naughty Sauce.\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/button-mash-la.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1648" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/button-mash-la.jpg" alt="button-mash-la" width="700" height="466" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://buttonmashla.com/" target="_blank">Button Mash</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Button+Mash/@34.0739963,-118.2515224,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x355cc40d877c2234?sa=X&amp;sqi=2&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiB0vCu6NrJAhUI5mMKHWXUDggQ_BIIcTAK" target="_blank">1391 Sunset Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90026</a></em>\n\nButton Mash is another cool bar making Echo Park its home with craft beer and vintage arcade games on the mind. From Modern Times to Firestone, what can be more appealing than sipping on one of your favorite brews while trying to beat your high score.\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/formans-tavern.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1649" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/formans-tavern.jpg" alt="formans-tavern" width="700" height="465" /></a>\n<h2><a href="http://www.formansla.com/" target="_blank">Forman''s Tavern</a></h2>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=the+forman+la&amp;oq=the+forman+la&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57j0l2j69i61l3.1880j0j4&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;es_sm=91&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=the+forman+la&amp;rflfq=1&amp;rlha=0&amp;tbm=lcl&amp;rlfi=hd:;si:1013143609108019037" target="_blank">10149 Riverside Dr, Los Angeles, CA 91602</a></em>\n\nOne more Valley location rounds out the list, and it''s Forman''s Tavern which took the old Lucy''s 51 space in Toluca Lake. Sitting close to Timmy Nolan''s, this area of the east Valley is actually a destination for craft beer. And with taps pouring Smog City, Kinetic, and Modern Times, it''s a good one at that.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'The Best New LA Craft Beer Spots: Fall / Winter 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-best-craft-beer-openings-in-fall-2015', '', '', '2015-12-14 00:02:28', '2015-12-14 08:02:28', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1630', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1658, 4, '2015-12-14 22:06:17', '2015-12-15 06:06:17', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can''t go to all of them, doesn''t mean you can''t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we''ve found for the week of Monday December 14th to Sunday December 20th, 2015.\n\nKnow of an event that''s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we''ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday December 15</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony''s featuring The Bruery</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nTuesdays at Tony''s is back with a special night featuring four beers from The Bruery''s 12 Days of Christmas series. Enjoy 2012''s 5 Golden Rings, 2013''s 6 Geese a Layin, 2014 7 Swans a Swimmin, and 2015''s 8 Maids a Milkin. You can grab an individual snifter for $6.75 or a flight of all four for $20.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday December 16</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Ninkasi Pint Night at Darryl''s Couch</strong>\n<em>Camarillo, 5pm</em></h3>\nNinkasi is gracing the taps at Darryl''s Couch in Camarillo with their 10% Imperial Stout, Ground Control, brewed with Oregon hazelnuts, star anise, cocoa nibs, and a yeast strain that survived a trip to space. Also on tap will be Dawn of The Red, their India Red Ale and Ninkasi reps will be giving out pint glasses and other swag.\n<h3><strong>Steal the Glass Night at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nThis week''s Steal the Glass Night at Eureka is featuring Hellion, a Belgian Style Golden Ale from Ritual Brewing Co in Redlands.\n<h3><strong>Heirloom Grain &amp; Brew Dinner at Maximiliano</strong>\n<em>Highland Park, 6pm</em></h3>\nJoin the Maximiliano crew for an evening of exploration and celebration including delicious food and amazing beer. The dinner starts out with a welcome and bread tasting with Farmer Mai Nguyen and Baker Mark Stambler. Then follow that up with a five course meal and pairing of specially commissioned beers from Craftsman Brewing &amp; Highland Park Brewing. This is a one of a kind experience with some of the best at their craft in beer and food. <a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/e/heirloom-grain-and-brew-dinner-tickets-19568762696" target="_blank">Grab your tickets here</a>.\n<h3><strong>One Night Stand with The Bruery at Beer Belly</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 6pm</em></h3>\nCheck out the last One Night Stand event of the year featuring The Bruery and their awesome beers like 8 Maids a Milkin, Humulus Lager, Jardinier, Prarie Rue, Humulus Terreux, Ukulele, Imperial Cabinet, Souren, Geriatric Hipster Club, Melange #12, Mocha Wednesday, and Sans Pagaie.\n<h3><strong>Festivus at The Glendale Tap</strong>\n<em>Glendale, 8pm</em></h3>\nThe Glendale Tap is back again this year with their Festivus holiday celebration and you''re not going want to miss this one. In addition to the Festivus Pole, Airing of Grievances, Feats of Strength, Festivus Prizes and Miracles, there will be some kick ass beer pouring. On tap will be specialty brews from Almanac, Angel City, Arts District, Ballast Point, Beachwood, Deschutes, Eagle Rock, El Segundo, Firestone, Highland Park, Monkish, Smog City, and Three Weavers. Not too shabby, eh?\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday December 17</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Beachwood 9 Double IPA Release</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 11:30am</em></h3>\nBeachwood is celebrating their 9 year anniversary and they''re back with another deliciously hoppy Double IPA with 9 special hops: Citra, Centennial, Chinook, Mosaic, Equinox, Nelson Sauvin, Galaxy, Warrior, and Comet. The bottles are releasing at both their Long Beach and Seal Beach locations at 11:30am on Thursday. We highly recommend you get your hands on at least one.\n<h3><strong>Grand Opening of The Surly Goat Encino</strong>\n<em>Encino, 4pm</em></h3>\nSay goodbye to Sweeney''s Ale House and hello to The Surly Goat Encino! In a move to focus the experience more on the beer (which is awesome) and less on the food (which is still delicious), The Goat Group''s Encino outpost is rebranding the bar as the 2nd location of the reputable The Surly Goat brand. Come on out to their official grand opening party, which will feature their full food menu, bar games, and a selection of limited and rare beers dug up from the Ryan Sweeney cellar, which you know is bound to impress. Head on out to Encino and welcome The Surly Goat''s new location to the neighborhood.\n<h3><strong>Allagash Bottle Release at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nAllagash is releasing a new beer called James and Julie, which is a Flemish Sour Brown ale with an aroma of raisins, figs, cherries, and caramelized sugar. Select will also be pouring other Allagash beers like Victor, Victoria, Aventureux, Little Brett, and Nancy.\n<h3><strong>5 Year Vertical Anchor Christmas at Surly Goat</strong>\n<em>West Hollywood, 7pm</em></h3>\nSanta is coming early to WeHo this year with a sack full of Anchors! On draft you''ll find Anchor Christmas 2011-2015, Old Foghorn, Bigleaf Maple Autumn Red, Anchor Barrel Ale, and Brotherhood Steam.\n<h3><strong>Silent Night, Deadly Night at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 7pm</em></h3>\nPhantom Carriage is kicking off the Christmas season the only way they know how - with a classic 1985 killer-in-a-Santa-suit slasher horror film called Silent Night, Deadly Night. You''ll also have the opportunity to meet Robert Brian Wilson, who played "Billy" the killer Santa from the film. They''ll also be releasing a new barrel-aged beer and don''t forget to wear your ugly sweater. The best sweater wins a fiendish prize!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday December 18</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Holiday Beer Tasting at Buzz Wine Beer Shop</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nBuzz is throwing together a little holiday beer tasting event featuring some great beers like New Belgium''s Accumilation White IPA, Green Flash Jolly Folly IPA, Saint Bernardus Christmas Ale, IronFire Ginger Dead, Ballast Point Peppermint Victory at Sea, and Prairie Bomb.\n<h3><strong>Anchor Brewing Company Tap Takeover at Eagle Rock Lounge</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 7pm</em></h3>\nAnchor Brewing is taking over the taps at Eagle Rock Lounge and the first 24 people will receive a free Anchor pint glass.\n<h3><strong>A Yuletide Holiday Sing-a-long at Three Weavers</strong>\n<em>Inglewood, 8pm</em></h3>\nThe Three Weavers crew is joining up with some fellow So Cal brewery members from Noble, Eagle Rock, and Monkish and putting together a holiday jam band covering some of your favorite seasonal sing-a-longs. The always amazing Three Weavers brews will be flowing and all it takes to get in is $5 and a can of food which will all be donated to Bread & Roses Cafe in Venice, a really great charity supporting the homeless.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday December 19</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Winter Beer Party at Southland Beer</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 12pm</em></h3>\nSouthland Beer is hosting an all-day winter beer party to celebrate everyone''s favorite holiday beers. They''ll be tapping The Bruery''s 8 Maids a Milkin, Petrus'' Winter, Barley Forge''s Fusty Puckett, and Telegraph''s Winter Ale plus will be waiving the corkage fee on all winter/holiday/pumpkin beers.\n<h3><strong>4th Annual Ugly Sweater Party at Bravery Brewing</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 12pm</em></h3>\nBravery Brewing is hosting its 4th anniversary Ugly Sweater Party and live music, special and limited beers pouring, and an ugly sweater contest at 9pm.\n<h3><strong>Timeless Pints Holiday Party</strong>\n<em>Lakewood, 1pm</em></h3>\nTimeless Pints is throwing their holiday party full of ugly sweaters, live music, amazing food, and of course craft beer. Wear your ugliest holiday sweater and win fun prizes!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday December 20</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Victory at Sea Day at The Federal Bar</strong>\n<em>North Hollywood, 10am</em></h3>\nThe Federal Bar is celebrating Ballast Point''s Victory at Sea Day early with a few awesome variations of the Imperial Porter, including a Nitro version, peppermint, coconut, and peanut butter. Not a bad way to start your Sunday.\n<h3><strong>Victory at Sea Day at Naja''s Place</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 10am</em></h3>\nThe South Bay''s favorite beer bar is jumping in on the Victory at Sea Day fun with four variations of the beer on tap, limited glassware, and food specials.\n<h3><strong>Victory at Sea Day at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 12pm</em></h3>\nIn addition to their house brews, Phantom Carriage will have Ballast Point''s Victory at Sea Imperial Porter along with the peanut butter, coconut, and peppermit variations. Enjoy the beers, pair each with a specialty dessert, and potentially win the special Victory at Sea chalice giveaway.\n<h3><strong>Victory at Sea Day at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 12pm</em></h3>\nSelect Beer Store is celebrating Victory at Sea Day, pouring the original imperial porter with coffee and vanilla, as well as a peanut butter variant and a coconut variant. Head on down there and try them out.\n<h3><strong>Victory at Sea Day at Blue Palms Brewhouse</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 12pm</em></h3>\nBlue Palms is in on the Victory at Sea Day fun with the original Victory at Sea Imperial Porter with coffee & vanilla as well as the peppermint, peanut butter, and coconut variants. They''ll also be pouring Ballast Point Fugu Horchata beer cocktails. Head on down to Hollywood and join the fun.\n<h3><strong>Drink with Santa at Smog City</strong>\n<em>Torrance, 12pm</em></h3>\nSmog City is inviting everyone over to their Torrance brewery to get their photo taken with a craft beer version of Santa, one who is extra jolly and sips on Smog City beers throughout the day. They''ll also be hosting a handful of creative local artists and their creations for your last minute holiday shopping.\n\n&nbsp;', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Dec 14, 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-dec-14', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1658', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1687, 4, '2015-12-20 22:03:55', '2015-12-21 06:03:55', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can''t go to all of them, doesn''t mean you can''t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we''ve found for the week of Monday December 21st to Sunday December 27th, 2015.\n\nKnow of an event that''s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we''ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Monday December 21st</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>National Lampoon’s Christmas Vacation at Kinetic</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 4pm</em></h3>\nPair a classic holiday comedy with craft beer and food at Kinetic on Monday.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday December 22nd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Tuesday Night Flight with Anchorage Brewing at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nSelect Beer Store is gearing up for Christmas with a little visit from Anchorage Brewing. They''ll be pouring Anchorage Brewing Bitter Monk, Between the Staves and Deal with the Devil.\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony’s: Holiday Flight Night at Tony’s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nEnjoy a special holiday version of Tuesdays at Tony''s with a flight of their favorite holiday beers, including Lost Abbey''s Gift of the Magi, Port Brewing''s Santa''s Little Helper (2014), Rubicon Brewing''s Winter Wheat Wine, and Monkish''s Magnificat.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday December 23nd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>First Annual EBC Ugly Sweater Christmas Party at Enegren Brewing</strong>\n<em>Moorpark, 4pm</em></h3>\nEnegren is throwing their first annual Ugly Christmas Sweater party complete with a food truck, live music, a $2 holiday cask, a photobooth picture contest with holiday prizes, and $1 off beers if you''re wearing an ugly Christmas sweater.\n<h3><strong>Craft Beer, Ugly Sweaters &amp; Goodwill to All at Provisions Market</strong>\n<em>Orange, 6pm</em></h3>\nProvisions in downtown Orange is celebrating the holidays with a fun little event combining holiday cheer, some limited beers, food, and a canned good drive. They''re featuring 2 ticket packages:\n\n1. $30 for eight tasters of a selection of draft beers plus a holiday sausage sandwich.\n2. $50 for eight pours from the selection of limited beers from The Bruery plus a holiday sausage sandwich.\n\nThis includes 2013 Tart of Darkness, 2013 Sour in the Rye with Kumquat, 2013 Smoking Wood Rye, 2012 Smoking Wood Smoked Imperial Rye in Bourbon Barrels, Black Tuesday (2013-2015), 2013 Bottleworks XII, 2013 Bois, 2012 Melange #3, 2013 Melange #3, 2013 Saison Tonnellerie, 2013 Sans Pagaie, 2013 5 Golden Rings, 2013 The Wanderer, 2013 Grey Monday, 2013 Windowsill, 2013 Bryeian Batch 1000, 2013 Beauregarde, and some surprise additions\n<h3><strong>Festivus Celebration &amp; Triva at Alosta Brewing Co</strong>\n<em>Covina, 7pm</em></h3>\nHit up Alosta for a special Festivus version of their weekly trivia night. There''s not many details of what is planned, but if you''re into beer and trivia, this should be a good one.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday December 24nd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Christmas Eve Prime Rib Dinner at Kinetic</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 12pm</em></h3>\nKinetic is serving up a special prime rib dinner for Christmas Eve, so if your plans are open for the holiday, craft beer and a nice dinner are a possibility.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday December 26th</strong></span></h2>\n<h2><span style="color: #ec4731;"><strong>PICK OF THE WEEK:</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Tovarish Bottle Release at Beachwood</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 11:30am</em></h3>\nBeachwood''s awesome Russian Imperial Espresso Stout is back again the day after Christmas. Bottles will be available at both locations at 11:30am. for $16 / 22oz. bottle.. They''ll also be pouring a 5 year Tovarish vertical on draft, 5 different cask variations, special menu items and limited edition glassware.\n<h3><strong>Modern Times Day at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 12pm</em></h3>\nHead over to Select Beer Store in Redondo Beach this Saturday for a Modern Times tap takeover featuring some really great beers like Black House Stout on nitro, City of the Sun IPA, Lost Horizons Double IPA, Blazing World hoppy amber, Southern Lands IPA, Monster''s Park Stout with Coffee &amp; Coconut. The event lasts til 8pm so stop by when you can and check them out.', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Dec 21, 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-dec-21', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1687', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1738, 4, '2015-12-27 20:03:30', '2015-12-28 04:03:30', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can''t go to all of them, doesn''t mean you can''t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we''ve found for the week of Monday December 28th, 2015 to Sunday January 3rd, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that''s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we''ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday December 29th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Victory at Sea &amp; Christmas Beers at Hollingshead Delicatessan</strong>\n<em>Orange, 10am</em></h3>\nHollingshead is a little late to the Victory at Sea madness, but better late than never! They''ll be pouring a peanut butter variant, coconut, peppermint, and Captain Crunch cereal version on cask. The rest of their taps will be pouring a variety of Christmas Ales.\n<h3><strong>Kinetic Brewing''s Fourth Anniversary Party</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 12pm</em></h3>\nKinetic is celebrating their fourth year in style, tapping some of their rarest kegs, such as Inaugurale, Barrel aged First Gear, 2nd Gear, 3rd Gear, 2014 Paradox, 2015 Paradox, Dark Matter, and "Fourth Gear", their anniversary beer tapping at 6pm.\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony''s at Tony''s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nEnjoy a special mystery flight night version of Tuesdays at Tony''s featuring four beers that won''t be listed on the menu. If you can properly guess the style of ALL four beers, then you get a free beer!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday December 31st</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>New Year''s Eve Haven at Haven Gastropub</strong>\n<em>Orange, 11am</em></h3>\nOne of OC''s best gastropubs is opening up til 2am for NYE for a non-ticketed night of great food, craft beer, craft cocktails, and all your friends. They''ll be serving up their full menu as well as a 3-course Chef''s Prix-Fixe menu for $55/person with the option to add craft beer or wine pairings for $15 more. <a href="http://hoppedla.com/la-craft-beer-new-years-eve-2015/" target="_blank">Check out our 2016 NYE guide for more info.</a>\n<h3><strong>New Year''s Eve at Kinetic Brewing</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 12pm</em></h3>\nKinetic is getting NYE started early, opening up at 12 and a dinner special starting at 4pm. Their kitchen closes at 9pm, at which point DJ SwiFt will be taking over the speakers for your dancing pleasure. Craft beer will be flowing and they''ll also have champagne available for your midnight toast.\n<h3><strong>Happy New Year Happy Hour at Mohawk Bend</strong>\n<em>Echo Park, 3pm</em></h3>\nTo celebrate NYE, Mohawk Bend is opening up their Happy Hour menu from 3pm to 1:30am featuring discounted food, a limited selected of $4.50 California craft brews, $2 off wine, $5 well drinks, and two specialty cocktails.\n<h3><strong>NYE at Blue Palms Brewhouse</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 4pm</em></h3>\nBlue Palms is celebrating with all 24 of their draft beers for $4 all night. Their full menu will be available (truffle burger!), they''ll have a complimentary champagne toast at midnight, and they''ll be open until 3am (last call at 1:30 though).\n<h3><strong>NYE Dinner at Beachwood BBQ</strong>\n<em>Seal Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nAt Beachwood''s Seal Beach location, they''ll be serving up a special prix-fixe dinner from Chef Jameson for $35/person and you can add special beer pairings from cellarmaster Shawn for just $10 more. <a href="http://hoppedla.com/la-craft-beer-new-years-eve-2015/" target="_blank">Check out our 2016 NYE guide for more info.</a>\n<h3><strong>NYE at Surly Goat Encino</strong>\n<em>Encino, 8pm</em></h3>\nThe newly renamed Surly Goat Encino (formerly Sweeney''s Ale House) is throwing a little NYE bash with a hosted bar, music, and a champagne toast at midnight. For $50 pre-sale ($75 at the door) you can take your pick from their 28 taps, all of their wines, any well cocktails including their tap cocktails, the Dublin Donkey, and champagne. Not a bad option for SFV beer drinkers because you know they''ll be pouring some awesome brews.\n<h3><strong>New Year’s Eve at Little Bear</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 8pm</em></h3>\nSurly Goat''s sister bar in DTLA, Little Bear, is hosting a similar shindig of their own. Hosted bar from 8pm to Midnight with a champagne toast, all for $50.00 pre-sale.\n<h3><strong>NYE at the Salted Pig</strong>\n<em>Riverside, 8pm</em></h3>\nFor those of you closer to Riverside, The Salted Pig is hosting a special 5 course dinner for $75/person or $100 with paired beers complete with a midnight toast. Seats are filling up, so call (951) 848-4020 to make your reservation.\n<h3><strong>No Cover New Year''s Eve Bash at Angel City Brewery</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 8pm</em></h3>\nAngel City is back with their signature NYE bash which is no cover, no dress code, just craft beer and fun times. They''ll have food trucks, live music, party favors to the first 150 guests, and there will be a midnight toast with their Champagne Berliner beer brewed special for the holidays.\n<h3><strong>NYE at Tony''s at Tony''s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 8:30pm</em></h3>\n<strong>SOLD OUT!</strong> Tony''s Darts Away is throwing an all-inclusive NYE party with UNLIMITED pours of their California craft beers (check our NYE guide to see some of the beers you''ll get to choose from), all-you-care-to-eat pub food and a raffle featuring beers hand-picked from owner Tony Yanow''s private cellar. Tickets are already all sold out, but look out for this event next year.\n<h3><strong>New Year''s Eve at Golden Road Brewing</strong>\n<em>Burbank/Glendale, 9pm</em></h3>\nIf you''re one of the few left who aren''t anti AB-owned Golden Road, they''re throwing a NYE bash featuring craft beer, champagne, and music by DJ Onion. They''re also doing a RSVP-only $50 four-course dinner paired with Golden Road beer including a limited release barrel-aged beer starting at 6pm. Vegan options as well as their full menu are also available. Just show up for the party, RSVP to abby@goldenroad.la for the dinner.\n<h3><strong>Coast to Coast Toast NYE at Tuning Fork</strong>\n<em>Studio City</em></h3>\nTuning Fork Gastropub in Studio City is bringing back their "Coast To Coast Toast" for the third year in a row. Starting at 9pm, they''ll ring in 2016 with a toast every hour on the hour for each US time zone. Chef Jay will have some delicious food specials and the bar will feature some great drink prices.\n<h3><strong>New Year’s Eve Party at Ladyface</strong>\n<em>Agoura Hills</em></h3>\nLadyface is back again with their signature NYE celebration where you can reserve a table starting at 9pm, which includes your choice of sparkling white, cellar beer, or Ladyface pitcher. For 2 people, you pay $75 and get your choice of 1 of the above. For 4 people, you pay $100 and get your choice of 2 of the above. To add 2 more people to your reservation, just add $50 and it includes another beverage choice. Or forget the reservation and just stop by to hang out - no cover. They''ll also have live music by local bands, Captions at 9pm and Magic Bronson at 11pm. Email events@ladyfaceale.com for more info.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday January 1st</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>New Year''s Day Brunch at Kinetic Brewing</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 10am</em></h3>\nRecover from your NYE shenanigans with brunch at Kinetic in Lancaster. They''ll be pouring mimosas and beery marys, as well as a delicious breakfast at the pub until 3pm.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday January 3rd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>4th Anniversary Celebration at I &amp; I Brewing</strong>\n<em>Chino, 11am</em></h3>\nI &amp; I Brewing in Chino is celebrating their 4th anniversary with a beer release, food trucks, live music, and special glassware. Tickets are $10 and they include your first pint and a specialty glass. <a href="http://iandi4th.brownpapertickets.com/" target="_blank">Grab them here.</a>', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Dec 28, 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-dec-28', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1738', 0, 'post', '', 0);
