(1746, 4, '2015-12-27 23:12:28', '2015-12-28 07:12:28', 'Still figuring out your New Year’s Eve plans? Hopped LA has you covered so you can ring in the New Year with a glass of something cold, hoppy, and delicious when the clock strikes midnight. Here are the top 2015 NYE events in LA to get your craft beer on.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1747 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/haven-nye-e1451279712759.jpg" alt="Haven Gastropub NYE 2015" width="500" height="625" />\nNew Year''s Eve Haven at Haven Gastropub</strong>\n<em>Orange, 11am</em></h3>\nOne of OC''s best gastropubs is opening up til 2am for NYE for a non-ticketed night of great food, craft beer, craft cocktails, and all your friends. They''ll be serving up their full menu as well as a 3-course Chef''s Prix-Fixe menu for $55/person with the option to add craft beer or wine pairings for $15 more. Here''s what you can expect on the food side of things:\n\n<em><strong>Course #1 - choice of</strong></em>\n<em>Foie Gras Torchon, blood orange gelée, brioche toast point, hazelnut, frisée, blood orange-taragon relish</em>\n<em>or</em>\n<em>Butter Poached Oysters, vodka-cauliflower velou</em><span class="text_exposed_show"><em>té, crispy potato, caviar</em></span>\n\n<em><strong>Course #2 - choice of</strong></em>\n<em>Thyme Basted Sea Bass, squid ink gnochetti, shrimp and champagne butter, broccoli rabe</em>\n<em>or</em>\n<em>Rib Eye, smoked celery root purée, whey glazed turnip, port and bacon braised black kale, bbq demi</em>\n\n<em><strong>Course #3 - choice of</strong></em>\n<em>Mexican Hot Chocolate pots de crême, pepita biscotti, mescal-cinnamon whip cream</em>\n<em>or</em>\n<em>Honey Crisp Apple Galette, cider caramel cream, tart apple sorbet</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1748 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/kinetic-nye-e1451279816519.jpg" alt="Kinetic NYE" width="600" height="222" />\nNew Year''s Eve at Kinetic Brewing</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 12pm</em></h3>\nKinetic is getting NYE started early, opening up at 12 and a dinner special starting at 4pm. Their kitchen closes at 9pm, at which point DJ SwiFt will be taking over the speakers for your dancing pleasure. Craft beer will be flowing and they''ll also have champagne available for your midnight toast.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1749 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/mohawk-nye-e1451279891939.jpg" alt="Mohawk Bend NYE" width="450" height="696" />\nHappy New Year Happy Hour at Mohawk Bend</strong>\n<em>Echo Park, 3pm</em></h3>\nTo celebrate NYE, Mohawk Bend is opening up their Happy Hour menu from 3pm to 1:30am featuring discounted food, a limited selected of $4.50 California craft brews, $2 off wine, $5 well drinks, and two specialty cocktails. This is a great way to celebrate NYE the affordable way and still get awesome beers in the process.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1750 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/blue-palms-nye.jpg" alt="Blue Palms NYE" width="560" height="374" />\nNYE at Blue Palms Brewhouse</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 4pm</em></h3>\nBlue Palms is celebrating with all 24 of their draft beers for $4 all night. Their full menu will be available (truffle burger!), they''ll have a complimentary champagne toast at midnight, and they''ll be open until 3am (last call at 1:30 though). If you''re in Hollywood for NYE, this is where you''re gonna want to be.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1751 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/beachwood-nye-e1451280300305.jpg" alt="Beachwood BBQ NYE" width="500" height="647" />\nNYE Dinner at Beachwood BBQ</strong>\n<em>Seal Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nAt Beachwood''s Seal Beach location, they''ll be serving up a special prix-fixe dinner from Chef Jameson for $35/person and you can add special beer pairings from cellarmaster Shawn for just $10 more. If you''ve been to Beachwood before, you know this dinner is bound to be awesome.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1752 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/surly-goat-nye-e1451280380270.jpg" alt="Surly Goat NYE" width="600" height="600" />\nNYE at Surly Goat Encino</strong>\n<em>Encino, 8pm</em></h3>\nThe newly renamed Surly Goat Encino (formerly Sweeney''s Ale House) is throwing a little NYE bash with a hosted bar, music, and a champagne toast at midnight. For $50 pre-sale ($75 at the door) you can take your pick from their 28 taps, all of their wines, any well cocktails including their tap cocktails, the Dublin Donkey, and champagne. Not a bad option for SFV beer drinkers because you know they''ll be pouring some awesome brews.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1753 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/little-bear-nye-e1451281258414.jpg" alt="Little Bear NYE" width="600" height="338" />\nNew Year’s Eve at Little Bear</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 8pm</em></h3>\nSurly Goat''s sister bar in DTLA, Little Bear, is hosting a similar shindig of their own. Details are scarce, but it all seems similar to Surly''s: hosted bar from 8pm to Midnight with a champagne toast, all for $50.00 pre-sale (probably $75 at the door).\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1754 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/salted-pig-nye-e1451281327750.jpg" alt="Salted Pig NYE" width="600" height="597" />\nNYE at the Salted Pig</strong>\n<em>Riverside, 8pm</em></h3>\nFor those of you closer to Riverside, The Salted Pig is hosting a special 5 course dinner for $75/person or $100 with paired beers complete with a midnight toast. Seats are filling up, so call (951) 848-4020 to make your reservation.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1758 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/angel-city-nye-e1451282330735.jpg" alt="Angel City NYE" width="600" height="300" />\nNo Cover New Year''s Eve Bash at Angel City Brewery</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 8pm</em></h3>\nAngel City is back with their signature NYE bash which is no cover, no dress code, just craft beer and fun times. They''ll have food trucks like Kai Kai Dumplings, Market Burgers and Peaches Smokehouse &amp; Southern Kitchen, live music from Naked Walrus, JUICE, and Dirty Lingo, party favors to the first 150 guests, and there will be a midnight toast with their Champagne Berliner beer brewed special for the holidays. The beer is a twist on their regular Berliner-Weisse, blended with Chardonnay and Viognier grape must, then fermented with a house strain of Belgian yeast and pushed to the limit of carbonation. Nice way to toast to the new year in Downtown LA!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1760 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/tonys-nye-e1451282952899.jpg" alt="Tonys NYE" width="600" height="600" />\nNYE at Tony''s at Tony''s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 8:30pm</em></h3>\n<strong>SOLD OUT!</strong> Tony''s Darts Away is throwing an all-inclusive NYE party with UNLIMITED pours of their California craft beers like Pliny the Elder, Blind Pig, Oude Tart, Spontaneous Cheer, Brandy Barrel-Aged Angel''s Share, and Bourbon Barrel-Aged Santa''s Little Helper. You''ll also get all-you-care-to-eat pub food and a raffle featuring beers hand-picked from owner Tony Yanow''s private cellar. <strong>Tickets are all sold out now, but look out for this event to come back next year!</strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1755 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/golden-road-nye-e1451281394550.jpg" alt="Golden Road NYE" width="400" height="618" />\nNew Year''s Eve at Golden Road Brewing</strong>\n<em>Burbank/Glendale, 9pm</em></h3>\nIf you''re one of the few left who aren''t anti AB-owned Golden Road, they''re throwing a NYE bash featuring craft beer, champagne, and music by DJ Onion. They''re also doing a RSVP-only $50 four-course dinner paired with Golden Road beer including a limited release barrel-aged beer starting at 6pm. Vegan options as well as their full menu are also available. Just show up for the party, RSVP to abby@goldenroad.la for the dinner.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1757 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/ladyface-nye-e1451281793435.jpg" alt="Ladyface NYE" width="400" height="620" />\nNew Year’s Eve Party at Ladyface</strong>\n<em>Agoura Hills, 9pm</em></h3>\nLadyface is back again with their signature NYE celebration where starting at 9pm you can reserve a table, which includes your choice of sparkling white, cellar beer, or a Ladyface pitcher. For 2 people, you pay $75 and get your choice of 1 of the above. For 4 people, you pay $100 and get your choice of 2 of the above. To add 2 more people to your reservation, just add $50 and it includes another beverage choice. Or forget the reservation and just stop by to hang out - no cover. They''ll also have live music by local bands, Captions at 9pm and Magic Bronson at 11pm. Great for all of you west Valley people, especially for couples and groups looking to keep it classy. Email events@ladyfaceale.com for more info.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1756 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/tuning-fork-nye-e1451281680507.jpg" alt="Tuning Fork NYE" width="600" height="401" />\nCoast to Coast Toast NYE at Tuning Fork</strong>\n<em>Studio City</em></h3>\nTuning Fork Gastropub in Studio City is bringing back their "Coast To Coast Toast" for the third year in a row. Starting at 9pm, they''ll ring in 2016 with a toast every hour on the hour for each US time zone. Chef Jay will have some delicious food specials and the bar will feature some great drink prices. They usually have a great tap list, so I''m assuming you''ll see more of the same for this event, maybe even some special kegs make an appearance.', 'Where to Celebrate New Year''s Eve 2015 with Craft Beer in LA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'la-craft-beer-new-years-eve-2015', '', '', '2015-12-27 23:12:28', '2015-12-28 07:12:28', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1746', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1802, 4, '2016-01-04 22:04:29', '2016-01-05 06:04:29', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />Here at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday January 4th to Sunday January 10th, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday December 15</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Tuesday Night Flights: Prairie Artisan Ales at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nHead on out to Select Beer Store for some special pours of Prairie''s awesome beers, including Bomb!, Brett C, and Birra.\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony’s featuring healthy eats with Chef Caroline</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nThis edition of Tuesdays at Tony''s is one that you can feel good about. Why? Well, that new years resolution about you eating better and exercising more is getting the support it needs from your pals at Tony''s Darts Away. So, Chef Caroline is whipping up some healthy eats (TBD), and you can''t partake in the food and/or a second beer until you pump out ten pushups. New year, new you!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday January 8</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Saison Loving Tap Takeover...With Cheese! at Buzz Wine Beer Shop</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nAll you saison lovers out there, Buzz has got a tap takeover for you! They''ll be pouring some of the best domestically brewed saisons and Vagabond Cheese will be in the house putting together special cheese pairings for the beer lineup. The saisons that they''ll be pouring include Prairie''s Birra, Saint Somewhere''s Cynthiana, Jolly Pumpkin''s Bam Bière, Green Bench''s Saison De Banc Noir, and Propolis'' Beltane Herbal Golden.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday January 9</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Eagle Rock Night at Craft Beer Cellar</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 4pm</em></h3>\nCraft Beer Cellar in Eagle Rock is making themselves right at home with their first of many Second Saturday Sessions. To kick things off, Eagle Rock Brewery is taking over the taps, the brewers are coming out, and Eagle Rock Brewery Public House is serving up some munchies. There will also be music and merch giveaways. When it''s time to hit the road, enjoy 10% off Eagle Rock bottles to-go and take the party back to your place.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday January 10</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Small Batch Sunday at King Harbor Brewing</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 3pm</em></h3>\nKing Harbor is kicking off the first of their Small Batch Sunday series, where you''ll be able to try some of the freshest small batch beer possible straight from their fermentation tanks. This first edition features two variations of their Oatmeal Porter, one blended with Coldbot Coffee''s African bean, the other blended with Coldbot Coffee''s Central American bean. This will be a cool opportunity to see how the terroir of these different regions affects the taste of the bean and how they interact with King Harbor''s Oatmeal Porter, so coffee beer lovers be sure to check this out!', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Jan 4, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-jan-4', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1802', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1817, 4, '2016-01-11 19:31:28', '2016-01-12 03:31:28', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />Here at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday January 11th to Sunday January 17th, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday January 12</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Anderson Valley Tap Takeover at Crazy Harry''s</strong>\n<em>Winnetka, 5pm</em></h3>\nYour local craft beer bar in the middle of the Valley is letting Anderson Valley take over its taps for the evening (and probably for several days afterward). No word on the tap list, but AV makes some solid brews, and their Boont Amber Ale will be $5, so worth checking out if you''re in the area.\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony''s featuring The Bruery at Tony''s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nTuesdays at Tonys is back again this week with a lineup from none other than The Bruery! They''ll be pouring Reuze, Batch 1731, Mash, and 4th Meal this evening, so head on out to Burbank and get your Bruery on.\n<h3><strong>Founders Brewing Comes to LA at Far Bar</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 7pm</em></h3>\nFounders Brewing is finally here and the folks at Far bar are helping you welcome them with open arms! They''ll be pouring Centennial IPA, Porter, Red''s Rye IPA, Oatmeal Stout Nitro, Breakfast Stout, Harvest Ale, Mosaic Promise, Pale Ale, and they''ll also have bottles of Project PAM available. Head on out and join the celebration!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday January 13</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Hangar 24 Tap Takeover at Kinetic Brewing Company</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 4pm</em></h3>\nHangar 24 will be heading out to Lancaster and pouring from the guest taps at Kinetic Brewing Co! They''ll be pouring Betty IPA, Helles Lager, Easy Glider session IPA, Chocolate Porter on Nitro, Double Betty, and at 6pm they''ll be tapping 2015 HammerHead and 2014 Pugachev''s.\n<h3><strong>Beer Dinner with Highland Park Brewery at Haven Gastropub</strong>\n<em>Orange, 6:30pm</em></h3>\nSurprise surprise, Haven in Orange is putting on another EPIC beer dinner, this time featuring the amazing beers of Highland Park Brewery. There will be 5 courses paired with some awesome beers and tickets will be $85. Check out the full menu and <a href="http://www.universe.com/highlandparkhaven" target="_blank">grab your tickets here</a> before they sell out!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday January 14</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Founders Brewing LA Launch Party at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nJoin Select Beer Store as they welcome Founders Brewing to LA! They''ll be pouring a bunch of Founders beers and will have a food truck stop by, so South Bay, hit it up!\n<h3><strong>From Farm to Palate: Saison Tasting at Green Jug</strong>\n<em>Woodland Hills, 5pm</em></h3>\nHey West Valley, Green Jug is hosting their first tasting of 2016 and if you love saisons, you''re in luck. Tastings are $9 and will include Modern Times Lomaland, Blackberry Farm Classic Saison, Perennial Saison de Lis, Shady Oak Barrelhouse Sonomatastic, and a couple more surprises.\n<h3><strong>Bierhall Karaoke at Alpine Village</strong>\n<em>Torrance, 5pm</em></h3>\nIf you''ve been dying to combine your two greatest loves: craft beer and karaoke, then you''ll be wanting to head down to Torrance to Alpine Village. 20+ craft beers, happy hour prices, and one of the most eclectic song books in LA.\n<h3><strong>Great Divide Tap Takeover at Uncle Henry''s Deli</strong>\n<em>Downey, 7pm</em></h3>\nUncle Henry is bringing in some friends from Great Divide in Colorado for a tap takeover. They''ll be pouring Chocolate Yeti, Espresso Yeti, Oatmeal Yeti, 21st Anniversary Sour Wine Aged, and Old Ruffian Barleywine.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday January 15</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>The Rookery Third Anniversary</strong>\n<em>Pomona, 11am</em></h3>\nIf you know Pomona, you know there''s one bar where you can get awesome craft beer. Yep, that''s right. The Rookery is celebrating their third anniversary all weekend long with a beer lineup that you probably won''t find anywhere else in the LA area. Stop on by for a chance to sip on Sanctum Unicobra Fire Cannon (Rookery Collab), Polymath Saisons of the Stoneage (Rookery Collab), Alosta Annum, Almanac Peach de Brettaville, Ohana Surf Shack Flanders, The Bruery Melange #3, The Lost Abbey Track #10, Wiens Crowded, Alesmith BA Speedway Stout, Modern Times Devil''s Teeth with Coffee, Monkish Seme Della Vita, Council Beatitude Raspberry, El Segundo Broken Skull, Highland Park The Party IPA, Highland Park Company of Parrots, Stillwater Gose Gone Wild, Eviltwin Ashtray Heart, Logsdon Peche n Brett (bottle), and Noble Ale Works Naughty Sauce.\n<h3><strong>Fourth Annual Barleywine Festival at Kinetic Brewing Company</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 11:30am</em></h3>\nApparently, Kinetic is hosting their fourth annual barleywine festival over the course of the weekend. I couldn''t find many details about it, but if you love barleywine, you''re gonna want to check this out.\n<h3><strong>Baja Beer Tasting at Craft Beer Cellar</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 4pm</em></h3>\nCraft Beer Cellar is celebrating craft beers from south of the border this Friday with some awesome brews from Cerveceria Insurgente, Cerveceria Agua Mala, and Cerveceria Wendlant. They''ll also be serving complimentary chips and salsa for your snacking pleasure.\n<h3><strong>Firestone Milk &amp; Cookies Night at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nFirestone''s Nitro Merlin Milk Stout is here and Select is celebrating by bringing in Specialty Brown Butter Cookie Co. cookies so you can celebrate with milk and cookies, adult style.\n<h3><strong>Barley Forge Tap Takeover at Buzz Wine Beer Shop</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nWatch out Downtown LA, Barley Forge is coming to town and taking over the tap at Buzz! If you haven''t had the chance to try this Costa Mesa brewery''s beers yet, this is your chance. They''ll be pouring Grandpa Tractor Dortmunder Lager, The Orange Curtain IPA, The Black Dahlia Belgian-style dark ale, and The Patsy rye stout with coconut which is one of my personal favorite beers. Check this event out, you won''t be disappointed!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday January 16</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Founder''s Brewing Tap Takeover at The Eight Bar in Whole Foods DTLA</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 12pm</em></h3>\nFounders is taking over the taps at The Eight Bar and giving you your chance to get bottles of KBS! They''ll be pouring All Day IPA, Pale Ale, Dirty Bastard, Mosaic Promise, Porter, Nitro Oatmeal Stout, Breakfast Stout, and Blushing Monk 2015 and if you keep your receipt, you''ll get the chance to come back and grab bottles of KBS next week.\n<h3><strong>2nd Anniversary Party at Public Beer Wine Shop</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 3pm</em></h3>\nLong Beach''s best spot to grab a beer or pick up a bottle to-go is having their 2nd anniversary celebration and it sounds like they''re not fooling around! Brewist LBC will be providing free tasters of their Belgian style Witbier and Sweet Stout while supplies last from 6-9pm. Shady Grove Foods will be serving up their delicious food while supplies last from 7-10pm. Not to mention, they''ll be pouring Beachwood Tovarish, Sierra Nevada Bigfoot, Smog City The Nothing, Monkish Magnificat, Logsdon Far West Vlaming, El Segundo Foxy Brown, Phantom Carriage Broadacres with Dragonfruit, Ladyface 6th Anniversary Ale, Highland Park Partly Cloudy, and Boulevard Saison Brett. Better swing by and check this one out.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday January 17</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Bottle Share - Playa Edition at 38 Degrees Ale House</strong>\n<em>Alhambra, 12pm</em></h3>\n38 Degrees is hosting a bottle share, and if you know the caliber of people who work at and frequent the craft beer bar, you can expect some whales to show up that day. Dig out the best of your cellar and head out to Alhambra for a daytime bottle share to remember!\n<h3><strong>Bikes &amp; Brews at Craft Beer Cellar</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 12:15pm</em></h3>\nYou don''t have to give up those New Years resolutions just yet! Craft Beer Cellar is teaming up with their neighbors at Rev Cycle for a fun workout paired with craft beer. $25 gets you a 1 hour cycling class at Rev and a pint or flight of beer at Craft Beer Cellar afterward. The class is filling up, so <a href="http://revcyclingla.com/" target="_blank">reserve your spot here</a>.', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Jan 11, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-jan-11', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1817', 0, 'post', '', 3),
(1864, 4, '2016-01-19 22:16:42', '2016-01-20 06:16:42', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />Here at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday January 18th to Sunday January 24th, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Monday January 18</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>2nd Annual Dinner with the Brewmaster at Broken Bit</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 5pm</em></h3>\nBravery Brewmaster, Brian Avery, is joining up with Chef Harry Estrada of Broken Bit for a special 5 course dinner paired with 5 Bravery beers. Seats are limited, so grab your tickets ASAP!\n<h3><strong>Founders Brewing Launch Celebration at Barbara''s at the Brewery</strong>\n<em>Lincoln Heights, 5pm</em></h3>\nFounders officially hits LA with a tap takeover at Barbara''s. Tap list TBA.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday January 19</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger Raffle at Beachwood Brewing</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 11:30am</em></h3>\nBeachwood is back for the 5th year with their Pliny the Younger raffle benefitting the Melanoma Research Foundation in memory of Tony Carbone. The $5 tickets will be on sale January 19th at 11:30am through February 20th at 10pm at both Beachwood locations. Buy as many as you want for your chance to win a pour of Pliny the Younger at your leisure between February 23rd and March 3rd.\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony’s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nTony''s will be pouring three vintages of Stone Russian Imperial Stout: 2013, 2014, 2015. Grab a single pour for $6.75 or a flight of all three for $14.\n<h3><strong>Bottle Flight Night with Logsdon Farmhouse Ales at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nSelect is featuring the awesome beers from Logsdon Farmhouse Ales: Kili Wit, Seizoen, and the multiple award winning Peche ''n Brett (2012 World Beer Cup Gold, 2014 Silver GABF). Get yours!\n<h3><strong>Founders Launch Party at Blue Palms</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 7pm</em></h3>\nFounders is taking over the taps at Blue Palms with 15 beers pouring, including the highly sought after, KBS, tapping at 7pm. They''ll also be pouring All Day IPA, Centennial IPA, Dirty Bastard Scotch Ale, Pale Ale, Porter, Red''s Rye IPA, Breakfast Stout, Mosaic Promise IPA, Backwoods Bastard BA Scotch Ale, Blushing Monk , Harvest Ale Wet Hopped IPA, and Oatmeal Stout on Nitro.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday January 20</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Fog Island Draft Release at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 11:30am</em></h3>\nJoin the folks from Phantom Carriage for a brand new draft release of Fog Island, their first ever "clean" beer. Yep, that means no funk, sour, or tartness in this one. Fog Island clocks in at 5.3% ABV, is dry hopped with 100% mosaic, and features notes of stone fruit and blueberry. Growler fills will also be available. Sounds like a good one!\n<h3><strong>6th Anniversary Brewmasters Dinner at Ladyface</strong>\n<em>Agoura Hills, 6pm</em></h3>\nLadyface is kicking off their 6th anniversary celebration week with a special beer dinner featuring guest Chef Daniel Mattern. Five delicious courses will be paired with Ladyface ales, including some cellar surprises &amp; Ladyface 6th Anniversary Ale "Iron Lady", a golden strong ale brewed with Viognier grape must and steel fermented with French oak. Tickets are $75 per person. Check out the menu below and then <a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/e/ladyface-6th-anniversary-brewmasters-dinner-tickets-20243458730" target="_blank">get your tickets here</a>.\n<strong>Course 1:</strong> Amuse Bouche &amp; Apperatif\nRoasted Kabocha Squash, Dandelion, Burrata, Saba &amp; Brown Bread\nBeer: Midnight Special\n<strong>Course 2:</strong> Grilled Scallop, Black Rice, Tangerines &amp; Watercress\nBeer: Oak Barrel-Aged Tripel W/ Fresh Kumquats on cask\n<strong>Course 3:</strong> Boudin Blanc, Celery Root. Sweet &amp; Sour Prunes\nBeer: Dérailleur®\n<strong>Course 4:</strong> Ale-Braised Lamb Shank, Curried Peas, Fingerling Potatoes &amp; Raita\nBeer: 6th Anniversary Ale\n<strong>Course 5:</strong> Barley Sticky Pudding With Whipped Crème Fraiche\nBeer Blue-Belly Barleywine\n<h3><strong>Steal the Glass with Firestone Walker at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nEureka is doing a special version of their Steal the Glass night featuring Firestone Walker''s new Velvet Merlin Oatmeal Milk Stout on nitro served with Brown Butter Cookies made in Cayucos, CA. Plus you get to take the Firestone glass home with you!\n<h3><strong>Founders Brewing Tap Takeover at Naja''s Place</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 6pm</em></h3>\nFounders continues their takeover of So Cal with a takeover at Naja''s Place. The beer lineup includes All Day IPA, Backwoods Bastard, Centennial IPA, Breakfast Stout, Porter, Red’s Rye IPA, Dirty Bastard, Imperial Stout, and Blushing Monk 2015\n<h3><strong>Women''s Beer Forum: New Beers for the New Year at Eagle Rock Brewery</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 7pm</em></h3>\nHere''s an event for the ladies of the LA craft beer scene. The Women''s Beer Forum will be gathering at Eagle Rock Brewery, talking craft beer, and tasting brews from Arts District Brewing''s Devon Randall. Flights are $12, there will be a food truck outside, and you can <a href="http://eaglerockbrewery.com/events/women-s-beer-forum-new-beers-for-the-new-year" target="_blank">reserve your spot here</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday January 21</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Nothing''s Better Than Cupcakes at Southland Beer</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 5pm</em></h3>\nSouthland is tapping a keg of Smog City''s awesome double chocolate imperial stout, The Nothing, and Viva Los Cupcakes will be serving up Mexican flavored cupcakes to go along with it. They''ll even have bottles of The Nothing to buy and take home with you. What''s better than cupcakes? The Nothing. Thats what.\n<h3><strong>Battling El Nino: Imperial Stout Tasting at Green Jug</strong>\n<em>Woodland Hills, 5pm</em></h3>\nGreen Jug''s next tasting features some big winter beers including Deschutes'' The Abyss, Belching Beaver''s Horchata Stout, Old Orange''s Smudgepot Imperial Stout, Drake''s Jolly Rodger 2015 Imperial Coffee Porter, plus two more. Flights are $9.\n<h3><strong>Hangar 24 Tap Takeover at Beer Belly</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 6:30pm</em></h3>\nThe Beer Belly crew is hanging with Hangar 24 and some of their great beers like 2015 Pugachev''s Cobra, 2014 Pugachev''s Cobra, 2013 Hammerhead, Betty, Double Betty, Orange Wheat, Easy Glider, Iconic DIPA, Chocolate Porter on Nitro, Helles Lager, Alt Bier, and Amarillo Pale Ale.\n<h3><strong>Almanac Tap Takeover at Overland Cafe</strong>\n<em>Palms, 7pm</em></h3>\nOverland Cafe''s invited Almanac in for a tap takeover featuring some really awesome beers including Barbary Coast Imperial Stout brewed with Dandelion Chocolate cacao nibs, chili pepper, sea salt, vanilla and oak staves, their West Coast Style IPA, Saison Doloroes Dry-Hopped Farmhouse Ale brewed with locally grown wheat, rye and barley, and Elephant Heart de Brettaville Farmhouse ale aged in wine barrels with Elephant Heart plums and dry-hopped with El Dorado hops.\n<h3><strong>Oceanside Ale Works Tap Takeover at Uncle Henry''s Deli</strong>\n<em>Downey, 7pm</em></h3>\nUncle Henry''s will have Oceanside Ale Works in the house featuring their Oaked Flanders Red, Bourbon Imperial Stout, Bourbon Winter Warmer, and Bourbon Strong Ale.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday January 22</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Eagle Rock Brewery 6th Anniversary Doubleheader Celebration at 38 Degrees Ale House</strong>\n<em>Monrovia, 5pm</em></h3>\nThe 38 Degrees crew is celebrating Eagle Rock''s 6th anniversary in a special way with a double header at their two locations. The first kicks off in Monrovia where the Eagle Rock Brewing team will be hanging out and taps will be pouring 3 specialty flights:\n\n<strong>ERB Core Brand Flight</strong>\nÜmläüt - A Pilsneresque Ale - 4.8% abv.\nManifesto - Belgian Style Witbier 5.7% abv.\nRevolution - Extra Pale Ale 5.2% abv\nPopulist IPA - IPAa 7.0% abv.\n<strong>ERB Specialty Flight</strong>\n2 North (Part of new Daytrip Series) American Brown Ale\nZes - Collaboration 6th Anniversary Golden Strong Ale - 8.0% abv.\nAll of Your Oat - Double IPA with Oats - 8.0% abv.\nYearling Batch 3- Amber American Sour aged in wine barrels. 6.6% abv.\n<strong>ERB Sour Flight (Poured from bottles)</strong>\nYearling Batch 2 - Amber American Sour aged in wine barrels - 6.6% abv.\nTarte Noir Batch 1 - Dark Sour Ale - 7% abv.\nTarte Noir Batch 2 - Dark Sour Ale - 7% abv.\nEquinox - Sour Blond Ale - 6.0% abv.\n<h3><strong>Eagle Rock Brewery 6th Anniversary Doubleheader Celebration at 38 Degrees Ale House</strong>\n<em>Alhambra, 8pm</em></h3>\nThe Eagle Rock celebration continues at 38 Degrees Alhambra at 8pm where the same beer flight specials apply.\n<h3><strong>Wolf Creek Tap Takeover at Eagle Rock Lounge</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 7pm</em></h3>\nWolf Creek will be pouring 4 of their beers at the Eagle Rock Lounge and the first 24 people will get free pint glasses.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday January 23</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Transplants Brewing Grand Opening</strong>\n<em>Palmdale, 12pm</em></h3>\nThe long awaiting grand opening of Transplants Brewing is finally here! Head on out to Palmdale and partake in the ribbon cutting ceremony, live art, and special beers pouring. Come on out and welcome one of the LA area''s newest breweries!\n<h3><strong>Coffee Beer &amp; Donuts at Southland Beer</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 12pm</em></h3>\nSouthland Beer is after our hearts with this one, an event pairing coffee beers and donuts. Donuts will be provided by California Donuts in Koreatown and the taplist will include Highland Park''s Wakeup on nitro (Brewed with Tyresto coffee), Telegraph Handlebar Abbey (With cold-pressed coffee from Handlebar Coffee Roasters), Left Hand Bittersweet Imperial Coffee Milk Stout (With Allegro Coffee''s Mocha Java Blend), Claremont Craft Ale''s Coffee Del IPA (With "Colombian Giraldo" from Klatch Roasting). They''ll be pouring a flight of these beers and will also be pouring Smog City''s Coffee Porter and a couple other coffee beer surprises.\n<h3><strong>January Bottle Release & Tasting Room Open at Beachwood Blendery</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 2pm</em></h3>\nBeachwood Blendery is holding their first bottle release of 2016 on Saturday and opening up their tasting room for the weekend, 2-10pm on Saturday and 12-6pm on Sunday. They''ll be releasing a Barrel-Aged Saison for $15 a bottle, Berliner "Rice" for $13 a bottle, and Spelt Saison with Mosaic for $13 a bottle. They''ll also have some of these beers pouring on draft, a couple past release bottles for sale, and t-shirts available. If you''ve been waiting to check out Beachwood Blendery, here''s your chance!\n<h3><strong>Iron Triangle Brewing Grand Opening</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 5pm</em></h3>\nHere''s one that a lot of people have been waiting for: the grand opening of Iron Triangle Brewing! This brewery opening has gotten a ton of buzz over the last year and on Saturday they''ll have live music, food of some kind, and will be pouring 7-10 beers at their big, brand spanking new, Arts District brewery. This is an event you won''t want to miss.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday January 24</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Triple 6th Anniversaries with Eagle Rock, Ladyface &amp; Strand</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 12pm</em></h3>\nEagle Rock Brewery is not only celebrating their own 6th anniversary, but also the 6th anniversaries of fellow breweries, Strand and Ladyface. Plan on having plenty of beer from all three breweries, a food truck or two, and fun! This is a great way to pay tribute to a three breweries that have pioneered the recent craft brewery movement in LA.\n<h3><strong>Ladyface 6th Anniversary Invitational</strong>\n<em>Agoura Hills, 12pm</em></h3>\nLadyface has something awesome planned for their 6th anniversary and you need to know about it! They''ve put together an invitational boutique beer festival with some cellared, barrel-aged special release and hard-to-find ales from our fellow brewers. They''ll also be pouring from their own cellar reserve list as well as 6th Anniversary collaboration ales "Iron Lady" and "Zes" from EagleRock. Tickets are $35 and include a commemorative glass &amp; 20 tasting samples of your choice. They''ll be serving food from their regular menu and seating will be first come first served, so get there early if you want a seat.\n<h3><strong>Amarantha Bottle Release at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 12pm</em></h3>\nGet ready for a new bottle release from LA''s sour beer brewery, Phantom Carriage! Amarantha is a 6.3% Lambic-Inspired Wild Ale aged with blueberries. Bottles are $14 each and there is a 2 bottle limit, so head on down to the South Bay and get your sour on.\n<h3><strong>2nd Annual Burns Supper at MacLeod Ale</strong>\n<em>Van Nuys, 6pm</em></h3>\nMacLeod is back with their 2nd annual Burns Supper, which is a traditional Scottish event that includes a grand feast, poetry, bagpipes, and of course, fantastic ale. Kilts recommended, but not required. Tickets are $60 and <a href="https://cask.ticketbud.com/macleod-ale-2nd-annual-burns-supper" target="_blank">you can grab them here</a>.', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Jan 18, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-jan-18', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1864', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1875, 4, '2016-01-26 08:44:32', '2016-01-26 16:44:32', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />Here at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday January 25th to Sunday January 31st, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday January 26</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Speakeasy Tap Takeover at Darryl''s Couch</strong>\n<em>Camarillo, 5:30pm</em></h3>\nSpeakeasy is taking over the taps at Darryl''s Couch with a few beers you don''t see on draft around these parts too often. They''ll be pouring Syndicate Barrel-Aged Vintage Ale, Butchertown India Black Ale, Big Daddy American India Pale Ale, Prohibition American Amber Ale, and Pop Gun German Pilsner. They''ll also have the ConFusion food truck on site for all your eating needs.\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony''s: Gose Flight Night at Tony''s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nTuesdays at Tony''s is back this week with a flight of some awesome Gose beers. They''ll be pouring Anderson Valley''s Blood Orange Gose, Almanac''s Golden Gate Gose and Ginger Gose, and Sierra Nevada''s Otra Vez. Flights are $22, single pours are $6.75.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday January 27</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>One Night Stand Kickoff Event at Beer Belly</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 5pm</em></h3>\nBeer Belly is kicking off their 2016 One Night Stand series with a special keg from each of this year''s participating breweries. They''ll be pouring Arts District Brewing''s Lemon Honey Golden Ale, Noble Ale Works'' Do You Smell What the Waka’s Cooking?, Beachwood''s Hops of Fury, Three Weavers'' Tooth &amp; Claw, Firestone Walker Barrelworks'' Bretta Weisse, a special surprise beer from Monkish, Phantom Carriage''s Triple Curse, Modern Times'' Devil’s Teeth with Coffee, Highland Park Brewery''s Junior Junior, Smog City''s Spittin’ n Cussin’, and The Bruery Terreux''s Juggling Walruses.\n<h3><strong>Steal the Glass Night featuring Founders at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nThis week, Eureka''s got Founders Brewing in the house featuring two handles of beers TBA and glassware for you to take home.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday January 28</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Stout Thing at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 5pm</em></h3>\nPhantom Carriage is putting its guest taps to the test with a super special stout night featuring Speakeasy Scarface, Bells Expedition Stout, Epic Big Bad Baptist, Great Divide Oak-Aged Yeti, Big Sky Ivan the Terrible, Firestone Walker Velvet Merlin on Nitro, Stone 12th Anniversary Bitter Chocolate Oatmeal Stout, Smog City The Nothing, DrieFontein Zwet.Be, Stillwater Surround Oak, Deschutes The Abyss, and Artiflex Imperial Stout on Nitro. And if that wasn''t enough, they''ll also have bottles of Firestone Walker Velvet Merkin, Eclipse 50/50, North Coast Old Rasputin, Port Brewing Santa’s Little Helper, and Amager Bryghus / Jester King Danish Metal. Pair all that dark beer with horror films, doom metal, a stout float, a "White Zombie" ice cream cookie, or artisan meat &amp; Vagabond cheese.\n<h3><strong>Attack of the Skullys: Paradox Beer Company at Green Jug</strong>\n<em>Woodland Hills, 5pm</em></h3>\nGreen Jug is bringing Paradox 31-36 to the Valley for a special sour beer tasting. Enjoy #31 Salted Apricot Sour, #32 Dry Hopped Sour Red, #33 Sour Pumpkin Brown, #34 Ginger Pear Sour, #35 Salted Plum Sour, and #36 Golden Coconut Sour. Flights are $14.\n<h3><strong>Meet the Valley Brewers at Taps Gastropub</strong>\n<em>Northridge, 5pm</em></h3>\nThe brewers in the San Fernando Valley are coming together at Taps Gastropub for a special SFV beer night on Thursday. Join 818 Brewing, San Fernando Brewing, Hand Brewed, and MacLeod for the first in a series of events uniting the breweries in the SFV.\n<h3><strong>Goose Island Tap Takeover at Lordsburg Taphouse &amp; Grill</strong>\n<em>La Verne, 6pm</em></h3>\nJoin Lordsburge Taphouse in welcoming Goose Island brews to their tap handles! They''ll be pouring some of your favorites like 2014 Bourbon County Brand Stout, 2014 Bourbon County Coffee Stout, 2014 Bourbon County Barleywine, 2014 Bourbon County Vanilla Rye, Lolita Raspberry Wild Ale Aged in Cabernet Sauvignon Wine Barrels, Sofie Belgian Style Farmhouse Ale, and 312 Urban Wheat Ale.\n<h3><strong>Council Beatitude Tap Takeover at Uncle Henry''s Deli</strong>\n<em>Downey, 7pm</em></h3>\nHead on over to Uncle Henry''s for a tap takeover of Council''s awesome tart saison series, Beatitude. They''ll be pouring several different versions like Three Berry, Apricot, Pineapple, Passion Fruit, and Raspberry.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday January 29</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Ashland Hill One Year Anniversary Celebration</strong>\n<em>Santa Monica, 11am</em></h3>\nAshland Hill is celebrating their one year anniversary with $1 beers and other food and drink specials all day. Sure, the tap list isn''t exactly comparable to other westside joints like Library Alehouse and Daily Pint, but they pour a good amount of solid brews like Ballast Point Grapefruit Sculpin, Smog City Hoptonic, Goose Island Bourbon County Brand Stout, and Monkish Feminist. Plus, did we mention $1 beers all day in Santa Monica? Not sure you''ll find that anywhere else.\n<h3><strong>Hangar 24 Tap Takeover at Blue Palms</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 4pm</em></h3>\nBlue Palms is back with another epic tap takeover, this time with Redlands'' Hangar 24 Brewery. In addition to some of their classics like Orange Wheat, Betty IPA, and Betty Double IPA, they are bringing along some heavy fire, including Pugachev''s Cobra Russian Imperial Stout 2014, Hammerhead Barleywine 2012, Hammerhead Barleywine 2015, Tailslide Strong Ale 2013, Vinaceous Old Ale 2015, Winter Warmer, and Nitro Chocolate Porter. Strong ale fans unite!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday January 30</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>New Beer Release: Cerveza Hermosa at King Harbor</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 2pm</em></h3>\nKing Harbor is starting the summer beach party a little early this year with the release of their brand new Mexican Amber Lager, Cerveza Hermosa. They''ll be celebrating the release at the brewery with free carne asada tacos (while they last - grillin'' starts at 2pm) and a Michelada bar with Cayucos Hot Sauce and Shellback''s Tavern Bloody Mary mix. Just because its winter in LA, doesn''t mean it can''t feel like summer in Cabo, right?!\n<h3><strong>Almanac Sours + Specialty Darks at The Oaks Tavern</strong>\n<em>Sherman Oaks, 2pm</em></h3>\nThe Oaks is bringing out the big guns on Saturday with some awesome sours from Almanac and some big dark beers from a few different breweries. For $15, you can choose four 5oz tasters, or for $24 you can get tasters of all 8 of the following beers:Almanac Dogpatch Grand Cru, Almanac Farmer''s Reserve Grand Cru, Almanac Pumpkin Sour, Allagash Nancy, Ballast Point Victory at Sea Coconut, Firestone Velvet Merlin Milk Stout Nitro, Elysian Punkaccino Coffee Pumpkin Ale, and Allagash James Bean, Tripel infused w/ cold pressed coffee.\n<h3><strong>An Evening with Famille Rue at Public Beer Wine Shop</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 3pm</em></h3>\nThe Bruery and Breury Terreux are headed to Long Beach''s favorite bottle shop &amp; tasting room with some awesome beers for you to try. On draft and in bottles will be Fourthmeal (collaboration with Maine Beer Company), So Happens It''s Tuesday, Prairie Rue (collaboration with Prairie Artisan Ales), and Humulus Rueuze. They''ll also be pouring a special draft only Rice &amp; Beans, their popular Or Xata spring seasonal dosed with fresh coffee beans. Beers start pouring at 3, live music starts around 9. Head on out!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday January 31</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Beer &amp; Donut Pairing Event at Craft Beer Cellar</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 11am</em></h3>\nYour favorite Eagle Rock bottle shop &amp; tasting room is hosting a nice little daytime beer &amp; breakfast pairing to end your week right. Enjoy four Donut Friend mini-donuts (Javabreaker, Chocolate Glazed, Bacon, and Poppyghandi) paired with a flight of four delicious craft beers carefully selected to compliment the flavor of each donut respectively (Ballast Point Victory at Sea, Youngs Double Chocolate Stout, Aecht Schlenkerla Rauchbier Marzen, and Allagash Saison). They''ll also have cold brew coffee from Found Coffee for a little additional pick-me-up. Tickets are $15 and <a href="http://www.brownpapertickets.com/event/2496234" target="_blank">you can grab them here</a>.\n<h3><strong>Baskerville Bottle Release at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 12pm</em></h3>\nAnother bottle release from Phantom Carriage! This one is Baskerville, a 11.5% Imperial Stout aged in Four Roses Bourbon Barrels. Bottles are $13 apiece with 2 bottle max. This one is rather limited, so head over there to make sure you get yours!\n\n&nbsp;', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of Jan 25, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-jan-25', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1875', 0, 'post', '', 2);
