(1886, 4, '2016-02-01 23:18:08', '2016-02-02 07:18:08', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1890" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/craft-beer-superbowl-2016.jpg" alt="Los Angeles Craft Beer Superbowl 2016" width="1200" height="628" />The Super Bowl is back and we know you don''t want to spend the game sipping on fizzy yellow macro corporate beer at some douchey LA sports bar. You want to go somewhere where you can enjoy your beer as much as you enjoy the biggest football game of the year. Luckily, Los Angeles is home to a bunch of bars and several breweries that will allow you to do just that. Here are 13 great spots to drink craft beer during Super Bowl 50:\n<h3><strong>Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 10am</em></h3>\nWhile Select won''t be showing the game, they''re giving 10% off all multipacks to go, so you can be the hero when you show up at your Super Bowl party. While you''re there, enjoy a pour or two of Founders KBS, Faction Hop Soup, and Monkish Cart Fetish.\n<h3><strong>Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 11am</em></h3>\nPhantom Carriage is turning off the horror films in favor of the big game and is also releasing their newest bottled beer, Centennial Muis, a flavorful 100% brett wild Belgian blonde ale with Centennial hops. They''ll also have house smoked meats, fresh tamales, and classic Super Bowl snacks with the game playing on their 130" 4K projection theatre screen. Sours, snacks, and Super Bowl. Not a bad combo!\n<h3><strong>The Doughroom</strong>\n<em>Palms, 12pm</em></h3>\nHead on over to the west side where The Doughroom is throwing the game up on a big projector screen and dishing out some food and drink specials as well as a halftime raffle for 4 bottles from Toolbox Brewing. Right now they''re pouring some awesome brews like Pineapple Sculpin, Three Weavers Knotty DIPA, and Drake''s Jolly Roger, plus they''ll have two beers pouring from Toolbox and the leftovers from their Perennial Ales night, so there''s you''re basically guaranteed to find something you''ll love to sip on.\n<h3><strong>The Daily Pint</strong>\n<em>Santa Monica, 1pm</em></h3>\nLA''s diviest craft beer bar is throwing a laid back Super Bowl party where they''ll have the game up on their 12 foot big screen and free BBQ to munch on. Not to mention, some of the awesome beers they consistently have gracing their taps like Stone Ruination with toasted coconut and vanilla, Firestone Walker Nitro Merlin, New Belgium Le Terroir, Russian River Pliny the Elder, and more.\n<h3><strong>Brewyard Beer Co</strong>\n<em>Glendale, 1pm</em></h3>\nCatch the game at one of LA''s newest breweries in Glendale. They''ll have the game playing, beer specials flowing, and food from the Berlin Sausage and Grilled Cheese Food Truck available.\n<h3><strong>The Oaks Tavern</strong>\n<em>Sherman Oaks, 1pm</em></h3>\nThe Oaks is throwing a Super Bowl party that the Valley can get behind. Not only cause they''ll be pouring awesome beers (recent pours include Almanac Dogpatch Sour, Ballast Point Victory at Sea with Coconut, Firestone Walker Velvet Merlin, and they''ll also have Bourbon County 2013 &amp; 2014 on tap!), but also because every drink you buy gets you a raffle ticket. Which means you could possibly take home a Bud Light field goal table which is essentially is like the paper football field goal flicking game you played in class during high school but on steroids.\n<h3><strong>Alosta Brewing Co</strong>\n<em>Covina, 2pm</em></h3>\nAlosta in Covina will have the game up on their screens and will be raffling off prizes throughout the day. Wear your Broncos or Panthers jersey and get $1 off your beers!\n<h3><strong>Tuning Fork Gastropub</strong>\n<em>Studio City, 2pm</em></h3>\nHead out to Tuning Fork in Studio City for the big game. They''ll have food specials, $5 beers, and $8 beer flights. Plus they''re hosting their 3rd annual All-or-Nothing Challenge, which means if you finish their epic $20 All-or-Nothing Burger in 5 minutes or less, you could win 2 Dodgers Tickets and the burger is on the house. Good thing they have some solid craft beers to wash it down with!\n<h3><strong>El Segundo Brewing Co</strong>\n<em>El Segundo, 2:30pm</em></h3>\nAt El Segundo Brewing, it''s not the Super Bowl, it''s the Dank Bowl. They have about 40 seats in their tasting room and one of those could be yours for the big game. They''ll have a party sub and some bar snacks available and all you have to do is commit to spending at least $40 throughout the game. And that shouldn''t be hard with all of their awesomely dank IPAs on tap. Email pete@elsegundobrewing.com to reserve your seat.\n<h3><strong>Draughts Restaurant &amp; Bar</strong>\n<em>Thousand Oaks, 3pm</em></h3>\nIf you find yourself in the Conejo Valley on Sunday, you''re gonna want to watch the game at Draughts in TO. Not only will they have the game on all 19 of their 50" flat screens, but they''ll also be one of the only places offering happy hour specials during the game. From 3-6pm, take advantage of $4 select pints, $7 select mugs, $12 select pitchers, $5 well drinks, $5 Jager shots, and 25% off all appetizers. They''ll also be having random giveaways throughout the game and a halftime raffle for a flat screen TV. With 45 taps recently pouring Topa Topa''s Chief Peak, Belching Beaver''s Peanut Butter Milk Stout, Noble Big Whig, and Rough Draft Weekday IPA, you really can''t go wrong.\n<h3><strong>The Pub at Golden Road</strong>\n<em>Burbank/Glendale, 3:25pm</em></h3>\nThe folks at Golden Road have a killer Super Bowl special planned for this Sunday. During the game enjoy a $25 all you can drink special along with some food specials like Santa Maria dry-rubbed tri tip sandwich on Foccacia w/ grilled onions and jalapenos. Pair that with a Wolf Among Weeds and you''ll forget you''re celebrating in an AB-InBev owned establishment.\n<h3><strong>The Fat Dog</strong>\n<em>Hollywood &amp; NoHo, 3:30pm</em></h3>\nOk this Hollywood &amp; North Hollywood spot isn''t pouring the types of beers you''re probably looking for. But there are definitely worse places to score craft beer around LA during the Super Bowl. They''ll have $3 pints and $5 surf vs turf food specials. If you go, be sure to ask your server about the #TheFatDogLA hashtag special too!\n<h3><strong>Kinetic Brewing Co</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 3:30pm</em></h3>\nKinetic is throwing the game up on their 12 foot screen, will be serving up hot wings, and will of course be pouring their beers for you to enjoy throughout the game. Lancaster, you know what to do!\n\n&nbsp;', '13 LA Craft Beer Spots to Watch the 2016 Super Bowl', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'craft-beer-super-bowl-la-2016', '', '', '2016-02-01 23:18:08', '2016-02-02 07:18:08', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1886', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1889, 4, '2016-02-02 00:01:52', '2016-02-02 08:01:52', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\n\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday February 1st to Sunday February 7th, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday February 2</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at</strong> <strong>Tony’s</strong>:<strong> Special Tapping of Cuvee De Tomme</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nTony''s is tapping Lost Abbey''s massive brown ale that is made from four fermentable sugars including malted barley, raisins, candy sugar and sour cherries, which gets fully fermented before being placed in bourbon barrels where the beer ages for one year with the sour sherries and wild brettanomyces yeast. 11% ABV,  $6.75 a pour.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday February 3</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Firkin Good Time with Wolf Creek at Crazy Harry''s Bar</strong>\n<em>Winnetka, 5pm</em></h3>\nCrazy Harry''s Bar is hosting a firkin good time with Wolf Creek with a special Belgium beer made with raspberries. And they''re bringing along some additional beers to give you an experience with some local flavor from just 20 minutes north.\n<h3><strong>Ritual Brewing Tap Takeover at Simmzy''s Manhattan Beach</strong>\n<em>Manhattan Beach, 6pm</em></h3>\nRedlands-based Ritual Brewing brings their beers all the way to Manhattan Beach for a special tap takeover. They''ll be tapping Hop-O-Matic (West Coast IPA), Love &amp; Malt (Brown Ale), Extra Red (American Red Ale), Hellion (Belgian Style Golden Ale) and Big Deluxe (Imperial Oat Stout and Gold Winner at the Great American Beer Festival).\n<h3><strong>Steal The Glass Night featuring Telegraph at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nThis week''s brewery is Telegraph, and their bringing  California Ale and Downtown Abbey. Have a pint and take home the glass!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday February 4</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>City Tavern DTLA''s 2nd Birthday w/ $2 Pints</strong>\n<em>Downtown LA, 4pm</em></h3>\nCity Tavern DTLA is blowing the candles out to honor two years open and celebrating with $2 pints of Ballast Point''s Mango Even Keel, Belching Beaver''s Peanut Butter Milk Stout, and more. Throw in $4 cocktails and you''ve got one hell of a birthday party.\n<h3><strong>Eagle Rock Tap Takeover at Blue Palms Brewhouse</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 4pm</em></h3>\nEagle Rock is swooping into Hollywood and taking over 6+ taps at Blue Palms, and will include beers such as Yearling Sour Red Ale, All Your Oat DIPA, and Populist IPA. One of LA''s most legit, longstanding breweries with one of LA''s most legit, longstanding beer bars. Sounds like a match made in heaven.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday February 5</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Power Plant TIPA - Day One at El Segundo Brewing</strong>\n<em>El Segundo, 12pm</em></h3>\nEl Segundo''s behemoth triple IPA makes its Day One release just in time to send up to The Bistro DIPA Fest (their Hammerland won gold last year!). But the release is also just in time for you to be able to have some of the freshest Power Plant TIPA for bottle or case purchases. It''s $10 for a bottle and $100 for a case, with a 2 case limit. Great way to celebrate Super Bowl weekend!\n<h3><strong>First Friday Sour Beer &amp; Cheese Pairing w/ Vagabond Cheese at Buzz Wine Beer Shop</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nVagabond Cheese and Buzz are kicking off their First Friday series with a special sour beer and cheese pairing that you won''t wanna miss! The flight of 5 beers from Phantom Carriage Brewery, Brouwers Verzet, Paradox Beer Company, Almanac Beer Co. &amp; Cascade Brewing will be paired with 5 cheeses and Vagabond owner Alex Ourieff will be on hand to chat more about cheese, beer, and everything in between. <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/first-friday-sour-beer-cheese-pairing-w-vagabond-cheese-cheesebeerscheers-tickets-20974898486" target="_blank">Grab your tickets in advance here</a>.\n<h3><strong>Firestone Walker Milk &amp; Cookies Night at Eagle Rock Lounge</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 7pm</em></h3>\nIt''ll be a night of delicious beer and treats provided by the fantastic Firestone Walker and their Nitro Merlin milk stout paired with specialty Brown Butter Cookie Co. cookies. Who doesn''t love a little beer dessert to end the day?\n<h3><strong>First Friday with Perennial Ales at The Doughroom</strong>\n<em>Palms, 7pm</em></h3>\nThe Doughroom will be pouring 4 rare beers from Perennial Ales including Meriweather, Hommelbier, Saison de Lis, and Abraxas. It''s not too often you see these beers around LA, so you probably don''t want to miss this one.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday February 6</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Dankbowl 2016 at El Segundo Brewing</strong>\n<em>El Segundo, 6pm</em></h3>\nIt''s only right for the IPA masters at El Segundo organize a special tasting of 6 IPAs in their prep for the Bistro DIPA Fest. With the release of a brand new DIPA, Hop Plunge, fresh Power Plant AND a brand new variation called NUCLEAR Power Plant, El Segundo will have a few structured flights (see below), along with tasting notes and sheets for you to take your own. Then, cast your vote for El Segundo''s best DIPA!\n\n<strong>Flight #1 - Power Plant - ye be my friend</strong>\nSpark Plug\nHop Plunge\nPower Plant\nNuclear Power Plant\n\n<strong>Flight # 2 - Give me ALL the DIPA''s you have</strong>\nTwo 5 Left\nHop Tanker\nHop Plunge\nHammerland\nPower Plant\n<h3><strong>Lost in the Woods Los Angeles: Wood-Aged Beer Release Party at Peddler''s Fork</strong>\n<em>Calabasas, 7pm</em></h3>\nNew Belgium is honoring their most celebrated wood-aged beers La Folie and Transatlantique Kriek with a special 3-course food pairing at the awesome Peddler''s Fork in Calabasas. Enjoy a farm-to-table meal paired with the two rare New Belgium sours and other NB beers like Citradelic IPA. They''ll have live music in the background and gift bags for the first 50 guests as well as some limited edition New Belgium swag. This is a very exclusive event and tickets are going fast <a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/e/lost-in-the-woods-los-angeles-wood-aged-beer-release-party-tickets-19505176508?aff=es2" target="_blank">so grab yours today</a>!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday February 7</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Super Bowl 50</strong>\n<em>Various Locations, 3pm</em></h3>\nFrom The Doughroom and El Segundo to the west to The Pub at Golden Road and Alosta Brewing Co. to the east, there are plenty of places to enjoy craft beer in LA for Super Bowl 50. <a href="http://hoppedla.com/craft-beer-super-bowl-la-2016/" target="_blank">Check out our latest guide and start planning your Super Bowl Sunday!</a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of February 1, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-feb-1', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1889', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1929, 4, '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\n\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday February 8th to Sunday February 14th, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday February 9</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Three Weavers Tap Takeover at Darryl’s Couch</strong>\n<em>Camarillo, 5:30pm</em></h3>\nThree Weavers is taking over the taps at Darryl’s Couch in Camarillo and bringing along six of their awesome brews, including their latest collaboration with Noble Ale Works, The Messenger IPA!\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony’s with Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em><h3>\nPhantom Carriage beers arrive at Tony’s Darts Away for the first time and we are all stoked! They’ll be pouring Broadacres, Muis, Dolores, and possibly a few other beers. If you love sours and haven’t made your way to Phantom Carriage’s South Bay brewery yet, this is a great chance to try what they’re brewing up.\n', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of February 8, 2016', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1929', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1930, 4, '2015-03-24 10:04:08', '2015-03-24 17:04:08', 'Welcome back, hop heads.\n\nWhen I brought you the <a href="http://hoppedla.com/best-beer-bars-in-the-sfv-west/" target="_blank">best beer bars of the West SFV</a> a few weeks ago, I was actually quite impressed at the number of craft beer destinations that were populating my list. However, I knew that it was only the beginning, because before craft beer won the west - it conquered the east.\n\nThe East SFV is a growing mecca for craft beer in the Valley given that the first craft breweries and tasting rooms have opened up and Sherman Oaks has a new stretch of spots along Ventura Blvd., dubbed "restaurant row". So, without further adieu, let''s see where you can dive head first into hops east of the dreaded 405.\n\n<em>Last Updated: January 2016</em>\n<h2>Breweries</h2>\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east9.png">\n</a><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east9.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-635" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east9.png" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east9" width="600" height="398" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.macleodale.com/" target="_blank">MacLeod Ale Brewing Co.</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/14741+Calvert+St,+Van+Nuys,+CA+91411/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c29709034dad59:0x84437b2b008a2c92?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwir7P6jvozKAhUCwmMKHR4rCAQQ8gEIGzAA" target="_blank">14741 Calvert St, Van Nuys, CA 91411</a></em>\n\nMacLeod Ale is one of the <a href="http://hoppedla.com/first-breweries-sfv/" target="_blank">first micro-breweries to open in the Valley</a> after Pac City, but pulls off their launch much cleaner. Specializing in cask-conditioned British ales, they make the Hopped LA list due to their expansive tasting room featuring games, darts, homemade crackers made from spent grain, and bring-your-own cheese nights; and of course, their ability to brew their ales right here at home.\n<h3><img class="alignnone wp-image-1638" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/brewyard-brewing.jpg" alt="brewyard-brewing" width="600" height="338" /><strong><a href="http://www.brewyardbeercompany.com/" target="_blank">Brewyard Beer Company</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Brewyard+Beer+Company/@34.167286,-118.292298,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x2508ed95754cf04b?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjZ9Kzo09rJAhVD0WMKHbnbBbUQ_BIIbjAK" target="_blank">906 Western Ave, Glendale, CA 91201</a></em>\n\nBrewyard Beer Co. fills the void between the SFV and the rest of LA with a great variety of styles on tap Wednesday through Sunday each week. The offerings range from their Black Sunrise black lager and Split Shift IPL to the Soul Cal California Common and Tropico Saison w/ passion fruit. So, yeah, you can say there is something for everybody.\n<h3><img class="alignnone wp-image-1633" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/san-fernando-brewing.jpg" alt="san-fernando-brewing" width="600" height="338" /><strong><a href="http://www.sanfernandobrewingcompany.com/#san-fernando-brewing-co" target="_blank">San Fernando Brewing Co.</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/San+Fernando+Brewing+Company/@34.2833695,-118.4320611,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xb1dcdf89db38dc9e?sa=X&amp;sqi=2&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi9q4CD09nJAhUUU2MKHXLvBa8Q_BIIdTAK" target="_blank">425 Park Ave, San Fernando, CA 91340</a></em>\n\nThe Valley welcomed another addition to the list of new breweries and San Fernando Brewing Co. is doing it right. With five core beers, upcoming seasonal offerings, and an open taproom that overlooks the brewing operation, you feel like a part of the action while sipping some great beer.\n<h2>Beer Bars/Tasting Rooms</h2>\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/public-school-818-3.png">\n</a><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/public-school-818-3.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1221" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/public-school-818-3.png" alt="public-school-818-3" width="600" height="450" /></a><strong><a href="https://www.psontap.com/locations/ps818/" target="_blank">Public School 818</a> </strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/15300+Ventura+Blvd,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91403/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c297eb1b446bf9:0xbf3946b571c15e11?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjVus6uvozKAhWFKGMKHds-CxQQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">15300 Ventura Blvd, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403</a></em>\n\n<a title="Now Open: Public School 818 in Sherman Oaks" href="http://hoppedla.com/now-open-public-school-818-sherman-oaks/" target="_blank">Public School 818 opened in early March</a> and so far the buzz has been good. They kicked off their opening with a tap list that could satisfy the hop heads, but I wouldn''t count on it being a go-to spot if you''re looking for IPAs. Though they do have a great house IPA brewed by Fig Mountain called School House IPA that is worth a try.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east1.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-627" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east1.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east1" width="600" height="450" /></a><a href="http://www.bluedogbeertavern.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Blue Dog Beer Tavern</strong></a></h3>\n<a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Blue+Dog+Beer+Tavern/@34.1518985,-118.4659804,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x1e28f96e498ab160?sa=X&amp;sqi=2&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiPvf_EvozKAhVD6WMKHVq5Do0Q_BIIigEwDg" target="_blank"><em>4524 Saugus Ave, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403</em></a>\n\nBlue Dog and I have some history, and while their weekly tap list could use tweaking here and there, I have no bad things to say about their Chi Chi Burger. But this is a beer blog, so enough about that. Blue Dog was one of the first to bring craft beer to this little pocket and remains a very popular hang out, especially if your pup is tagging along. Hop heads can be satisfied by Green Flash West Coast IPA on tap and some different bottle selections. But that Chi Chi Burger though...\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east2.jpg">\n</a><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east2.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-628" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east2.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east2" width="600" height="400" /></a><a href="http://www.onthethirty.com/" target="_blank"><strong>On The Thirty</strong></a>\n\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/14622+Ventura+Blvd+%23112,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91403/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c297c5762ad0eb:0x1bf56e6c5b6661e1?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjVu_76vozKAhVFy2MKHSl8DG4Q8gEIGzAA" target="_blank">14622 Ventura Blvd #112, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403</a></em>\n\nLocated along Sherman Oaks'' restaurant row, On The Thirty brings a more casual vibe to the neighborhood and thirty types of craft beer to your palate. The food specialty here is pizza, but check their menu for more tasty items like the Lobster Roll. Pair them with The Dudes Double Trunk or El Segundo''s White Dog IPA while you catch the NFL Sunday Ticket this season. I''ll be guy in the corner pissed off at his fantasy team.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east14.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-640" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east14.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east14" width="600" height="319" /></a><b><a href="http://tippleandbrine.com/" target="_blank">Tipple &amp; Brine</a> (Temporary Closed)</b></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/14633+Ventura+Blvd,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91403/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c297c584c797af:0x4c7a238cae62cdfa?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjU2s-Hv4zKAhVWz2MKHctYBJsQ8gEIKDAB" target="_blank">14633 Ventura Blvd, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403</a></em>\n\nAnother spot along restaurant row, Tipple and Brine focuses on quality, local fare and that mission translates to the beers. You won''t find a huge tap list here, but you''ll be able to order something decent to go with your oysters. For an after-dinner libation, head out back and upstairs to Tunnel Bar Cocktail Lounge which sits on top of T&amp;B.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east13.jpg">\n</a><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east13.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-641" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east13.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east13" width="600" height="417" /></a><a href="http://www.theoakstavern.com/The_Oaks_Tavern/Home.html" target="_blank"><strong>The Oaks Tavern</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/13625+Moorpark+St,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91423/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2962f18d27ecd:0xb9817d30fa20d0f6?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwixwZfMv4zKAhUT02MKHRzqAeAQ8gEIGzAA" target="_blank">13625 Moorpark St, Sherman Oaks, CA 91423</a></em>\n\nDuring my time residing in Sherman Oaks, this space underwent a few different changes, finally landing onto a craft beer concept that makes me resent leaving that area before it opened. The Oaks is super casual, featuring darts, pool, positive social interactions, and a wall full o'' taps. Tuesdays and Thursdays are karaoke nights, so grab a pint of Belching Beaver''s Beavers Milk and belt out your best rendition of "Don''t Stop Believin''".\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/tipsycow.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-712" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/tipsycow.jpg" alt="tipsycow" width="600" height="338" /></a><a href="http://tipsycowla.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Tipsy Cow</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/15005+Ventura+Blvd,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91403/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c297c17415fd67:0x68d4b8a9395d8d75?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjerMjlv4zKAhUFLmMKHVbmCdYQ8gEIGzAA" target="_blank">15005 Ventura Blvd, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403</a></em>\n\nAnother new spot along restaurant row, Tipsy Cow is all about burgers, beer, and milkshakes. In fact, the decor almost reminds me of an upscale diner. They are tapping into the local brew scene, as well as the surrounding VTA and SD counties, so the usual suspects can be found behind the bar. Additionally, those milkshakes can be made boozy, so if you''re not feelin'' like beer, you have options. Did I mention the burgers are grand?\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1257 size-full" style="border: 4px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east" width="600" height="336" />\n</a><strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/hob1979" target="_blank">House of Billiards</a> </strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/14662+Ventura+Blvd,+Van+Nuys,+CA+91403/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c297c5a119896f:0x94f04536ab384da9?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiM3OLiwIzKAhUOyGMKHfjIAYwQ8gEIGzAA" target="_blank">14662 Ventura Blvd, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403</a></em>\n\nI don''t know what happened to the House of Billiards that used to exist when I lived down the street from it, but the Bud Light has been replaced with the good stuff, albeit it may still be served in Bud Light-branded pint glasses. When I heard that they were pouring craft here, I couldn''t believe it, but the most recent Untappd activity tells me that Noble''s Citra Yum Yum TIPA and Enjoy By 4/20/15 are gracing the beer taps and that''s all I need to know.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east3.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-629" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east3.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east3" width="600" height="299" /></a><a href="http://www.thewoodmanla.com/" target="_blank"><strong>The </strong><strong>Woodman</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/13615+Ventura+Blvd,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91423/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c29628dce80545:0x8a73f638afae1cc2?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwinudGOwozKAhVO4GMKHR1RAJkQ8gEIGzAA" target="_blank">13615 Ventura Blvd, Sherman Oaks, CA 91423</a></em>\n\nThe Woodman is another new gastropub along "The Row", and came from the owners of The Surly Goat in West Hollywood. Even though it''s not owned by The Goat Group anymore, they still pour some serious beer. The food is approachable, yet upscale like rabbit empanadas and Thai coconut curry mussels.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east5.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-631 size-full" style="border: 4px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east5.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east5" width="550" height="335" />\n</a><a href="http://thelocalpeasants.com/" target="_blank"><strong>The Local Peasant</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/14058+Ventura+Blvd,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91423/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2962cd1370eb7:0x4da79b88f1264eac?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiCz8WiwozKAhVM8GMKHX3dBaYQ8gEIJTAB" target="_blank">14058 Ventura Blvd, Sherman Oaks, CA 91423</a></em>\n\nThe Sherman Oaks counterpart is, of course, the original and still holds that same exclusive charm it did when it first opened. Providing a more intimate setting than it''s west Valley location, you''ll still find your favorite food items and a list of beers that''ll suit your tastes. Currently, you can sip on Lagunitas Little Sumpin'' Extra DIPA and Deschutes Fresh Squeezed IPA to name a couple.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east8.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-634" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east8.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east8" width="600" height="332" /></a><a href="http://www.boneyardbistro.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Boneyard Bistro</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/13539+Ventura+Blvd,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91423/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c296289b5ec875:0x2c95711e9fc724e0?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiNnIizwozKAhUT7GMKHTRJDSgQ8gEIGzAA" target="_blank">13539 Ventura Blvd, Sherman Oaks, CA 91423</a></em>\n\nAnother popular Sherman Oaks spot, Boneyard can get pretty crowded - and for good reason. They have great (but expensive) food, a full bar with experienced bartenders, and an impressive haul of craft beer. If you dare see Pliny the Elder on tap in this neck of the woods, it will more than likely be here. Currently, they''re pouring Noble Ale Works'' Chinook Showers from their limited release Showers series and Eel River''s Emerald Triangle.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east6.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-632" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east6.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east6" width="600" height="400" /></a><strong><a href="http://tuningforkgastropub.com/" target="_blank">Tuning Fork</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/12051+Ventura+Pl,+Studio+City,+CA+91604/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2bdfd6ce3dbaf:0x2801647eda61fc78?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiyjN6-wozKAhUUHmMKHbJsBNMQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">12051 Ventura Pl, Studio City, CA 91604</a></em>\n\nTuning Fork is a nice gem in Studio City that opened up a few years ago. It gained a following fairly quickly and it''s now serving the likes of celebs and locals alike. Their beer selection is pretty big, but it''s mostly in bottles and cans. Not a bad thing, however, as that selection alone presents many Golden Road, Pizza Port, and Lagunitas options. So, order an All or Nothing Burger and a Wolf Among Weeds, and we''ll stick a fork in ya.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east10.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1259" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east10.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east" width="600" height="399" /></a><strong><a href="http://laureltavern.com/" target="_blank">Laurel Tavern</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/11938+Ventura+Blvd,+Studio+City,+CA+91604/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2be080f05596b:0xa0b6d05c1b8692cd?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjJ4JXNwozKAhVU5WMKHQv7CcAQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">11938 Ventura Blvd. Studio City, Ca 91604</a></em>\n\nI left Laurel off the list intentionally last time, simply because I felt as though it wasn''t a craft beer destination. And while I''m still on the fence about it, I caved because, yeah, I can see people coming here for the beer. Not that your selection is phenomenal, but it''s diverse enough to satisfy most palates. Hey, for you hop heads, you''re getting Ballast Point''s Sculpin and Golden Road''s Wolf Among Weeds, which ain''t a bad thing.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east7.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-633" style="border: 4px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east7.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east7" width="600" height="450" />\n</a><strong><a href="http://www.stoutburgersandbeers.com/" target="_blank">Stout Burgers and Beer</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/11262+Ventura+Blvd,+Studio+City,+CA+91604/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2be1475cbf69f:0xad5cd88556f96ec4?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjT3YTYwozKAhUM9GMKHZVPA4oQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">11262 Ventura Blvd, Studio City, CA 91604</a></em>\n\nStout makes our list as they offer a fairly comfortable selection of craft beer on tap, making it possible for you to find something you like. Whether it be as solid as a Stone IPA or the off-chance that Avery''s Maharaja is on that night, you''ll hopefully end the night with a stomach full of burgers and beer. And what could honestly be better than that? Well, sex, of course.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/the-bellwether.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1645" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/the-bellwether.jpg" alt="the-bellwether" width="700" height="466" /></a><strong><a href="http://thebellwetherla.com/" target="_blank">The Bellwether</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/The+Bellwether/@34.1466478,-118.4215995,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xa2b79ecba01a6597?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiR5pfc4trJAhUBwmMKHZoCAVEQ_BIIdzAK" target="_blank">13251 Ventura Blvd, Studio City, CA 91604</a></em>\n\nThe Fathers Office alum set their sights on Studio City and opened The Bellwether in an attractive location on Ventura Blvd. There''s a strong focus on cocktails here, but there is plenty of beer to keep the enthusiasts satisfied with offerings from Craftsman, Hangar 24, and Three Weavers.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/formans-tavern.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1649" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/formans-tavern.jpg" alt="formans-tavern" width="700" height="465" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.formansla.com/" target="_blank">Forman''s Tavern</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=the+forman+la&amp;oq=the+forman+la&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57j0l2j69i61l3.1880j0j4&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;es_sm=91&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=the+forman+la&amp;rflfq=1&amp;rlha=0&amp;tbm=lcl&amp;rlfi=hd:;si:1013143609108019037" target="_blank">10149 Riverside Dr, Los Angeles, CA 91602</a></em>\n\nOne more Valley location rounds out the list, and it''s Forman''s Tavern which took the old Lucy''s 51 space in Toluca Lake. Sitting close to Timmy Nolan''s, this area of the east Valley is actually a destination for craft beer. And with taps pouring Smog City, Kinetic, and Modern Times, it''s a good one at that.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1260" style="border: 4px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east.png" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east" width="600" height="450" />\n</a><strong><a href="http://www.districtpubnoho.com/" target="_blank">District Pub</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/5249+Lankershim+Blvd,+North+Hollywood,+CA+91601/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c295f186358b77:0x2e3ef8103cac97d8?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjd4tfmwozKAhUBIWMKHWpVDSoQ8gEIJjAB" target="_blank">5249 Lankershim Blvd. North Hollywood, Ca 91601</a></em>\n\nI can''t neglect NoHo, because they actually have some places worth checking out. It sports at lease 24 taps with some bottled selections as well. Bring beer lovers of all styles here because the selection is vast. Sign me up for the Firestone Walker Union Jack or Epic''s Hopulent IPA and you wouldn''t get a complaint out of me. Once you''re done here, it''s best to move on to the nearby Brickyard Pub.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east12.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1261" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east12.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east" width="600" height="400" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.brickyardnoho.com/" target="_blank">The Brickyard Pub</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/11130+W+Magnolia+Blvd,+North+Hollywood,+CA+91601/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c295f39608dc5f:0x2f653ccf97511f35?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjG5_z2wozKAhUHwWMKHbPWCisQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">11130 Magnolia Blvd. North Hollywood, Ca 91601</a></em>\n\nAnother craft beer spot in NoHo, The Brickyard Pub is a place to grab a cold one and break the rack on the pool table. It''s deemed "not your average dive bar", and they''re right. Both of their locations (the other is in Hollywood) boast a wide selection of beer and it''s a great place for gateway craft beer drinkers to try some new things. Worst case scenario, you''re drinking a Racer 5 or Green Flash West Coast.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/simmzys-burbank-beer.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1318" style="border: 4px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/simmzys-burbank-beer.jpg" alt="simmzys-burbank-beer" width="600" height="401" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.simmzys.com/home/location" target="_blank">Simmzy''s Pub</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/3000+W+Olive+Ave,+Burbank,+CA+91505/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2bfc566355941:0xaf63b51eebcccd8e?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwio1qeAw4zKAhUK3mMKHTKBD4IQ8gEILzAC" target="_blank">3000 W. Olive Ave. Burbank, Ca 91505</a></em>\n\nSimmzy''s Pub is Burbank''s new kid on the block and it''s certainly helping to make the city a small destination area for craft beer. Simmzy''s is bright, open, and very inviting making it an approachable place to please your palate. They''re pouring house beers contract-brewed by Golden Road, while serving the likes of King Harbor IPA, Ballast Point''s Grapefruit Sculpin, and their East to West (which is phenomenal). One thing to note is that Simmzy''s is kid friendly and even has a separate menu for the little ones.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east10.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-649" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east10.png" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east10" width="640" height="482" />\n</a><a href="http://tonysda.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Tony''s Darts Away</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/1710+W+Magnolia+Blvd,+Burbank,+CA+91506/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2956130ee4d69:0xf08c3273a1e75eb3?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwipyK2Mw4zKAhVDKWMKHXIKDn8Q8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">1710 W Magnolia Blvd, Burbank, CA 91506</a></em>\n\nTony''s is a no-brainer if you are a fan of LA craft beer, and it''s my pleasure if I''m introducing this spot to you for the first time. Before it became the TDA that you see today, it used to be a dive bar of the same name. LA beer dude, Tony Yanow, took over the space, kept the name (coincidentally the same as his), and gave craft beer a new life in Los Angeles. Specializing in California brews and plump, signature sausages, Tony''s Darts Away is your friendly, neighborhood hangout where friends meet friends and strangers become friends. Make it a point to stop by on their yearly anniversary parties where Golden Road brews up a special to-die-for "Darts Away IPA".\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east11.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-650" style="border: 4px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east11.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east11" width="600" height="399" />\n</a><a href="http://www.storytavernburbank.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Story Tavern</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/150+S+San+Fernando+Blvd,+Burbank,+CA+91502/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c29551267e3c8f:0xb86e49cbf2317fa6?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjY5K2Vw4zKAhXJKGMKHe1kAhUQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">150 S San Fernando Blvd, Burbank, CA 91502</a></em>\n\nThis craftsman-style pub sits on San Fernando Blvd. just a stone''s throw away from downtown Burbank. It''s also just down the road from a Gordon Biersch Brewery Restaurant (but who cares about that). Story Tavern presents itself like an ordinary pub that boasts such fare as Shepard''s Pie, and a handful of beer engines that pump from nearby casks. Don''t worry, though, as the craft beer taps have a few different locations behind the bar giving you over 20 options to choose from. Make this a stop when you head out this way to visit Tony''s Darts Away.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east16.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-682" style="border: 4px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east16.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east16" width="600" height="400" /></a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/glendaletap" target="_blank"><strong>Glendale Tap</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/4227+San+Fernando+Rd,+Glendale,+CA+91204/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c0e42db19795:0x34d2edf15ddddc52?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiv5tiew4zKAhUP4WMKHSjcB8EQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">4227 San Fernando Rd, Glendale, CA 91204</a></em>\n\nGlendale Tap opened a couple years ago to an area of LA that wasn''t ripe with craft beer bars, aside from the Pub at Golden Rub and Links &amp; Hops. Still going strong today, Glendale Tap is armed with 52 taps and pouring your favorites from Ballast Point, El Segundo Brewing Co., Deschutes, and more.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east12.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-651" style="border: 4px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/best-beer-bars-sfv-east12.png" alt="best-beer-bars-sfv-east12" width="600" height="400" />\n</a><strong>Honorable Mention: <a href="http://hoppedla.com/valley-beverage-co/" target="_blank">Valley Beverage Co.</a> </strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/14901+Ventura+Blvd,+Sherman+Oaks,+CA+91403/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c297c157324b61:0x7aeac4b4a8366dca?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwiz2Ky0w4zKAhVWz2MKHctYBJsQ8gEIGzAA" target="_blank">14901 Ventura Blvd, Sherman Oaks, CA 91403</a></em>\n\nYup, it''s another bottle shop. But it''s not just any other bottle shop - it''s the giant of the east SFV where Green Jug is that of the west. Any trip to Valley Beverage Co. will ensure you don''t leave empty handed as their beer selection is fantastic. They are also one of the few places in town to grab bottles of the hard-to-find whales that grace the shelves in the back (meaning you need to ask for them). The downside is that EVERYBODY knows when the shipments come in, which means if you don''t get here fast then that beer you wanted...is already gone. Don''t worry, wait a few days until Vendome of Toluca Lake gets the same beer in and you''ll probably get your hands on it. <a href="http://hoppedla.com/vendome-liquors-toluca-lake/" target="_blank">Get our take on Vendome in our "#InsideTheBottleShop" series.</a>\n\nIt seems I''ve already done some good today for all of my Valley kids out there. I''ve laid out the road map for you, and now leave you to find the hoppy treasures that await. So, go forth and prosper, my friends. In other words, GET HOPPED.\n\nDid I miss a good spot? I''m definitely not above correction. Alternatively, did I introduce you to a new place you can''t wait to check out? Whatever the case, let me know in the comments or tweet at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. Thanks for reading!', 'Your Guide to the Best Craft Beer Spots in the East SFV', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-craft-beer-spots-sfv-east', '', '', '2015-03-24 10:04:08', '2015-03-24 17:04:08', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=626', 0, 'post', '', 14);
