(1936, 4, '2015-06-15 23:04:08', '2015-06-16 06:04:08', 'Ready for <a href="http://labeerweek.org/" target="_blank">LA Beer Week 2015</a>? We sure are! If it feels like it came a little bit earlier this year, you''re right. The LA Brewer''s Guild has moved up the date from its original September kickoff up to June. And frankly, we couldn''t be happier!\n\nAnd once again, <a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/" target="_blank">the official LA Beer Week event calendar</a> is chock full of awesome events each day of the week. If you don''t know what you''re looking for, it can be kind of intimidating. That''s why we put together this handy guide of what we feel are the best events of the week. I totally encourage you to <a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/" target="_blank">browse the full event calendar</a>, but if you''re looking for a shortcut, you''ve come to the right place. Here''s our guide for the best events of LA Beer Week 2015:\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday, June 19th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1615669838689098/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1367 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/labwpreviewflyer-e1434434761866.jpg" alt="LABW Preview + Hoppywood Flyer" width="450" height="450" />\nLABW Preview at City Tavern w/ Karl Strauss &amp; Hopped L</a><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1615669838689098/" target="_blank">A</a></strong></h3>\n<em>Culver City, 6pm</em>\n\nOk, so technically this event is before the official start of LA Beer Week, and we''re a bit biased since it''s one of our own events, but it''s going to be super fun and you''re gonna want to put this on your calendar. You may have heard <a href="http://hoppedla.com/hoppywood-and-bine/" target="_blank">we recently teamed up with Karl Strauss to brew a special LABW collab beer, Hoppywood &amp; Bine</a>. Well on Friday, June 19th we officially release the beer to the public. The Karl Strauss team is coming up from San Diego with their Brewmaster, Paul Segura, a bunch of merch, and several other awesome, hard to find beers. Plus it doesn''t get much better than City Tavern, so this will be a great way to start out your 2015 LA Beer Week!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday, June 20th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/653635338116488/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1355" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/lawbkickoff-e1434329723648.jpg" alt="LA Beer Week Kickoff Fest" width="700" height="289" />\nLA Beer Week Kickoff Festival at Exposition Park</a></strong></h3>\n<em>Exposition Park, 12pm</em>\n\nWhenever anyone asks me my favorite beer event of the year, my answer is ALWAYS the LA Beer Week Brewer''s Guild Kickoff Festival. It''s the perfect mix of super local breweries, some of the best beers they brew, day drinking, music, beer education, food trucks, and legitimate craft beer lovers. This year is at a new location, and I have a feeling it''s going to be even more epic than last year. <a href="http://labeerweek.org/tickets/" target="_blank">Grab your tickets now for $45 because they''re not selling them at the gate!</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday, June 21st</strong></span></h2>\n<iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/127970104" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe>\n<h3><strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/820734644669933/" target="_blank">Cask &amp; Ye Shall Receive 2.0</a></strong></h3>\n<em>Van Nuys, 1pm</em>\n\nMacLeod is one of the most unique breweries in Southern California. If you haven''t visited their tasting room, tried one of the beers on cask/tap at your local beer bar, or picked up one of their newly released bottles, then you''re just missing out, man. Luckily for us, their 1 year anniversary and LA Beer Week fall during the same time, so they''re throwing together something extra special for the occasion. The event will showcase a number of their own delicious traditional British style cask ales as well as specialty casks from over 14 different LA breweries. Get unlimited pours and choose from one of three sessions: 1-4pm (which also features a panel discussion with Tomm Carroll, Andy Black, Evan Price, Aaron Champion, and others), 4-7pm, or 7-10pm. <a href="https://macleodale.ticketbud.com/cask" target="_blank">Pick up tickets for $50 here</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Monday, June 22nd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/22/day-one-mayberry-ipa-release" target="_blank"><strong>Day One: Mayberry IPA Release</strong></a></strong></h3>\n<em>El Segundo - 12pm</em>\n\nMayberry is one of the best IPAs coming out of Los Angeles these days and El Segundo is doing one of their famous Day One releases right in the middle of LA Beer Week. That means they bottle the beer and have it ready for you to pick up mere hours later. It doesn''t get much fresher than that! And it doesn''t get much better than fresh Mayberry.\n<h3><strong><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1062335497129323/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1387" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/threeweavers-e1434558846803.jpg" alt="threeweavers" width="500" height="322" />\nPink Boots LA Takeover of Three Weavers Brewing Company</a></strong></h3>\n<em>Inglewood - 4pm</em>\n\nThere are several reason why this event needs to be on your calendar. The <a href="https://www.facebook.com/pinkbootsLA" target="_blank">Pink Boots Society</a> is a totally worthy cause, Three Weavers brews some seriously kick-ass beers, and their Inglewood location is the perfect spot for a summer evening drinking sesh. Plus, have you seen that beer list?? You''ll get to try two brand new Three Weavers collaboration beers - Return of Sassy IPA with soon-to-be-opened Arts District Brewing and We Saw Them Coming Watermelon Saison with new-to-LA 21st Amendment. Not to mention those guest taps: 21st Amendment''s Down to Earth Session IPA, Arizona Wilderness'' Pine Mountain Sour, Beachwood''s Hopular Mechanics IPA, Drake''s Omega Session, Highland Park''s Bonkers IPA, among many others. Tickets are $20 and benefit the Pink Boots Society Scholarship Fund. <a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/e/pink-boots-takeover-of-three-weavers-tickets-17415386891" target="_blank">Grab yours today!\n\n</a>\n\n<a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/25/kick-the-keg-night" target="_blank"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1368" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/kickthekeg-e1434429450507.jpg" alt="City Tavern Kick the Keg" width="300" height="420" /></strong></a>\n<h3><a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/22/kick-the-keg" target="_blank"><strong>Kick the Keg at City Tavern Culver City</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Culver City - 6pm</em>\n\nBack again this year is City Tavern''s fun as hell Kick the Keg event. Their Culver City outpost is featuring the best brews of the west side and a few from outside LA, including 22 kegs from breweries like Strand, Smog City, Phantom Carriage, Monkish, King Harbor, Golden Road, Firestone Walker, El Segundo, Drakes, Congregation Ale House, and Ballast Point. First keg to kick gets crowned king or queen of the tavern. Come on out and show the west side what''s up!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday, June 23rd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1354" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/LAS-TOP-HOPS-Social-Post.png" alt="LA''S TOP HOPS Social Post" width="560" height="315" />\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/481082658708035/" target="_blank">LA''s Top Hops Presented by HoppedLA.com at Crazy Harry''s Bar</a></strong></h3>\n<em>Winnetka - 5pm</em>\n\nOk another biased selection, but on Tuesday the 23rd we''re throwing a special LA Beer Week IPA Night at our favorite Valley beer bar, Crazy Harry''s in Winnetka. This is a totally no-frills event featuring a bunch of delicious hoppy beers that this part of LA just doesn''t see on tap very often - if ever. You can definitely expect to see our Hopped LA / Karl Strauss LABW collaboration IPL, Hoppywood &amp; Bine, accompanied by IPAs from Four Sons, El Segundo, Noble Ale Works, Strand, Three Weavers, and more! PLUS we''ll be releasing our very first shirt honoring the killer group of breweries we have here in LA. Details to come, but you''re not gonna want to miss it.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday, June 24th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/24/meeting-of-the-guilds-lasfsd" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1362" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/meetingoftheguilds2015.png" alt="Meeting of the Guilds 2015" width="600" height="600" />\nMeeting of the Guilds at Naja''s Place</a></strong></h3>\n<em>Redondo Beach - 6pm</em>\n\nThe Meeting of the Guilds has a new home! If you''re wondering the cause of my excitement it''s not because I don''t like the previous year''s venue, Mohawk Bend. Quite the contrary actually. It''s just that the LA Beer scene has grown so big that this event needed a larger space to accommodate all the breweries from the 3 different Brewers Guilds along with all the thirsty drinkers that enjoy them. This is one of the most fun events of the week, allowing us locals to try some SF and SD beers that we don''t normally see in these parts alongside some of our favorite LA beers. The voting aspect of it is always a bit of a joke (the home team always wins), but this is a great event to come out to the South Bay, show your support, and drink some amazing beers.\n\n<strong><a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/24/california-brewmasters-photo-safari" target="_blank">California BrewMasters Photo Safari</a></strong>\n\n<em>Carson - 6pm</em>\n\n<strong>Beer Blogger Bonus!</strong> Our fellow LA beer blogger, Nick Gingold of <a href="http://www.cabrewmasters.com/" target="_blank">California BrewMasters</a>, is teaming up with local brewery tours company, <a href="http://labeerhop.com/" target="_blank">LA Beer Hop</a>, to offer a special edition of their South Bay tour which includes beer photography instruction from the pro beer photographer himself. This will be a great opportunity to brush up on your beer photography skills and learn directly from Nick, who just wrapped up a job as the official beer photographer of the Firestone Walker Invitational Beer Festival a couple weeks ago. The tour starts and ends at Phantom Carriage and will hit Monkish and Smog City over 3-4 hours and will also include beer flights at each brewery. I couldn''t find a ticket link, but it looks like tickets cost $50, so just <a href="http://labeerhop.com/contact" target="_blank">hit up LA Brew Hop</a> to get signed up.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday, June 25th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/25/kick-the-keg-night" target="_blank"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1368" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/kickthekeg-e1434429450507.jpg" alt="City Tavern Kick the Keg" width="300" height="420" />\nKick the Keg at City Tavern DTLA</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Downtown LA - 6pm</em>\n\nThis is the east side version of City Tavern''s Kick the Keg event, going down at their awesome Downtown LA location. You''ll have a little more room to spread out at this newer spot and drink some of the best of what the east side and greater LA breweries have to offer. Choose from 28 beers made by breweries like Absolution, Angel City, Ballast Point, Bootlegger''s, Cismontane, Eagle Rock, Firestone Walker, Golden Road, Ladyface, Noble Ale Works, Ohana, Ritual, and Telegraph. Same rules apply - whichever keg kicks first gets crowned the king or queen of the tavern, so show up and place your vote(s)!\n<h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/920874401268787/" target="_blank"><strong>\nMeasure Your Head: An Adventure Through Flights of Mixed Fermentation Beer at Barbara''s at the Brewery</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Lincoln Heights - 6pm</em>\n\nIt''s not very often you''ll see us hop heads getting super deep into things like yeast, bacteria, and fermentation, but this event is wayyy too unique to pass up. First the setting: Barbara''s at the Brewery, a really cool little beer bar outside of DTLA that just doesn''t get as much love as it should. Then, the players: Mark Jilg from Craftsman, Henry Nguyen from Monkish, and Bob Kunz from Highland Park Brewery, who are some of the most forward-thinking and unique brewers in the area. They''re getting together and walking through beer flights and talking about the effects of mixed fermentation on the beer''s end result. This will be one of the neatest educational events of LA Beer Week, <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/measure-your-head-an-adventure-with-flights-of-beer-tickets-17345885009" target="_blank">so be sure you grab your $20 ticket to either Flight #1 at 6:30pm or Flight #2 at 7:30pm</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday, June 26th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/26/meet-the-founders-at-beer-belly-firestone-walker" target="_blank"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1363" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/beerbellymeetfounder-e1434332085291.png" alt="Beer Belly Meet the Founder" width="550" height="384" />\nMeet the Founders at Beer Belly: Firestone Walker</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Koreatown - 6pm</em>\n\nFirestone Walker co-founder, David Walker, embarks once again on Walker''s Wild Ride throughout LA and one of his stops is at the legendary Beer Belly in Koreatown. This will be a great chance for you to gather some friends, order some unique food items off of Beer Belly''s crazy comfort food menu, and try some of Firestone''s best beers including, Stickee Monkey 2014, Unfiltered DBA, Sucuba 2014, Easy Jack, Union Jack, Double Jack, Wookey Jack, Pivo Pils, DBA, Opal, 805, and last but not least, a keg of a mystery Barrelworks sour. Yep, we''re definitely intrigued. Gonna have to show up to find out!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday June 27th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/456423291191415/" target="_blank"><strong>38 Degrees 6th Anniversary Party</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Alhambra - 10am</em>\n\nIf you know anything about 38 Degrees, you know you''re not going to want to miss their 6th Anniversary Party. 38 Degrees owner Clay Harding has been a leading force in the LA Beer scene for 6 years strong, and you know his reputation for getting some of the best beers available in LA - and even some that aren''t available around these parts. Plus, their event is always pretty low maintenance - no tickets, pay as you go, their delicious full menu is available, and they''re pouring flights, tasters, and full pours. The only hiccup that could occur is the line that typically builds up throughout the day. Luckily it usually isn''t too bad AND you can hit up the Ohana tasting room after you''re done. This event is a can''t-miss in my opinion.\n<h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/1644052005826824/" target="_blank"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1364" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/rarestoftherare-e1434332503473.jpg" alt="Smog City Rarest of the Rare" width="600" height="222" />\nRarest of the Rare at Smog City Brewing Company</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Torrance - 12pm</em>\n\nAfter a 2 year hiatus, Smog City - widely considered one of LA''s best breweries - is opening its doors for another edition of Rarest of the Rare, a special event where they pour a bunch of their best and rarest brews. They''ll open up 3 bars at their brewery tasting room for our enjoyment, pouring delicious and hard to find beers like Infinite Wishes, The Nothing, Bourbon O.E., Old Fashioned O.E. (beer cocktail), Goldie, Cuddlebug, Unity (and variants), ChipShot Coffee Porter, My Tai HopT, Little Bo Pils, Coffee Porter, Hoptonic IPA, LA Saison, Sabre-Toothed Squirrel, Zwickel Bo Pils, and more.\n<h3><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1389" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/ladiescraftbeer-e1434559841869.jpg" alt="ladiescraftbeer" width="550" height="206" />\n<a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/380866108774453/" target="_blank">Ladies of LA Craft Beer at Mohawk Bend</a></strong></h3>\n<em>Echo Park - 4pm</em>\n\n<strong>Beer Blogger Bonus!</strong> Our fellow LA beer blogger, <a href="http://www.girlswholikebeer.com/" target="_blank">Girls Who Like Beer</a>, is hosting an intimate evening with some of the leading ladies of LA''s craft beer scene. The event starts with a panel featuring Alex Nowell (Brewmaster at Three Weavers), Devon Randall (Brewmaster at Arts District Brewing), Lauren O''Neill (Beer Buyer at Mohawk bend), and Sarah Bennett (beer journalist at LA Weekly, Beer Paper LA, and more) to give you a well rounded discussion about the industry and women''s important roles within it. There will be some very special beers tapped for this evening to go along with Mohawk''s amazing pizza selection (that Bahn Mi pizza is CRAZY good!). Tickets are $35 and you can (and SHOULD) buy them <a href="https://girlswholikebeer.eventbrite.com/" target="_blank">right here.</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday, June 28th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><a href="https://www.facebook.com/events/894737910598505/" target="_blank"><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1365 size-full" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/eaglerockbrewmastersdinner-e1434332836796.jpg" alt="Eagle Rock Brewmaster''s Dinner" width="500" height="750" />\nEagle Rock Public House: Brewmaster''s Dinner</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Eagle Rock - 6pm</em>\n\nOn the last night of Beer Week, Eagle Rock Public House is hosting a super limited beer dinner featuring beers and dishes paired specifically for LA Beer Week. Featured breweries include Craftsman, Three Weavers, Ladyface, Smog City, and Eagle Rock Brewery. This will be a nice intimate and expertly paired dinner that is guaranteed to be the perfect combo of amazing food and amazing beer. Email info@eaglerockpublichouse.com to secure your spot before it fills up!\n<h3><a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/28/close-out-labw7-with-el-segundo-brewing-co" target="_blank"><strong>Close Our #LABW7 with El Segundo Brewing Co. at Venice Ale House</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Venice Beach - 7pm</em>\n\nSome of the best hoppy beers in LA paired with one of the best sunset beach views in LA? Can''t go wrong there! Check out Venice Ale House for a sunset beer gathering featuring a tap takeover by El Segundo Brewing Co. followed by small bites and a DJ in their intimate Rose Room. It looks to be a very chill way to close out an epic beer week with a glass of fresh Mayberry and classic So Cal sunset on Venice Beach.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>All Week: June 20-28th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><a href="http://labeerweek.dola.com/events/2015/6/20/punish-the-palate-week-labw7" target="_blank"><strong><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1380" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/06/punishpalate-e1434435762128.jpg" alt="Punish The Palate" width="450" height="450" />\nPunish the Palate Week at Johnny''s Bar</strong></a></h3>\n<em>Highland Park - 2pm</em>\n\nA special bonus for all of us hop heads! A week-long LABW celebration at Highland Park''s Johnny''s Bar, where their 18 taps will be filled only with delicious IPAs and sours. Pick any day during the week and head over there to punish your palate with your favorite local and non-local hoppy and tart beers. They''ll also be dropping some specialty kegs at random times throughout the week, so we''ll try our best to keep you updated here on what''s going on!', 'Your Guide to the Best LA Beer Week Events in 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'la-beer-week-2015', '', '', '2015-06-15 23:04:08', '2015-06-16 06:04:08', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1353', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1937, 4, '2015-08-02 21:11:10', '2015-08-03 04:11:10', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1426" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/surfnsudsheader1.jpg" alt="Surf n Suds Carpinteria 2015" width="1200" height="628" />\nIf you’re a craft beer drinker in Southern California, you know how many beer festivals are popping up these days. And even though they all seem relatively the same, they are definitely NOT all created equal. From the curated list of participating breweries, shade and water availability, event location, food options, and restroom situation, there is a lot that can go right, or a lot that can go very very wrong.\n\nFor you Ventura/Santa Barbara area folks, there''s one local festival that''s doing things the right way: <strong><a href="http://surfbeerfest.com/" target="_blank">Surf ''n'' Suds Beer Fest in Ventura &amp; Carpinteria</a></strong>. We recently attended their Ventura Harbor edition and really enjoyed the list of breweries pouring, the local communities ties, and the fun vibe right on the water. Their 3rd annual Carpinteria festival is coming up on Saturday August 15th and here are three reasons you need to <a href="http://www.showclix.com/event/SurfnSudsBeerFestival2015" target="_blank">grab tickets</a> and put this awesome beachside beer fest in your calendar.\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1417 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/amtrak-e1438571863833.jpg" alt="Carpenteria Amtrak" width="600" height="360" />\n<strong>Transportation</strong></h2>\nMost of the beer festivals in the LA area usually require convincing your friend to be the DD or employing the services of a pricey Uber. Not this fest. If you live in nearby Santa Barbara, <a href="http://www.jumpontheschoolbus.com/brew-festival-transportation.php" target="_blank">the Brew Bus</a> will be picking up from Figueroa Mountain’s Santa Barbara brewery and dropping off at the festival for $10 a person. The fest is also right next door to the Carpinteria Amtrak station, making it easy for anyone north or south of the area to safely and affordably attend. If you live too local for either of those two options, the Santa Barbara Bicycle Coalition is hosting a free bike valet for anyone who wants to ride their bike to the fest. Not a bad way to mix a little cardio into your weekend drinking session.\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1418 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/beerpong-e1438571997277.jpg" alt="Life-sized Beer Pong" width="600" height="401" />\n<strong>Entertainment</strong></h2>\nSure, the main event of any beer fest should be solely be about the beer. But any event organizer knows there needs to be supplemental experiences to make sure the wide range of attendees are fully stimulated while sipping on their beer. Surf ''n'' Suds has definitely taken this into account, with a bunch of bands, life-sized beer pong games, a corn hole tournament presented by Spencer Makenzie''s Fish Company, and local surfboard shapers. And for those of you considering the VIP tickets, not only do you get in an hour early, but you can also attend a Q&amp;A session with Island Brewing Co. owner Paul Wright and meet-the-brewer sessions with Rincon Brewery’s Shaun Crowley and brewLAB’s Steve Jarmie, Rob Peed, and Peter Goldammer.\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1419 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/surfnsudsbeer-e1438572316241.jpg" alt="Surf ''n'' Suds Beer" width="600" height="378" />\n<strong>Beer</strong></h2>\nYes, the beer. In case you haven’t been following the Ventura County beer scene, there are a ton of awesome new breweries that have opened up over the past couple years. Surf ''n'' Suds does a great job highlighting these great local spots like Island Brewing Company, Rincon Brewery, brewLAB, Firestone Walker, Figueroa Mountain, Telegraph, Pure Order, Topa Topa, Anacapa, and Poseidon. In addition to local producers, they’ve also got a bunch of other really great breweries pouring like Stone, Elysian, Speakeasy, Pizza Port, Deschutes, Belching Beaver, Lagunitas, Hess, New Belgium, Avery, and more. No matter what style of beer you''re into, you''re going to find something delicious and refreshing to sip on while you''re enjoying the fest by the beach.\n\nWell, what are you waiting for? Saturday August 15th is coming up quick, so <strong><a href="http://www.showclix.com/event/SurfnSudsBeerFestival2015" target="_blank">grab your $50 general admission tickets or $65 VIP tickets now!</a> </strong>Use promo code "<strong>hopped</strong>" for $5 off each ticket. For more information, visit <a href="http://surfbeerfest.com/" target="_blank">surfbeerfest.com</a>.', '3 Reasons to Celebrate Summer at Surf ''n'' Suds Beer Fest in Carpinteria', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'surf-n-suds-beer-fest', '', '', '2015-08-02 21:11:10', '2015-08-03 04:11:10', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1414', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1938, 4, '2015-08-04 17:37:04', '2015-08-05 00:37:04', 'What''s up, everybody. We''re back with another beer bar guide helping you navigate the best places grab some brews in the Hollywood area. Now, Hollywood is big, so we had to be a bit selective especially when we''re dipping in the east and west areas of the neighborhood. And, yeah, we have some obvious ones on here, but hopefully there are a few that you haven''t been to or heard about yet. With that said, let''s get into the guide.\n<h2>Beer Bars/Tasting Rooms</h2>\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-blue-palms.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1431" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-blue-palms.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-hollywood-blue-palms" width="700" height="394" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.bluepalmsbrewhouse.com/" target="_blank">Blue Palms Brewhouse</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/6124+Hollywood+Blvd,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90028/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2bf21363c6bad:0x28778c668b387ecf?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjvqLywzq_KAhVG3GMKHVKlBxwQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">6124 Hollywood Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90028</a></em>\n\nSo, we''re starting off with one of the obvious ones, and for good reason. When you think about craft beer in the heart of Hollywood, you think Blue Palms. There are 24 taps of awesome choices, ranging from IPAs like Blind Pig, Pliny, and Wakatu Showers to delicious coffee porters like Pizza Port''s Dusk ''Til Dawn. Make sure you say ''what up'' to new bar manager, Todd.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-ball-and-chain.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1432" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-ball-and-chain.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-hollywood-ball-and-chain" width="700" height="467" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.ballandchainla.com/" target="_blank">Ball &amp; Chain</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/1643+N+Cahuenga+Blvd,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90028/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2bf3bc6bbe685:0x5f741ecba5877e25?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwj8oa28zq_KAhUK_mMKHceUBjQQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">1643 N Cahuenga Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90028</a></em>\n\nBall &amp; Chain''s been around for a little over a year and has been scoring big with the beers as well as the food. It''s a pretty narrow setting with a subway tunnel-like interior, but it''s plenty warm &amp; cozy especially when you''re feasting on meatball sliders and washing it down with a Three Weavers Expatriate, Grapefruit Sculpin, or Bootlegger''s Knuckle Sandwich.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-stout.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1434" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-stout.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-hollywood-stout" width="700" height="465" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.stoutburgersandbeers.com/" target="_blank">Stout</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/1544+N+Cahuenga+Blvd,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90028/@34.0994499,-118.3315349,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2bf3a3b173b8f:0x4c74512983a66cef" target="_blank">1544 N Cahuenga Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90028</a></em>\n\nStout, of course, made it to our guide for <a href="http://hoppedla.com/best-beer-bars-san-fernando-valley-east/" target="_blank">the best beer bars in the East SFV</a> as well as this one and it''s pretty apparent why. It''s a good place to grab a beer. The burgers are fantastic, albeit small (we''re growing boys), so it''s best to plan on filling up with Smog City''s Amarilla Gorilla, Golden Road''s Wolf Mother Triple IPA, or Alpine''s Hoppy Birthday.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-luckys-tavern.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1435" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-luckys-tavern.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-hollywood-luckys-tavern" width="700" height="467" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.luckys-tavern.com/" target="_blank">Lucky''s Tavern</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/6613+Hollywood+Blvd,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90028/@34.1018523,-118.3360757,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2bf3b57a5f0d5:0x3bab75671574f309" target="_blank">6613 Hollywood Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90028</a></em>\n\nLucky''s fans love the food, but they also come here for the beer. And while you won''t see a ton of your local favorites, they put out a nice variety so the chances of you finding something you like are pretty likely. In addition to some of the usual suspects like Racer 5 and Point The Way, they are also pouring some nice options such as Deschutes Pinedrops IPA and Alpine''s Hoppy Birthday.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-surly-goat.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1436" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-surly-goat.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-hollywood-surly-goat" width="700" height="408" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.surlygoat.com/" target="_blank">The Surly Goat</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/7929+Santa+Monica+Blvd,+West+Hollywood,+CA+90046/@34.0911173,-118.3648123,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2bec5c686e58d:0xec2c4825f15c645b" target="_blank">7929 Santa Monica Blvd, West Hollywood, CA 90046</a></em>\n\nIf you''re into beer, then you know all about The Surly Goat. You also know that Ryan Sweeney and The Goat Group know how to bring in the good stuff. Pull up a chair underneath the goat head and get a refreshing glass of Pliny the Elder or Bear Republic''s Hop Shovel IPA, and finish it off with a Lagunitas ScareCity #3 Imperial Coffee Stout.\n<h2></h2>\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-fat-dog.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1438" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-fat-dog.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-hollywood-fat-dog" width="700" height="525" /></a><strong><a href="http://thefatdogla.com/" target="_blank">The Fat Dog</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/801+N+Fairfax+Ave,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90046/@34.0911173,-118.3648123,17z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2beceec96cc87:0xdec66cae5c6a3806" target="_blank">801 N Fairfax Ave, West Hollywood, CA 90046</a></em>\n\nThe Fat Dog''s Hollywood counterpart isn''t exactly serving up the whales by any means, but what they lack in beers they make up for with their food. Some recent beers they had on tap include Dogfish Head''s 90 minute and Flying Dog''s Bloodline Blood Orange IPA, but they also have a bottle list for you to peruse as well.\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-brickyard.gif"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1439" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-brickyard.gif" alt="best-beer-bars-hollywood-brickyard" width="700" height="700" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.brickyardpubs.com/" target="_blank">Brickyard Pub</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/1810+Wilcox+Ave,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90028/@34.1041176,-118.3329223,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2bf3c4363c76d:0x9b29dfab7cfc7340" target="_blank">1810 Wilcox Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90028</a></em>\n\nHere''s another beer bar that has a Valley counterpart that made it to our <a href="http://hoppedla.com/best-beer-bars-san-fernando-valley-east/" target="_blank">East SFV list</a>, and from what I hear, it has A LOT of beer. As it turns out, Brickyard is a non-pretentious "dive" that succeeds in not only the beer, but plenty of activities, too. So, grab a few buddies, shoot some pool, and soak up on some Grapefruit Sculpin and Idiot IPAs all night (no guarantees you won''t turn into one later).\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-oinkster.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1440" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/best-beer-bars-hollywood-oinkster.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-hollywood-oinkster" width="700" height="525" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.theoinkster.com/" target="_blank">The Oinkster</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/776+Vine+St,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90038/@34.0851098,-118.3285789,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2b8cbafda87d3:0x3bcc4408e1ab88e1" target="_blank">776 Vine St, Los Angeles, CA 90038</a></em>\n\nIn the mood for good grub and solid craft beers? Then, The Oinkster will not disappoint. Sink your teeth into a juicy burger or their savory pastrami, and wash it all down with a Strand Atticus IPA or (even better) the phenomenal El Segundo Hammerland DIPA.\n\nThere''s a chance we missed your favorite Hollywood craft beer bar, so now''s your chance to be our expert. Fill us in if there''s one that needs to be on the list or let us know what you love about the ones that are up here in the comments below or on Twitter at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. Cheers!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;', 'Your Guide to the Best Craft Beer Spots in Hollywood', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'your-guide-to-the-best-beer-bars-in-hollywood', '', '', '2015-08-04 17:37:04', '2015-08-05 00:37:04', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1430', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1939, 4, '2015-08-05 10:27:06', '2015-08-05 17:27:06', 'Wow, August 6th is here already! National IPA Day is upon us once again, which means it is our patriotic duty as craft beer drinkers to hunt down hoppy brews to crack open as a tribute to our favorite beverage. This year, LA has more awesome IPA options than ever before, which can be a little overwhelming for some, if you''re looking to drink the best of the best on this special occasion. So, in true Hopped LA fashion, we did a little bit of field research and put together the ultimate IPA Day celebration guide for all you LA hop heads.\n\nHere are some incredibly amazing locally-brewed IPAs that you can currently find around LA and OC to make this 2015 IPA Day a celebration you won''t forget!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1459 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/amarillagorilla-e1438790925124.jpg" alt="Smog City Amarilla Gorilla" width="450" height="450" />\n<strong>Amarilla Gorilla IPA</strong></h2>\nThe latest batch of Smog City''s Amarilla Gorilla was released a couple weeks ago and the timing couldn’t have been better. The hops are tasting incredibly fresh, with bright and delicious orange citrus flavors. Great summer IPA? You got it.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><img class="alignnone wp-image-1460 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/citra-showers-e1438791169649.jpg" alt="Noble Ale Works Citra Showers" width="450" height="480" />\n<strong>Citra Showers Double IPA</strong></h2>\nThe latest batch of Hopped LA’s (and almost everyone else''s, really) favorite version of Noble Ale Works'' Showers series was re-released on Monday. This beer is just pure tropical citrus right in your face. There really are very few beers I like more than this one. But one of those beers is Noble''s I Love It! IPA which won the 2014 LA IPA Festival. Lucky for all of us, they’re re-releasing that as well this Thursday in their tasting room. Be like the rest of the Orange County beer drinkers and get over there for a growler fill.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1461 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/thrillseeker-e1438791438102.jpg" alt="Beachwood Brewing Thrillseeker" width="450" height="450" />\nThrillseeker IPA</strong></h2>\nAnother hoppy Beachwood favorite, Thrillseeker, was released a week ago and is already next to impossible to find in bottles around LA. If you saved a bottle to crack for IPA Day, then we applaud you. If not, you might just have to wander on down to their Long Beach or Seal Beach locations to get your hands on this citrusy-piney hop forward brew.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1462 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/thewolf-e1438791676427.jpg" alt="Golden Road The Wolf Pack" width="450" height="450" />\nWolf Among Weeds IPA</strong></h2>\nGolden Road’s year-round IPA is the one beer on this list that anyone can find at their local grocery store or beverage depot. Just because it’s everywhere, doesn’t mean it isn’t worth drinking. We blind tasted this against Pliny the Elder a few months back, and the Wolf really held its own! Not to mention, Golden Road unleashed the full Wolf Pack recently - a session IPA with the same hop lineup called Wolf Pup, and a Triple IPA with the same hop lineup called Wolf Mother. You may even be able to try all 3 on tap at some bars around town.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1477 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/lizardsmouth1-e1438815799581.jpg" alt="Figueroa Mountain Lizard''s Mouth" width="450" height="450" />\nLizard''s Mouth Imperial IPA</strong></h2>\nAnother one of our year-round favorites comes to you from Figueroa Mountain up north of LA in Buelton. Lizards Mouth is a solid Imperial IPA that is so dangerously drinkable (which I think is why it’s our dad''s favorite beer!). If you can grab a bottle under a couple months old, before the hop bitterness starts degrading, then it’s a real winner. After that, expect that malty sweetness to shine through, which is okay if your palate is ready for it.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1465 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/mayberry-e1438792273632.jpg" alt="El Segundo Mayberry IPA" width="450" height="450" />\nMayberry IPA &amp; Hammerland Double IPA</strong></h2>\nAnd here we go with an amazing IPA and Double IPA from LA’s favorite hoppy brewers, El Segundo Brewing. Mayberry is hailed as one of LA’s best IPAs within experienced beer circles and we couldn’t agree more. Plus, the latest batch was just packaged last week so you can be sure it is super fresh and delicious. Their Hammerland Double IPA was packaged a couple weeks ago and has a great balance between its clean malt backbone and tropical bitter hops. If you’re sipping on these to celebrate IPA day, you’ve got some serious style.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1466 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/expatriate-e1438792750228.jpg" alt="Three Weavers Expatriate" width="450" height="450" />\nExpatriate IPA &amp; Dual Citizen Double IPA</strong></h2>\nFine, we’re biased. Three Weavers is our favorite LA brewery, and the always awesome Expatriate IPA has become my new go-to IPA here in LA. Drink it, you won’t be disappointed. Plus they just released the latest batch of their Dual Citizen Double IPA last week and even though it came in a bit higher in ABV, you can’t tell because it’s just as delicious as the last batch. You can’t see it right now, but fresh Dual Citizen just puts a smile on my face. I also gotta throw a bonus shout out to their Return of Sassy IPA which has an amazing combination of rye spice and citrusy bitter hoppiness as well as their Even Sassier Double IPA which is SO good and rumored to be hitting taps any day now. Follow their <a href="https://www.facebook.com/threeweaversbrewing" target="_blank">Facebook</a> and <a href="https://instagram.com/threeweavers/" target="_blank">Instagram</a> to find out exactly when.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1467 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/ocularity-e1438792992147.jpg" alt="Bottle Logic Ocularity" width="450" height="450" />\nOcularity Double IPA</strong></h2>\nBottle Logic makes some amazing IPAs so it was hard to choose between them, but Ocularity really stands out to me recently. It’s a Double IPA and a bit more malt-forward than I usually like, but it’s balanced with very flavorful fruity citrus and herbal notes. Head over to their tasting room to get a pour and try a couple more of their other great IPAs as well. Plus The Cut food truck is there all the time and they make one of the best burgers we’ve ever had. Go and <a href="https://instagram.com/thecuthcb/" target="_blank">follow their Instagram</a> if you don’t believe me.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1468 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/thegreatone-e1438793267957.jpg" alt="Four Sons Brewing The Great One" width="450" height="450" />\nThe Great One Imperial IPA</strong></h2>\nIf you haven’t heard of Four Sons yet, don’t feel bad. They’re a small brewery out of Huntington Beach that hasn’t made its way too far north just yet. But with their recent brewhouse expansion and new canning efforts, you can bet they’ll be hitting LA pretty soon. The Great One is a delicious Double IPA that pours a dark amber and has a great balance of malty sweetness and piney bitterness. You can barely tell it sits at 10%, so sip on a couple of these and you’ll be feeling pretty great yourself.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1469 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/brightside-e1438793390558.jpg" alt="Highland Park Brewery Brightside" width="450" height="450" />\nBrightside IPA</strong></h2>\nWhen Highland Park releases an IPA, I drink it. No questions asked. With Hello LA, Neon, Bonkers, and 1 Up they had me hooked. Their latest IPA, Brightside is a light and hoppy, easy drinking summer IPA. You’ll have to go to their tasting room to get it, but that just means you get to try all of their other fantastic beers as well. Win-win, I say.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong><img class="alignnone wp-image-1470 size-full" style="border: 1px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/kingharboripacoconut-e1438793564541.jpg" alt="King Harbor IPA w/ Coconut" width="450" height="450" />\nKing Harbor IPA w/ Coconut</strong></h2>\nKing Harbor’s core IPA is a really good hoppy beer, that’s for sure. It’s not gonna blow your mind, but it’s got great flavor and isn’t going to ruin your palate for the rest of your drinking session. With the addition of coconut, this recent variation hit taps just in time for summer. While the coconut IPA thing seems to be trending a bit lately, this one doesn’t overdo it. Especially if you’re drinking it at their harborfront tasting room in Redondo Beach people watching and soaking up the sun. Then that’s just good decision making.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThere you have it. The best IPA''s currently pouring around LA and OC. Now your mission is to locate one or more of these delicious hoppy beers (we tend to use Untappd for that), and <strong>tag us in a photo on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/HoppedLA" target="_blank">Facebook</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">Twitter</a>, or <a href="https://instagram.com/hoppedla/" target="_blank">Instagram</a> so we know we steered you in the right direction!</strong>', 'The Best LA IPA''s to Drink on IPA Day 2015', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ipa-day-2015', '', '', '2015-08-05 10:27:06', '2015-08-05 17:27:06', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1458', 0, 'post', '', 0);
