(1940, 4, '2015-12-24 11:33:43', '2015-12-24 19:33:43', 'The melting pot that is Downtown Los Angeles seems to be taking quite the turn for the better. Pershing Square looks green and immaculate, there''s a ton of new construction going on, and it''s a got a shit-load of great places for craft beer.\n\nIf you''re looking for a perfect place for a craft beer bar crawl, then these breweries and bars are it. Whether it''s walking distance or a short Uber ride, feast your eyes on the craft beer scene in Downtown LA.\n\n<em>Last updated: February 2016</em>\n<h2>Breweries</h2>\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/angel-city-brewing1.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1708" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/angel-city-brewing1.jpg" alt="la-et-night-angel-city" width="800" height="567" /></a>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://angelcitybrewery.com/" target="_blank">Angel City Brewery</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Angel+City+Brewery/@34.0462629,-118.2376901,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x4e029d3a86495d12?sa=X&amp;sqi=2&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjn1NvI0_bJAhVO9WMKHdL1AFgQ_BIIhwEwFg" target="_blank">216 S Alameda St, Los Angeles, CA 90012</a></em>\n\nAngel City is known for introducing the Arts District their fair share of consistent, yet, diverse offering of brews to the public. The upside is their expansive, and historic, space where you''ll find it quite comfortable to take down an couple White Nite golden stouts.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/mumford-craft-beer-arts-district.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1706" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/mumford-craft-beer-arts-district.jpg" alt="mumford-craft-beer-arts-district" width="800" height="533" /></a></h3>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://www.mumfordbrewing.com/" target="_blank">Mumford Brewing Co.</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Mumford+Brewing/@34.046087,-118.242006,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x7a3dae54836d1366?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwisuI7x1PbJAhVQ6GMKHdLeD4gQ_BIIfjAN" target="_blank">416 Boyd St, Los Angeles, CA 90013</a></em>\n\nAlso located in the Arts District is Mumford Brewing. Although they are still relatively new, their reputation is growing with solid beers anchored by their Black Mamba, an American Black Ale.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/so-cal-brew-bus-boomtown.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1709" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/so-cal-brew-bus-boomtown.jpg" alt="so-cal-brew-bus-boomtown" width="800" height="452" /></a>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://www.boomtownbrew.com/" target="_blank">Boomtown Brewery</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Boomtown+Brewery/@34.050763,-118.233216,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xca3d36838602b4ce" target="_blank">700 Jackson St, Los Angeles, CA 90012</a></em>\n\nBoomtown opened not long after Mumford Brewing did in the Arts District that really helped solidify the neighborhood as a destination spot. Boomtown embraces delish food trucks and fun events, making this a place to visit during your beer-venture.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/arts-district-brewing.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1640" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/arts-district-brewing.jpg" alt="arts-district-brewing" width="800" height="450" /></a></h3>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://www.artsdistrictbrewing.com/" target="_blank">Arts District Brewing</a></strong></h3>\n<em><span class="_Xbe"><a href="https://www.google.com/webhp?sourceid=chrome-instant&amp;ion=1&amp;espv=2&amp;ie=UTF-8#q=arts+district+brewing&amp;rflfq=1&amp;tbm=lcl&amp;rlfi=hd:;si:14572293836080270156" target="_blank">828 Traction Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90013</a></span></em>\n\nAfter attracting the talented Devon Randall, Arts District became a place to pay attention to given the minds from 213 Nightlife and Blue Palms Brewhouse were behind this. It''s a fun, hip bar that just happens to have a potentially top-notch brewery operation inside of it.\n&nbsp;\n&nbsp;\n<img class="alignnone wp-image-2019 size-large" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/iron-triangle-beer-spots-in-downtown-la-1024x683.jpg" alt="iron-triangle-beer-spots-in-downtown-la" width="800" height="534" />\n<h3 class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwiS7J_V1_bJAhVV52MKHRCnDy4QghwICigAMAI"><strong><a href="http://www.irontrianglebrewing.com/" target="_blank">Iron Triangle Brewing Company</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Iron+Triangle+Brewing+Company/@34.036191,-118.2358,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x5374083cfa6534d5" target="_blank">1581 Industrial St, Los Angeles, CA 90021</a></em>\n\nSeveral years in the making, Iron Triangle was the brewery with ambitious plans and did not go back on their word to deliver. The brewery finally opened in January 2016 in their historic Arts District location, and has received plenty of positive feedback to garner a visit from you. With brewing operations led by Darren Moser, formerly of Maui Brewing, you can rest assured that the beers Iron Triangle is pouring will be solid. They recently signed with a distributor, so you can expect to see them in some of your local retail and bars as well.\n\n&nbsp;\n<div class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwiS7J_V1_bJAhVV52MKHRCnDy4QghwICigAMAI"></div>\n<h2 class="_mr kno-fb-ctx" data-ved="0ahUKEwiS7J_V1_bJAhVV52MKHRCnDy4QghwICigAMAI">Beer Bars/Tasting Rooms</h2>\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/city-tavern.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1710" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/city-tavern.jpg" alt="city-tavern" width="800" height="533" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.citytaverndtla.com/" target="_blank">City Tavern</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/735+S+Figueroa+St+%23133,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90017/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c7b1276e2951:0xc124669d6af0dacc?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjZ3b6r2fbJAhVBy2MKHfQrATEQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">735 S. Figueroa St. #133 Los Angeles, Ca 90017</a></em>\n\nCity Tavern is the hidden gem once you descend into Fig at 7th''s circular abyss. Of course, if you''ve been to City Tavern before, you know that they are serious about craft beer. Grab a pour of Dogfish Head''s Burton Baton while it''s still there, and some food if you''d like. The pastrami burger is amazing.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Screen-Shot-2015-08-04-at-5.47.49-PM.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1453" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Screen-Shot-2015-08-04-at-5.47.49-PM.png" alt="best-beer-bars-downtown-la" width="800" height="803" /></a><strong><a href="http://www.barreldownla.com/#about" target="_blank">Barrel Down</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/525+W+7th+St,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90014/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c7b4519c8aa5:0x90ecfbffec555178?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwix0J6G3PbJAhUC6WMKHeLGDgAQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">525 W 7th St, Los Angeles, CA 90014</a></em>\n\nBarrel Down is one of the newer spots to open up in a growing DTLA craft beer environment, and we were as excited as everybody else to see it open. Barrel Down sports 40 taps of American craft beer in addition to amazing cocktails. Think of it as the perfect place to hit up after work or during a night out. It''s core beers include Dogfish Head''s 90 Minutes and Barrelhouse''s Rye IPA, while some of the rotating taps will see the likes of Victory''s DirtWolf DIPA and Three Weavers'' Dual Citizen.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/psext1.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1498" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/psext1.jpg" alt="Public School 213" width="800" height="465" /></a><strong><a href="http://psontap.com/locations/ps213/" target="_blank">Public School 213</a></strong></h3>\n<i><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/612+S+Flower+St,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90017/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c7b3f168c477:0xf2195e4df159c049?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjmnOSd2vbJAhUP8GMKHeDLAu8Q8gEIIzAB" target="_blank">612 S. Flower St. Los Angeles, Ca 90017</a></i>\n\nOne of a few Public School locations in LA, PS213 takes up a favorable corner with a fresh look after absorbing the neighboring Daily Grill. If you haven''t wrecked your palate already, order an Avery Raja and hit up the happy hour menu if you made it in time. $4 fare like tacos, truffle fries, and street dogs ought to hit the spot.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la1.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-312" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la1.png" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="800" height="705" /></a><a href="http://sixthstreettavern.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Sixth Street Tavern</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/630+W+6th+St,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90017/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c7b462ae2325:0x6ff660b8ff619946?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwj7p9rx2_bJAhVB6GMKHW4_AxgQ8gEIIjAB" target="_blank">630 W. 6th St. Los Angeles, Ca 90017</a></em>\n\nAlpine''s Hoppy Birthday is a staple on tap, sooo yeah, this place is nice. Not only do they make tasty cocktails, but the beer list is expansive with options from breweries like Angel City, Craftsman, Alpine, and Deschutes. The Rockenwagner pretzel is pretty on point, but if you''re in this for the end of our DTLA beer crawl, you''re going to want to wait to the end. From here, you can pop into Library Bar next door, or it''s off to the next one.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3><a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la2.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-314" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la2.png" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="800" height="458" /></a><a href="http://springstla.com/" target="_blank"><strong>Spring Street Bar</strong></a></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/626+S+Spring+St,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90014/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c6355dbbfa5b:0x920a610b195cc73c?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwipo9z42_bJAhUO_WMKHaz_DrIQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">626-B S. Spring St. Los Angeles, Ca 90014</a></em>\n\nSpring Street Bar is also categorized as a deli, and that''s because they''ve got killer sandwiches. They also have 26 taps of frothy, delicious beer. Start with El Segundo''s Citra and end it with Deschutes Fresh Squeezed IPA, and it''s on to the next one.\n\nAt this point, the historic Cole''s Red Car Bar would be a great pit stop for an original french dip. We''ll encourage that you order an old fashioned, though the beer list is okay. Possible speciality beers can come from Three Weavers and other LA breweries.\n\n&nbsp;\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/far-bar.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1711" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/far-bar.jpg" alt="far-bar" width="800" height="533" /></a>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://farbarla.com/" target="_blank">Far Bar</a></strong></h3>\n<em><span class="_Xbe"><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Far+Bar/@34.04961,-118.23957,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x52d0b49417c487ad" target="_blank">347 E 1st St, Los Angeles, CA 90012</a></span></em>\n\nBehind this neon sign lies a great amount of taps not only in the front bar area, but in the back as well. Everything from Alpine''s Nelson to Noble''s Tongue Tickles have graced the taps here, so put Little Tokyo on your map.\n&nbsp;\n&nbsp;\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Screen-Shot-2015-12-25-at-1.53.46-AM.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-1712" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/Screen-Shot-2015-12-25-at-1.53.46-AM.png" alt="dtla-la-beer-whole-foods" width="800" height="761" /></a>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://www.wholefoodsmarket.com/stores/downtownlosangeles" target="_blank">The Eight Bar at Whole Foods Market DTLA</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/Whole+Foods+Market/@34.0460599,-118.2574096,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x89ca46225a10f4c6?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwj_j5qm3_bJAhUL62MKHTlLDAIQ_BIIdzAK" target="_blank">788 S Grand Ave, Los Angeles, CA 90017</a></em>\n\nThis brand new Whole Foods Market in DTLA brought their A-game with a bar that really feels separate from the rest of the grocery store. Nice and bright during the day, yet dark and comforting at night, the Eight Bar at Whole Foods Market DTLA does a nice job with their 36 taps, wine list, and full bar with food in this neck of the woods. <a href="https://www.instagram.com/dtlacraftbeer/" target="_blank">Their retail side is great, too</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la2.jpg"><img class="alignnone wp-image-320" style="border: 3px solid #000000;" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la2.jpg" alt="best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la" width="800" height="600" /></a>\n<h3><strong><a href="http://buzzwinebeershop.com/" target="_blank">BUZZ wine beer shop</a></strong></h3>\n<em><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/460+S+Spring+St,+Los+Angeles,+CA+90013/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x80c2c64a5d5180ed:0x6732d5a7cca0a9ab?sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwjckZif3fbJAhVBG2MKHbPHBLwQ8gEIHDAA" target="_blank">460 S. Spring St. Ste. C Los Angeles, Ca 90013</a></em>\n\nBuzz is THE specialty wine and bottle shop in DTLA that just happens to have a tasting bar towards the back. They hold numerous wine and beer tastings throughout the week, so it''s a great place to talk shop and sip the good stuff. Then, you can take a few bottles home to cap off the night.\n\nHave you been to any of these places mentioned above? Did I miss a good beer spot along the way here? Whatever the case, join the convo in the comments below or on Twitter at <a href="http://www.twitter.com/hoppedla" target="_blank">@HoppedLA</a>. Thanks for reading.', 'Your Guide to the Best Craft Beer Spots in Downtown LA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'best-beer-bars-in-downtown-la-2', '', '', '2015-12-24 11:33:43', '2015-12-24 19:33:43', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=289', 0, 'post', '', 1),
(1941, 4, '2016-02-09 13:01:17', '2016-02-09 21:01:17', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\n\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday February 8th to Sunday February 14th, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday February 9</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Three Weavers Tap Takeover at Darryl’s Couch</strong>\n<em>Camarillo, 5:30pm</em></h3>\nThree Weavers is taking over the taps at Darryl’s Couch in Camarillo and bringing along six of their awesome brews, including their latest collaboration with Noble Ale Works, The Messenger IPA!\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony’s with Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nPhantom Carriage beers arrive at Tony’s Darts Away for the first time and we are all stoked! They’ll be pouring Broadacres, Muis, Dolores, and possibly a few other beers. If you love sours and haven’t made your way to Phantom Carriage’s South Bay brewery yet, this is a great chance to try what they’re brewing up.\n<h3><strong>Fat Tuesday at The Federal Bar</strong>\n<em>North Hollywood, 6pm</em></h3>\nCelebrate Fat Tuesday in the east Valley at The Federal Bar! They''ll have Abita''s Wrought Iron, Purple Haze, Mardi Gras Bock, and ’14 Bourbon Street Imperial Stout on tap and will be serving Creole Shrimp n Grits for dinner. Finish it all off with Bayou Bootlegger Root Beer Floats.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday February 10</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Lucky Luke Tap Takeover at Kinetic Brewing</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 11:30am</em></h3>\nOne of the LA area''s newest breweries, Lucky Luke Brewing Co, is taking over the taps at Kinetic in Lancaster. Starting at 11:30am, they''ll be pouring The Beardsman American Pale Ale, The Mortician Black IPA, The Impresario IPA, The Millwright Oatmeal Stout, and The Tillman Tart Saison. Then later that evening, some special beers will be tapped. At 6pm, they''ll put on Chardonnay barrel-aged Actuary Belgian Golden Strong and Bourbon barrel-aged Rigger Imperial Stout. And at 7pm they''ll tap The Trotter American Sour. This will be an awesome celebration of Antelope Valley beer!\n<h3><strong>Wild Wednesday at Southland Beer</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 4pm</em></h3>\nHeads up, sour beer lovers! Southland is tapping a couple wild ales that you don''t typically see on tap around these parts. At 4pm, they''re taping Grimm''s Echoplex, a double dry-hopped American wild ale from Brooklyn NY, and Libertine''s Wild IPA from Morro Bay. Head on out to Koreatown and give them a try!\n<h3><strong>Steal the Glass Night at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nSteal the Glass Night is back at Eureka featuring Rogue Brewing''s 6 Hop IPA and Chocolate Stout. Time to add another pint glass to your growing collection!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday February 11</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Ninkasi Night at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nNinkasi is in the house at Select Beer Store this Thursday and will be pouring a handful of their beers including Helles Belles, Tricerahops IIPA, Dawn of the Red India Red Ale, Sour of Love American Kettle Sour Ale with Cranberry, Hop Cooler Citrus IPA, and Noir Coffee Milk Stout.\n<h3><strong>Modern Times Pint Night at The Daily Pint</strong>\n<em>Santa Monica, 5pm</em></h3>\nModern Times is in the house at The Daily Pint in Santa Monica pouring some of their classics as well some some new heavy hitters like Devils Teeth Old Ale, City of the Sun IPA, Mega Fortunate Islands Double IPA, Blazing World Hoppy Amber, Neverwhere Brett IPA, Lomaland Saison, Black House Oatmeal Stout, and Floating World IPA. Head out to the westside and check it out!\n<h3><strong>Chocolate &amp; Beer Pairing at Wolf Creek Brewery</strong>\n<em>Valencia, 6pm</em></h3>\nTruffles N'' Toffee will be back in the house at Wolf Creek for a special chocolate and beer pairing event. Tickets are $25 and a 7 course beer &amp; chocolate pairing, including Howlin'' Hefe with Bananas Foster Crunch and Over the Moon Stout with a Triple Threat Dark Chocolate. Grab your tickets at their tasting room or by emailing Laina@wolfcreekbrewery.com before they sell out!\n<h3><strong>Bell''s Hopslam 2016 at Surly Goat</strong>\n<em>West Hollywood, 6pm</em></h3>\nBell''s annual release of Hopslam hits Los Angeles for the first time! Surly Goat is celebrating with a bunch of bell''s beers, like Roundhouse IRA, Bear Hug Russian Imperial Stout, Expedition Stout, Java Stout, Oberon, Two-Hearted Ale, and of course, Hopslam. Head out and see what all the fuss is about!\n<h3><strong>Beer, Cheese &amp; Chocolate Pairing at Angel City Brewery</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 7pm</em></h3>\nVagabond Cheese is back with another beer pairing event, this time at Angel City in the Arts District and incorporating chocolate into the mix as well. <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/beer-cheese-chocolate-pairing-with-angel-city-brewery-vagabond-cheese-company-tickets-20237767708?aff=ebrowse" target="_blank">Tickets are $38</a> and include a 5 course beer, cheese, and chocolate pairing led by Vagabond owner, Alex Ourieff, and the Angel City team.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday February 12</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>An Evening with Monkish Brewing Co at Public Beer Wine Shop</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 3pm</em></h3>\nMonkish is heading down to Long Beach for a tap takeover at one of the LBC''s best beer spots featuring their Ninja Star, Shadowboxing, <span class="text_exposed_show">Feminist, Split Infinitive, and Olivia. </span>Grab a flight of all 5 beers for $15 and get 10% off all Monkish bottles if you buy a flight. They''ll also have food specials from Company of Khanh. If you haven''t tried any of Monkish''s beers yet, this is an excellent opportunity to do so.\n<h3><strong>Taste the Future: Modern Times Orderville Preview Party at 38 Degrees Ale House</strong>\n<em>Monrovia, 3pm</em></h3>\nPreview the brand new year-round Modern Times IPA, Orderville, a peachy, fruit-forward Mosaic hop bomb with a dry unobtrusive malt profile. This beer doesn''t go into wide release until next month, so here''s your chance to check it out!\n<h3><strong>Lovers'' Haven at Haven Gastropub</strong>\n<em>Orange, 5pm</em></h3>\nHaven is celebrating Valentine''s Day all weekend long with a special three course menu alongside their regular full menu. The Valentine''s menu is prix-fixe and will be $45 per guest with optional beer pairings for $15 more. Great beer and great food, it doesn''t get much more romantic than that!\n<h3><strong>Valentine''s Weekend at Mohawk Bend</strong>\n<em>Echo Park, 5pm</em></h3>\nMohawk Bend has put together a nice romantic evening of food and drink for you to take advantage of all weekend long. They''ve got a couple specialty cocktails, a V-Day themed craft beer flight, and some food specials for you and that special someone.\n<h3><strong>Taste the Future: Modern Times Orderville IPA Preview at Library Alehouse</strong>\n<em>Santa Monica, 6pm</em></h3>\nPreview the brand new year-round Modern Times IPA, Orderville, a peachy, fruit-forward Mosaic hop bomb with a dry unobtrusive malt profile. This beer doesn''t go into wide release until next month, so here''s your chance to check it out!\n<h3><strong>Modern Times Orderville Preview Event at The Federal Bar</strong>\n<em>North Hollywood, 6pm</em></h3>\nPreview the brand new year-round Modern Times IPA, Orderville, a peachy, fruit-forward Mosaic hop bomb with a dry unobtrusive malt profile. This beer doesn''t go into wide release until next month, so here''s your chance to check it out!\n<h3><strong>Tusk &amp; Grain Official Launch Event at Blue Palms</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 7pm</em></h3>\nSaint Archer''s Tusk &amp; Grain barrel aged beer series officially launches in LA with a special event at Blue Palms. They''ll have their Barrel Aged Blend No 01, Imperial Porter w/ Coffee &amp; Mexican Chocolate, and Barleywine “Old Fashioned” for you to enjoy.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday February 13</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Hopslam 2016 Release at Blue Palms Brewhouse</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 12pm</em></h3>\nBell''s Hopslam is hitting Hollywood Blvd this Saturday at noon! Head out to Blue Palms for your chance to try this hoppy Michigan favorite!\n<h3><strong>Claremont Craft Ales Night</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 5pm</em></h3>\nClaremont Craft Ales is in the house at Southland Beer and bringing along some of their awesome beers for your drinking enjoyment! They''ll have Single Dude IPA w/Citra, Double Dude DIPA w/Simcoe, Grapefruit Dude DIPA w/Grapefruit, Triple Dude TIPA w/Mosaic, Station 101 Red IPA, and St Mawes American Stout. Head out, drink some beers, chat with the brewers, and have a good time!\n<h3><strong>Beer &amp; Chocolate Pairing at Craft Beer Cellar</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 5pm</em></h3>\nCelebrate Valentine''s Day a day early at Craft Beer Cellar with a special beer &amp; chocolate pairing with Andrea''s Truffles. Tickets are $18 pre-sale and $20 day of the event and include Barley Forge Brewing The Patsy paired w/ Rum with Coconut Caramel Truffle, Modern Times Blazing World paired w/ Spicy Cinnamon with Habanero Salt Truffle, Lindeman Framboise paired w/ Peanut Butter with Captain Crunch Brittle Truffle, and Sierra Nevada Bigfoot paired w/ Triple Chocolate Toffee Truffle. <a href="http://beerandchocolate.bpt.me/" target="_blank">Grab your tickets</a> before they sell out!\n<h3><strong>Hoppy Valentine''s at Brouwerij West</strong>\n<em>San Pedro, 6pm</em></h3>\nPrimal Alchemy Catering is pairing a farm to table dinner with the brand new Brouwerij West for a special Valentine''s Day craft beer celebration. The night will start with tray passed appetizers and a complimentary 5 taster set and then lead into the multi-course farm to table dinner, where beers will be available for purchase. They''ll also have live music and a photobooth to help round out the evening. <a href="http://hoppyvalentine.bpt.me/" target="_blank">Tickets are available here</a> and are $100 for 1 person or $90 each as a couple.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday February 14</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Broken Hearts Circus at Angel City</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 1pm</em></h3>\nAngel City is hosting a circus themed Valentine''s Day celebration complete with clowns, jugglers, aerialists, stilt walkers, food trucks, live music, face painting, tarot card reading, and of course craft beer.\n<h3><strong>V-Day Beer &amp; Donuts at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 11am</em></h3>\nPhantom Carriage is celebrating Valentine''s day with fresh house-made donuts paired with carefully selected house beers, cold-pressed coffee, serial killer date night movies, and a DJ spinning deadly funk, jazz, soul and psych.\n<h3><strong>Valentine''s Day at ERPH</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 11am</em></h3>\nEagle Rock is celebrating Valentine''s Day with the return of their 2010 GABF gold medal winner, Red Velvet Imperial Red with Rye. To add to the festivities they will be offering $2 oysters, no corkage fees, and 10% off all bottles!\n<h3><strong>Cupcakes &amp; Craft Beer at Tony''s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 12pm</em></h3>\nCelebrate Valentine''s Day at Tony''s where if you order Alesmith''s My Bloody Valentine, you can get a free vegan red velvet cupcake from Bramble Bakeshop.\n<h3><strong>Smokey Valentine''s Day: McJaggery Stout Release at Transplants Brewing</strong>\n<em>Palmdale, 12pm</em></h3>\nTransplants are celebrating Valentine''s Day with a special beer release of their 9.1% McJaggery Stout made with jaggery (Indian Date palm sugar). You''ll also be able to get your glass smoked with bourbon soaked oak chips for a dollar more. Pretty awesome and unique way to spend your Valentine''s Day.\n<h3><strong>Valentine''s Day Dinner at Kinetic Brewing</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 4pm</em></h3>\nHead over to Kinetic for a special four course Valentine''s Day dinner. $100 per couple or $60 individual. <a href="https://scontent-sjc2-1.xx.fbcdn.net/hphotos-xtp1/t31.0-8/12657348_1066524370066083_3361756413627850537_o.jpg" target="_blank">Check out the menu here</a>.\n<h3><strong>Valentine''s Day Dinner at Beachwood BBQ &amp; Brewing</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nBeachwood is hosting a special four course Valentine''s Day dinner with craft beer pairings at both of their locations. No reservations are necessary, so round up your significant other and head over to Long / Seal Beach!\n<h3><strong>Valentine''s Day at The Pub at Golden Road</strong>\n<em>Burbank/Glendale, 6pm</em></h3>\nCozy up next to your loved one for a special Valentine''s Day dinner at Golden Road! They''re hosting a four course dinner plus one beer or wine pour for $50 per person. Email abby@goldenroad.la to reserve your spot before they''re filled up.\n<h3><strong>Valentine''s Day Soirée at Ladyface</strong>\n<em>Agoura Hills, 6pm</em></h3>\nLadyface is throwing a soirée in honor of Valentine''s Day complete with Seafood Trio and Cheese Plate specials, cocktail specials, and live music from 7-10pm. Reserve your spot by emailing events@ladyfaceale.com or calling (818) 477-4566.', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of February 8, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-feb-8', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1931', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(1942, 4, '2016-02-09 19:49:25', '2016-02-10 03:49:25', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1939" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/plinytheyounger2016.jpg" alt="Pliny the Younger 2016 Los Angeles" width="1200" height="628" />\n\nPliny the Younger season is here once again and Los Angeles is about to get real hoppy! Whether you''re a PtY vet or you''re still searching for your first taste of Russian River''s golden nectar, this is your guide to finding out where to drink Pliny the Younger Triple IPA in Los Angeles &amp; Orange County in 2016.\n\n<strong><em>Last Updated: March 7th, 2016</em></strong>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Library Alehouse</del></strong>\n<del> Santa Monica - Wednesday February 17, 8:30pm</del></h2>\n<del>Well 2016''s first unannounced Pliny the Younger tapping has hit LA. Library Alehouse started pouring the beer around 8:30pm this evening. The word on the street is there''s no line, so better get moving. The beer probably won''t last through the evening!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Naja''s Place</del></strong>\n<del>Redondo Beach - Friday February 19, 4pm</del></h2>\n<del>The tapping of the Younger at Naja''s Place on Friday was as underground as they come, with regulars and locals able to grab pours without the hassle of tickets or lines. By the time we even heard about it, the keg was minutes away from kicking. Just shows it pays to be a regular at your local beer bar.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Mohawk Bend</del></strong>\n<del> Echo Park - Saturday February 20th, 9:30am</del></h2>\n<del>Mohawk Bend is looking to be the first LA bar to tap Pliny the Younger in 2016 with their early morning event on Saturday. Tickets will start being passed out at 9:30am, and they''ll be tapping the beer at 11, so if you want to guarantee your spot, show up a little early to get in line. Last year, the Younger poured into the early afternoon, but don''t count on it lasting as long this year!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>38 Degrees Ale House</del></strong>\n<del> Alhambra - Saturday February 20th, 11am</del></h2>\n<del>38 Degrees is hosting their annual Pliny the Younger Day on February 20th, where craft beer drinkers will flock early to begin lining up along Main St for their chance to purchase a Russian River flight, including the elusive Younger. They''ll start handing out tickets at 8am and will tap the keg at 11am, so you can stick around or leave and come back to enjoy your Russian River flight including the awesome triple IPA.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Blue Palms Brewhouse</del></strong>\n<del> Hollywood - Saturday February 20th, 11:30am</del></h2>\n<del>Blue Palms is tapping their keg of Pliny the Younger at 11:30am on Saturday the 20th, but you can bet the line will start forming along Hollywood Blvd much earlier in the morning. Once open, they''ll split the line in two - one for cash and one for credit (cash is highly encouraged). Pours are $20 and will benefit the LAPD Police Activity League. It''s limit one per person, but if the line dies down and the Younger is still flowing, they MIGHT start pouring seconds. A Blue Palms truffle burger and a PtY sounds like a solid Saturday in my book!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Haven Gastropub</del></strong>\n<del> Orange - Sunday February 21st, 9am</del></h2>\n<del>Haven Gastropub is brunching it again this year with Pliny The Younger and they are serving it on a first come, first served basis. Whether you''re there for a pour of it on its own or as a part of the their Russian River flight, you''re going to want to get there early. It''s one pour per person, so plan on making it a whole brunch thing with their great menu and $3 craft beers from 9am - 11am. Of course, if you follow Haven Gastropub on Instagram at <a href="https://www.instagram.com/havengastropub/" target="_blank">@havengastropub</a>, you''ll have some chances to win a pass to the front of the line to guarantee yourself a pour of Younger.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Hollingshead Delicatessen</del></strong>\n<del> Orange - Monday February 22nd, 10am</del></h2>\n<del>The crew at Hollingshead will be tapping Pliny the Younger along with many other Russian River beers on Monday February 22nd at 10am. Russian River co-owner, Natalie Cilurzo will also be in the house for the event where OC beer fans will likely be calling in sick to work and lining up early for a pour of the awesome triple IPA.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>The Salted Pig</del></strong>\n<del> Riverside - Monday February 22nd, 11am</del></h2>\n<del>The Salted Pig is tapping their keg of Pliny on the morning of Monday the 22nd at 11am and will be distributing tickets to the line at 9:30am. One ticket per person and each ticket is $8. Get there early to make sure you get a pour!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Beachwood BBQ &amp; Brewing</del></strong>\n<del> Long Beach &amp; Seal Beach - Raffle Jan 19 - Feb 20 - Tapping Feb 23rd</del></h2>\n<del>Beachwood is back with its Pliny the Younger raffle for the 5th year now, where you can purchase as many $5 tickets as you''d like for your chance to win a pint. The raffle period is January 19th through February 20th, then they''ll be drawing raffle tickets on February 22nd live on the <a href="http://www.fourbrewers.com/" target="_blank">Four Brewers podcast</a>. Winners then have the chance to come in to one of Beachwood''s two locations to redeem their prize between February 23rd and March 3rd. Proceeds for the raffle support the Melanoma Research Foundation. Drink awesome super rare beer and support charity, it doesn''t get much better than that!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>The Crow Bar &amp; Kitchen</del></strong>\n<del> Corona Del Mar - Tuesday, Feb 23rd, 11:30am</del></h2>\n<del>The Crow in Corona Del Mar is bringing PTY back again this year with a ticketing system that could get you the chance to grab 2 pours if you show up early enough. Ticket sales start at 11:30am and if you''re one of the first 50 people in line, you get a chance to buy 2 tickets. After that they''ll be selling individual tickets until they sell out. The Younger taps at 1:30pm and ticket holders can come anytime between then and 4pm to redeem their pour. They''ll also have other Russian River brews as well as Hopslam in case you miss out on the Pliny.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Tony''s Darts Away</del></strong>\n<del> Burbank - Tuesday February 23rd, 12pm</del></h2>\n<del>The Younger is coming back to Tony''s and once again they''re serving it up in some special commemorative glassware. So here''s the deal: tickets will start being handed out to the line that will inevitably be forming along Magnolia Blvd at 12pm. One ticket per person. You''ll be placed into groups and given a time to come back once the keg is tapped at 3pm. $6.75 per glass, or $10 if you want it served in the "I Got Younger at Tony''s" glassware.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Eureka! Burger</del></strong>\n<del> Claremont - Tuesday February 23rd, 3pm</del></h2>\n<del>Eureka is tapping their keg of Pliny the Younger on Tuesday at 3pm. BUT the $9 tickets will start being sold as early at 8am, so you might want to get there early to secure your pour. The first 60 people in line after 8am get the chance to come back after 3pm with their ticket and receipt to redeem their pour.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Simmzy''s</del></strong>\n<del> Manhattan Beach - Tuesday February 23rd, 4pm</del></h2>\n<del>Simmzy''s threw on a keg of Pliny the Younger unannounced at their Manhattan Beach location. Still pouring as of 5pm, so if you read this in time, you know what to do.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Congregation Ale House</del></strong>\n<del> Long Beach - Tuesday February 23rd, 7pm</del></h2>\n<del>Congregation''s Long Beach chapter is tapping their keg of Pliny the Younger at 7pm on Tuesday. This is a last-minute tapping, so you should be able to head over there and get a pour without too much hassle.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Boneyard Bistro</del></strong>\n<del> Sherman Oaks - Tuesday February 23rd, 7pm</del></h2>\n<del>Boneyard is doing another unplanned tapping of Pliny the Younger on Tuesday around 7pm. This one is usually pretty low key and under the radar, so head on out!</del>\n<h2><del><strong>\n</strong><strong>Tustin Brewing Co</strong></del>\n<del> Tustin - Wednesday, Feb 24th, 10am</del></h2>\n<del>Tustin Brewing Co has learned from their years of tapping Pliny the Younger, and it shows with their organized process. At 10am, they''ll be giving out bracelets to everyone in line. If you get a bracelet, that means you get the opportunity to buy an $8 ticket for an 8 ounce pour. They don''t tap the keg til 3pm, so once you get your ticket, you can hang around the brewery, or leave and come back later that day for your Pliny the Younger pour. Simple, neat, easy, and delicious.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Eureka Burger</del></strong>\n<del> Redlands - Wednesday February 24th, 3pm</del></h2>\n<del>Eureka in Redlands threw on an unannounced keg of Pliny the Younger on Wednesday afternoon and it''s still pouring as of 4pm. Better hurry, this one won''t last long!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Eureka Burger</del></strong>\n<del> Claremont - Thursday February 25th, 3pm</del></h2>\n<del>Eureka Claremont is one of the lucky few who got more than one keg of Pliny the Younger and they are putting their second keg on tap Thursday at 3pm. It''s kind of late notice, so better get moving!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>The Surly Goat</del></strong>\n<del> West Hollywood - Thursday February 25th, 6pm</del></h2>\n<del>Surly Goat is tapping their keg of Pliny The Younger on Thursday 2/25 at 6pm, and you better believe a line will be forming well in advance of that. Luckily for those of you who participate in Surly''s Beer Passport Photo, you have an opportunity to get in earlier. Complete passport holders get in at 5pm, 60+ stamps get in at 5:15pm, 50+ stamps get in a 5:30pm, and 40+ stamps get in at 6:45pm. Then the rest of the line opens up at 6.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>The Bottle Room</del></strong>\n<del> Whittier - Saturday, February 27th, 10am</del></h2>\n<del>The Bottle Room in Whittier is throwing a few Russian River brews on tap on Saturday February 27th and one of those beers is in fact Pliny the Younger. They''re tapping at 10am, but if you want a pour, better get there early!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Barbara''s at the Brewery</del></strong>\n<del> Lincoln Heights - Saturday, February 27th, around 1pm</del></h2>\n<del>Barbara''s has one of the most underground Pliny the Younger tappings around and it all started early afternoon on Saturday 2/27 during their 17th anniversary party. They went quickly through one keg and put another one on later in the evening, which was limited to one glass per person. It''s still pouring as of right now (10:45pm) but the chances of it lasting through the night? Slim. Good thing they have a ton of other amazing craft beers pouring this weekend, so you really can''t lose.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Ladyface Ale Companie</del></strong>\n<del> Agoura Hills - Monday February 29th, 11am</del></h2>\n<del>Ladyface has just tapped their keg of Pliny the Younger accompanied by Bling Pig IPA on Monday February 29th. Pouring now, but you can bet that will change in the next couple hours. Not a bad way to start the week!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Father''s Office</del></strong>\n<del>Santa Monica - Monday February 29th, 5pm</del></h2>\n<del>Pliny the Younger quickly came and went at Father''s Office Santa Monica, however this year they''ve decided to institute a one pour per person ticketing system. The change made for an interesting night, but hopefully more people got to try a glass of the awesome triple IPA before the keg kicked. They then tapped an encore keg at 5pm the next day. This one went a lot smoother from what we hear.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Slaters 50/50</del></strong>\n<del> Anaheim Hills - Wednesday March 2nd, 6pm</del></h2>\n<del>Slaters in Anaheim is having a special Russian River night featuring Blind Pig, Row 2 Hill 56, Damnation, Pliny the Elder, and yes, Pliny the Younger. Doors open at 4pm and the Younger keg taps at 6pm, so you''ll probably want to be on time for this one.</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Verdugo Bar</del></strong>\n<del> Glassell Park - Wednesday March 2nd, 8pm</del></h2>\n<del>Verdugo Bar is tapping Pliny the Younger again this year on Wednesday March 2nd. Doors open at 6pm and the keg taps at 8pm. Should be a good one!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Lucky Baldwin''s</del></strong>\n<del> Old Town Pasadena - Saturday March 5th, 11am</del></h2>\n<del>Lucky Baldwin''s in Old Town will be tapping Pliny the Younger in addition to several other awesome Russian River beers on Saturday March 5th. Ticket sales start at 11am and the keg gets tapped at 1pm, so head on out to Old Town Pasadena and make a day of it!</del>\n<h2><strong>\n<del>Lucky Baldwin''s Trappiste</del></strong>\n<del> Pasadena - Sunday March 6th, 11am</del></h2>\n<del>Lucky Baldwin''s Trappiste is following suit the next day with their own Russian River event, including a keg of Pliny the Younger. Tickets for Younger go on sale at 11am and the keg taps at 1pm.</del>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2><strong>The Daily Pint</strong>\nSanta Monica - Wednesday March 2nd, 7pm</h2>\nOk, so this is just for the ticket sale, but you can bet tickets will go quick so we wanted to make sure you were on top of it. They''ll be selling tickets at the bar starting at 7pm on Wednesday, then will be tapping their Pliny the Younger keg on Monday March 7th. Exact timing for the tapping TBD, but their doors open at 2pm. Just be ready, ok?\n<h2><strong>\nFather''s Office</strong>\nCulver City - Monday March 7th &amp; Tuesday March 8th, 5pm</h2>\nFather''s Office Culver City released 100 tickets for a pour of Pliny the Younger on Monday the 7th and will be releasing another 100 tickets on Tuesday at 5pm. Get there early, this is one of the last few kegs in LA!\n<h2><strong>\nLucky Baldwin''s</strong>\nSierra Madre - Saturday March 12th, 11am</h2>\nLucky Baldwin''s Sierra Madre location will be hosting their own Russian River event a week after their other locations. And yes, this includes another keg of Pliny the Younger. Same drill as the other events: tickets on sale at 11am and the Younger keg taps at 1pm.\n<h2><strong>\nThe Med Kitchen + Bar</strong>\nHermosa Beach - Monday, March 14th &amp; 16th (SOLD OUT)</h2>\nThe Med is back with their Russian River beer dinner featuring, you guessed it, Pliny the Younger. The exclusive 5 course dinner will be on March 14th at 7pm, with tickets costing $75 + tax &amp; tip. If you aren''t able to to attend the dinner, or just don''t want to commit to the $75 ticket, The Med is selling tickets for a single pour of Pliny the Younger on March 16th. Tickets for this one are $10 and no reservations or food is required to purchase. Probably one of the best ways to ensure you get a quick hassle-free pour of the Younger. Call (310) 318-2666 or stop in to the restaurant to make your reservations.', '#PlinyWatch: Your 2016 Guide to Finding Pliny The Younger in LA', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'plinywatch-2016', '', '', '2016-02-09 19:49:25', '2016-02-10 03:49:25', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1936', 0, 'post', '', 17);
