(1977, 4, '2016-02-14 23:19:00', '2016-02-15 07:19:00', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" srcset="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap-300x157.png 300w, http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap-1024x536.png 1024w, http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png 1200w" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\n\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday February 15th to Sunday February 21st, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Monday February 15</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Ale Academy XX: Hops - The Spice of Life at Angel City</strong>\n<em>DTLA Arts District, 7pm</em></h3>\nThe week kicks off with a little beer education over at Angel City and their 20th installment of Ale Academy. In this session, you can learn how hops became a centerpiece in balancing sweetness and providing intense aromatics. <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/ale-academy-xx-hops-the-spice-of-life-tickets-21286455361" target="_blank">$5 gets you a beer tasting and the discussion</a>.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday February 16</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony’s: Pugachev''s Cobra with Hangar 24</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nThere was an extra keg lying around, and now they''re gonna tap it for you. Get your fix on this Russian Imperial Stout and see how the barrel-aged bourbon flavors impact your senses. The keg get tapped at 6pm and $6.75 gets a nice snifter.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday February 17</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Firestone Walker Tap Takeover at Crazy Harry''s Bar</strong>\n<em>Winnetka, 5pm</em></h3>\nFirestone Walker is heading back to Crazy Harry''s for another tap takeover and putting on the likes of Sucuba, Bretta Weisse, and Nitro Merlin. The list keeps growing, so mark this one down if you haven''t had your Firestone fix in a while.\n<h3><strong>A HopSlamin'' Good Time at Lordsburg Taphouse</strong>\n<em>La Verne, 5pm</em></h3>\nLordsburg Taphouse in La Verne is delivering the HopSlam to the east SGV and Bell''s is bringing more friends for a sweet tap takeover. HopSlam is being talked about a lot lately, so get your hands on it sooner rather than later.\n<h3><strong>Bottle Share at The Rookery</strong>\n<em>Pomona, 7pm</em></h3>\nFebruary marks the return of The Rookery''s monthly bottle share, so it''s time to grab some of the brews you''ve been hanging on to for sharing and bust them out on Wednesday. All you have to do is bring in a can/bottle/homebrew and spend $10 on food or beverage to participate.\n<h3><strong>Women''s Beer Forum: We LOVE Beer and Chocolate! at Eagle Rock Brewery</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 7pm</em></h3>\nWednesday is ladies night at Eagle Rock Brewery where beer will be drank and chocolate from Valerie Confections will be enjoyed. The cost is $20 for a flight of 4 delicious truffles paired with beer and a flight sheet to help you remember what you had.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday February 18</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Three Weavers Tap Takeover at Blue Palms</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 4pm</em></h3>\nFor all the Three Weavers fans out there, mark Thursday evening as "busy" because you''ll be spoiled by what''s on tap at Blue Palms. Soak your palate on The Messenger, Deep Roots ESB w/ Cacao Nibs, Knotty DIPA, and more! This is one event we''re putting on our list this week, so we hope to see you there.\n<h3><strong>Bottle Logic Night at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nOne of our favorite OC breweries is invading the taps at Select Beer Store and pouring Double Actuator, Greyhound (Grapefruit Pale), and Cobaltic Porter (GABF) among others. Don''t forget to grab some bottles to go on your way out, like you need us to remind you you''re at a fantastic bottle shop too.\n<h3><strong>Founders Tap Takeover at City Tavern</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nFounders is taking over the taps at City Tavern''s DTLA outpost and here''s what will be pouring: Centennial IPA, Azacca IPA, Dirty Bastard Scotch Ale, Breakfast Stout, Kentucky Breakfast Stout, and Project Pam Black IPA aged in maple syrup bourbon barrels. Should be a good one!\n<h3><strong>Modern Times Tap Takeover at Overland Cafe</strong>\n<em>Palms, 6pm</em></h3>\nModern Times is in the house at Overland Cafe with a handful of their brews. We don''t have word on the exact tap list, but you can probably expect awesome brews like Black House, City of the Sun, Floating World, Fortunate Islands, and more. They''ll also be doing some special food pairings with the beers, so get on it!\n<h3><strong>Smog City Tap Takeover at House of Billiards</strong>\n<em>Sherman Oaks, 7pm</em></h3>\nA little bit of pool and a lot of Smog City beer. Now, that''s a solid Thursday Night. We''ve been digging what House of Billiards has been doing lately in terms of selection, and getting one of the LA''s best breweries in the mix is definitely helping.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday February 19</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Breckenridge Brewery Tap Takeover at Eagle Rock Lounge</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 7pm</em></h3>\nEagle Rock Lounge is hosting one of Colorado''s finest with plenty of taps including two barrel-aged beers in addition to their core line-up. The first 24 people will get a pint glass, so get there early if want to add some new glassware to your collections.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday February 20</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger Day at 38 Degrees Ale House</strong>\n<em>Alhambra, 11am</em></h3>\nWell, the time has come for the Pliny wave to hit LA and it''s all starting at 38 Degrees. There aren''t a ton of details, but it sounds like Pliny will be part of a special flight and there could be some commemorative merchandise you can purchase as well.\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Blue Palms Brewhouse</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 11:30am</em></h3>\nNext up on the Pliny list is the charity event at Blue Palms where $20 gets you a 10oz pour. There will be two separate lines for cash and credit, where cash is strongly encouraged. It''s bound to get busy in there, but what else would you expect when Pliny the Younger is around.\n<h2><strong><a href="http://hoppedla.com/plinywatch-2016/" target="_blank">Check out our guide to ALL the Pliny the Younger tappings in LA &amp; OC this year!</a></strong></h2>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3></h3>', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of February 15, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-week-feb-15', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=1977', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2077, 4, '2016-02-22 18:02:10', '2016-02-23 02:02:10', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\n\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday February 22nd to Sunday February 28th, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday February 23</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at The Crow Bar &amp; Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Corona Del Mar, 11:30am</em></h3>\nThe Crow in Corona Del Mar is bringing PTY back again this year with a ticketing system that could get you the chance to grab 2 pours if you show up early enough. Ticket sales start at 11:30am and if you’re one of the first 50 people in line, you get a chance to buy 2 tickets. After that they’ll be selling individual tickets until they sell out. The Younger taps at 1:30pm and ticket holders can come anytime between then and 4pm to redeem their pour. They’ll also have other Russian River brews as well as Hopslam in case you miss out on the Pliny.\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Tony''s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 12pm</em></h3>\nPliny the Younger is finally hitting the San Fernando Valley at Tony''s Darts Away. At 12pm, they will start distributing tickets on a first come first serve basis. You will be assigned a group with a time to come back for your PtY pour with group numbers being called approximately every 30 minutes. Your options include a 6oz. pour for $6.75, or a 6oz. pour plus a specialty "I Got Younger at Tony''s" glass for $10. Go for the glass.\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Eureka! Burger</strong>\n<em>Claremont, 3pm</em></h3>\nEureka is tapping their keg of Pliny the Younger on Tuesday at 3pm. BUT the $9 tickets will start being sold as early at 8am, so you might want to get there early to secure your pour. The first 60 people in line after 8am get the chance to come back after 3pm with their ticket and receipt to redeem their pour.\n<h3><strong>An Evening with Coronado Brewing at Far Bar</strong>\n<em>Little Tokyo, 7pm</em></h3>\nHeading up from San Diego, Coronado Brewing is crashing Far Bar for a night of unique and rare beers. The tap list is subject to change, but it seems like they are putting on Barrel Aged Stupid Stout, Seaside IPA, Sea Lady Black Lager, Sock Knocker DIPA, Mermaid''s Red, and Idiot IPA with Mango.\n<h3></h3>\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday February 24</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Tustin Brewing Co.</strong>\n<em>Tustin, 10am</em></h3>\nTustin Brewing Co has learned from their years of tapping Pliny the Younger, and it shows with their organized process. At 10am, they’ll be giving out bracelets to everyone in line. If you get a bracelet, that means you get the opportunity to buy an $8 ticket for an 8 ounce pour. They don’t tap the keg til 3pm, so once you get your ticket, you can hang around the brewery, or leave and come back later that day for your Pliny the Younger pour. Simple, neat, easy, and delicious.\n<h3><strong>Mac and Cheese Night at The Rookery</strong>\n<em>Pomona, 5pm</em></h3>\nIf you like craft beer and like mac and cheese, then enjoy the best of both of those worlds at The Rookery, where they will be offering 4 different kind of mac and cheese. Not a bad combo if you ask us.\n<h3><strong>Hopslam Release at Beachwood</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nHopslam has been making its way around LA, and now it''s Beachwood''s turn. Not only are they tapping Hopslam, but they are also putting on Bell''s Two Hearted Ale and Smitten Golden Rye Ale. If you haven''t had Hopslam before, we recommend you get on that.\n<h3><strong>Jeffers Drops Acid at Naja''s Place (SOLD OUT)</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5:15pm</em></h3>\nFirestone Walker Barrelworks'' very own Jeffers Richardson is conducting an intimate experience and dropping some knowledge on the acidity levels of sour beer. This ticketed event only went out to 25 lucky people, so if that includes you, have a great time!\n<h3><strong>Firestone Walker Tap Takeover at Darryl''s Couch</strong>\n<em>Camarillo, 5:30pm</em></h3>\nFirestone Walker is invading Darryl''s Couch this time around, and while the tap list hasn''t been announced yet, we''re pretty confident that FW fans will be happy with the selection.\n<h3><strong>Three Weavers Pairing Dinner at Boneyard Bistro</strong>\n<em>Sherman Oaks, 5:30pm</em></h3>\nWe''d like to say that anytime you''re pairing a meal with Three Weavers it''s going to be good. We feel no different about what the chef is serving up at Boneyard Bistro alongside the solid offering of 3W beers. Get your fix of Pork Belly "Bahn Mi" paired with The Messenger and Petite Filet "Cheesesteak" paired with Blood Junkie among others.\n<h3><strong>Celebrate Fe-BRUE-ary at Library Alehouse</strong>\n<em>Santa Monica, 6pm</em></h3>\nIf you''re on the Westside on Wednesday, you''ll be treated to quite the takeover by The Bruery. Get your hands on beers like Juggling Walruses (dark sour with currants), Rueuze (gueuze-style sour), Humulus Terreux, and more!\n<h3><strong>Steal the Glass Night at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nSteal the Glass Night is back at Eureka featuring Almanac Brewing''s Farmer''s Reserve Citrus and Peach de Brettaville. Time to add another pint glass to your growing collection!\n<h3><strong>Firestone Walker Tap Takeover at Naja''s Place</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 7pm</em></h3>\nIf you missed the one-on-one experience with Jeffers and his Acid Trip, you won''t have to miss out on the beers or the man himself. This is actually one of the largest curations of Firestone Walker beers LA has seen with 21 different beers.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday February 25</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Firestone Walker Tap Takeover at Whole Foods El Segundo</strong>\n<em>El Segundo, 5pm</em></h3>\nFirestone Walker fans in El Segundo get quite the treat with an array of awesome beers hitting the taps. Get ready for the 2012-2015 versions of Parabola, Helldorado, and 19th Anniversary. They will also be putting out some bottles for sale including Parabola, Sucaba, Stickee Monkee, Helldorado, Velvet Merkin, 19th Anniversary, and Agrestic.\n<h3><strong>Thursday Night Fight: Drake''s Hopocalypse vs. Faction Hop Soup at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nSelect is starting up some trouble with their new series pitting two great hoppy brews against each other. The first keg to blow makes it to the next round in the tournament, with the championship match coming in June during LA Beer Week. Head down to Redondo Beach on Thursday and cast your vote!\n<h3><strong>Chamber of High-Gravity Beers at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 6pm</em></h3>\nPhantom Carriage has put together a night for fans of horror films and high-gravity beers with a special screening of <em>Barons Blood</em>. Just in case you can''t make the 6pm showing, they are doing all over again at 8pm so you can get your fix.\n<h3><strong>Firestone Tap Takeover at Lordsburg Taphouse</strong>\n<em>La Verne, 6pm</em></h3>\nThat''s right, another Firestone tap takeover is happening and they are taking over 13 taps at Lordsburg Taphouse. They will be pouring Agrestic, 18th &amp; 19th Anniversary, Stickee Monkee, and much more!\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at The Surly Goat</strong>\n<em>West Hollywood, 6pm</em></h3>\nThe Surly Goat is tapping their keg of Pliny the Younger on Thursday 2/25 at 6pm, and you better believe a line will be forming well in advance of that. Luckily for those of you who participate in Surly’s Beer Passport Photo, you have an opportunity to get in earlier. Complete passport holders get in at 5pm, 60+ stamps get in at 5:15pm, 50+ stamps get in a 5:30pm, and 40+ stamps get in at 6:45pm. Then the rest of the line opens up at 6.\n<h3><strong>Avery Tap Takeover at The Local Peasant </strong>\n<em>Woodland Hills, 6pm</em></h3>\nRepresenting for the West Valley is The Local Peasant and their upcoming Avery tap takeover on Thursday night. Beers that will be pouring include Joe''s Premium Pilsner, White Rascal, Liliko''i Kepolo, Raja, Vanilla Bean Stout, Tweak, and Pump[KY]n.\n<h3><strong>Coronado Brewing Pint Night at City Tavern DTLA </strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nAnother Coronado event is taking place this week, but this time it''s at City Tavern DTLA. They aren''t bringing too many, but they are making it count with Orange Ave Wit, Mermaid Red, Merbear, Sandstone IPA, and Bobblehead Imperial Red.\n<h3><strong>King Harbor Beer Dinner w/ Chef Jen Story</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 6:30pm</em></h3>\nTo celebrate the release of their Coconut IPA, the crew at King Harbor summoned their friend Chef Jen Story to put together a delicious pairing at the brewery. With pairings such as Ponzu Roasted Tri-tip alongside the Coconut IPA and Underdone Double Chocolate Cake with Imperial Swirly, what can possibly go wrong?\n\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday February 26</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Twist & Stout - Tap Takeover at Buzz Wine Beer Shop</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nBuzz is hosting a stout-focused tap takeover featuring some really awesome dark beers, including Hug Me, a chocolate milk stout from Barley Forge, The Patsy, a coconut stout from Barley Forge (amazing beer!), Man''s Milk, a milk stout from Noble Ale Works, Bear Hug, an imperial stout from Bell''s, and Breakfast Stout, an imperial coffee stout from Founders.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday February 27</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at The Bottle Room</strong>\n<em>Whittier, 10am</em></h3>\nThe Bottle Room in Whittier is throwing a few Russian River brews on tap on Saturday February 27th and one of those beers is in fact Pliny the Younger. They’re tapping at 10am, but if you want a pour, better get there early!\n<h3><strong>Brouwerij West Grand Opening</strong>\n<em>San Pedro, 12pm</em></h3>\nThe official grand opening of Brouwerij West has finally come and will be kicking things off with at least 8 beers available in the tap room. The courtyard will be open, brewery tours will be in full effect, and food trucks &amp; music start at 5pm.\n<h3><strong>Beachwood Blendery Release &amp; Weekend Opening</strong>\n<em>Long Beach, 2pm</em></h3>\nStarting this weekend, the Beachwood Blendery tasting room will be open every Saturday from 2pm-9pm, and Sunday from 12pm-6pm. They will be kicking this off with a bottle release of Propagation Series 256 and 512 on Saturday at 2pm.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday February 28</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>4th Annual Vegan Chili Cook-Off at Tony''s Darts Away</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 12pm</em></h3>\nThe Vegan Chili Cook-off has returned to Tony''s and the 5 incredible chefs are bringing the heat this time. Tickets are $10 and include 5 samples of chili (one from each chef) and a voting ballot for people''s choice award. The tickets will be available the day of the event and not in advance. The official hashtag is #TDAcookoff.\n<h3><strong>Bikes &amp; Brews with Rev Cycle at Craft Beer Cellar</strong>\n<em>Eagle Rock, 12:15pm</em></h3>\nCraft Beer Cellar is back with another edition of Bikes &amp; Brews with their neighbors, Rev Cycle! Kick things off at 12:15 with an hour long cycling workout, then walk up the block to Craft Beer Cellar to enjoy a pint or a flight. Tickets are $25 and space is limited, <a href="http://bikesandbrews.bpt.me/" target="_blank">so reserve your spot now</a>!\n<h3><strong>The 2016 Academy Awards at Kinetic Brewing Co. </strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 4pm</em></h3>\nThe 88th Academy Awards begin at 4pm on Sunday, and Kinetic is airing it live at the pub. They will make it interesting by including games and plenty of prizes, so ring in Best Picture with your favorite Kinetic brew.\n<h3></h3>', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of February 22, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-feb-22', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=2077', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2150, 4, '2016-02-29 22:19:22', '2016-03-01 06:19:22', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\n\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday February 29th to Sunday March 6th, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday March 1st</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony''s with Caroline''s Pasta Party</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nThis week, the Tony''s Darts Away series brings you what they call "carb heaven" with Chef Caroline serving up different vegan and non-vegan versions of her favorite pasta dishes.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday March 2nd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Slater''s 50/50</strong>\n<em>Anaheim Hills, 6pm</em></h3>\nPliny the Younger has made its way to Slater''s 50/50 in Anaheim and it''s only available in flight form. This Russian River flight night consisting of Pliny the Elder, Blind Pig, Row 2 Hill 56, and Pliny the Younger is on a ticketed first come first serve basis. So, show up at 4pm and get your hands on one.\n<h3><strong>Beer &amp; Bingo Night at Three Weavers</strong>\n<em>Inglewood, 6:30pm</em></h3>\nThree Weavers is bringing free bingo to their tasting room this week. Games start at 6:30 and go until 9pm on Wednesday. Plus you''ll have the chance to win free Three Weavers gear. Can''t go wrong with that.\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Verdugo Bar</strong>\n<em>Glassell Park, 8pm</em></h3>\nVerdugo Bar is tapping Pliny the Younger again this year on Wednesday March 2nd. Doors open at 6pm and the keg taps at 8pm. Should be a good one!\n<h3><strong>Steal the Glass Night at Eureka Tasting Kitchen</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nSteal the Glass Night is back at Eureka featuring Gigantic Brewing''s Gigantic IPA, Ginormous Double IPA, and Slip Into Darkness Schwarzbier. Time to add another pint glass to your growing collection!\n<h3><strong>Modern Times Beer Party &amp; Tap Takeover at Blue Palms</strong>\n<em>Hollywood, 6:30pm</em></h3>\nBlue Palms is blowing the roof off the doors with a crazy Modern Times tap takeover featuring everything from Hooloomooloo DIPA, Floating World, and the new Orderville IPA. Also available: Monsters Park aged in Caribbean rum barrels. Now, that''s interesting. <a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/1742943105939809/" target="_blank">Full tap list here</a>.\n<h3><strong>El Segundo Beer Dinner at Sausal</strong>\n<em>El Segundo, 7pm</em></h3>\nGet ready for a three-course dinner of Nuevo Rancho dishes paired with your favorite brews from ESBC such as Power Plant Triple IPA. Make a reservation before it''s too late! Call: (310) 322-2723. Below is the full menu:\n\n<strong>MENU &amp; PAIRINGS:</strong>\n· Course #1 – Goat Cheese Stuffed Jalapeño Popper Salad with Mango, Frisée, Endive, and Bacon (paired with El Segundo Brewing Co.’s Citra Pale Ale)\n· Course #2 – Pork Adobo Stuffed Tamale with Deep Dark Black Mole Sauce, Avocado, and Pico de Gallo (paired with El Segundo Brewing Co.’s Hop Plunge IPA)\n· Course #3 – Rancho Beef Short Rib with Cabbage Slaw, Hominy, and Cilantro (paired with El Segundo Brewing Co.’s Power Plant Triple IPA)\n· Dessert – Mexican Chocolate Truffles (for the table)\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday March 3rd</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Around The World with Cider &amp; Cheese at Southland Beer</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 4pm</em></h3>\nSouthland Beer found out that pairing cider with cheese is one of the best things ever, so they''re bringing in a sudsy supply from Spain, the UK, France, and Los Angeles. <a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/1668487873410431/" target="_blank">Here''s the full list of pairings.</a>\n<h3><strong>Modern Times 5  Beer Release at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nOn the tails of Modern Times releasing a bunch of new and seasonal beers, Select Beer Store is putting them on in the form of Orderville IPA, Fruitlands Apricot Gose, City of the Dead Stout, Hooloomooloo DIPA, and Booming Rollers IPA. Sounds like a good lineup to us.\n<h3><strong>Inaugural Exotic Slider &amp; Craft Beer Pairing at 38 Degrees</strong>\n<em>Monrovia, 6pm</em></h3>\nTaking a cue from their Alhambra location, 38 Degrees Monrovia is pairing four exotic sliders with four perfectly matched craft beers yet to be named. They''re offering the sliders without the beer, but what''s the fun in that?\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday March 4th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>First Friday with Crux Fermentation Project at The Doughroom</strong>\n<em>West LA, 5pm</em></h3>\nThis edition of The Doughroom''s First Friday features the tapping of three drafts from Crux Fermentation Project out of Bend, Oregon. The first pour starts at 5pm!\n<h3><strong>Stone Brewing Tap Takeover at Beachwood</strong>\n<em>Seal Beach &amp; Long Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nStone Brewing is bringing up 24 beers to split between both Beachwood locations while they pour the new Beachwood/Stone collab Dude (Looks Like an IPA). Expect to see many vintage and barrel-aged beers dating back to 2007. Oh, and they''re running a shuttle bus between both locations all night.\n<h3><strong>Collaboration Beer &amp; Cheese Pairing at BUZZ Wine Beer Shop</strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nVagabond Cheese Company is teaming up with BUZZ Beer Wine Shop for a First Friday featuring savory cheese paired with some great, local collaboration beers from Three Weavers/Noble Ale Works, Eagle Rock/Ladyface Ale Companie, and more. For $26, you''ll get a flight of 5 beers paired with cheese, and Alex from Vagabond and Ryan from BUZZ will be on hand to answer any questions. <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/collaboration-beer-cheese-pairing-with-vagabond-cheese-company-tickets-21642208428?aff=es2" target="_blank">Get tix right here!</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday March 5th</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Stone Beer Brunch at Beachwood</strong>\n<em>Seal Beach, 10:30am</em></h3>\nFollowing the previous night''s house party, Stone''s back with brunch in Seal Beach as Chef Jameson prepares a five-course brunch paired up by Stone''s Craft Beer Ambassador Dr. Bill Sysak.<a href="http://stonebrunchatbeachwood.brownpapertickets.com/" target="_blank"> Get tix here.</a>\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Lucky Baldwin''s</strong>\n<em>Old Town Pasadena, 11am</em></h3>\nLucky Baldwin’s in Old Town will be tapping Pliny the Younger in addition to several other awesome Russian River beers on Saturday March 5th. Ticket sales start at 11am and the keg gets tapped at 1pm, so head on out to Old Town Pasadena and make a day of it!\n<h3><strong>Hoppy 2nd Birthday to Absolution Brewing</strong>\n<em>Torrance, 12pm</em></h3>\nTickets are out for Absolution''s 2nd birthday with live music, prizes, food trucks, and a surprise anniversary beer. <a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/1268938846456394/" target="_blank">Get all the details here.</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday February 28</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Lucky Baldwin''s Trappiste</strong>\n<em>Pasadena, 11am</em></h3>\nLucky Baldwin’s Trappiste is following up their sister location''s tapping with one the next day with their own Russian River event, including a keg of Pliny the Younger. Tickets for Younger go on sale at 11am and the keg taps at 1pm.\n<h3><strong><a href="http://hoppedla.com/plinywatch-2016/" target="_blank">See The Full List of Pliny the Younger Tappings in LA</a></strong></h3>', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of February 29, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-february-29', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=2150', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(2189, 4, '2016-03-07 22:52:20', '2016-03-08 06:52:20', '<img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1536" src="http://hoppedla.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/events-on-tap.png" alt="LA Beer Events This Week" width="1200" height="628" />\n\nHere at Hopped LA, we keep our ear to the ground to discover all of the coolest beer events going around Los Angeles. But just because we can’t go to all of them, doesn’t mean you can’t! Below find a list of the craft beer events we’ve found for the week of Monday March 7 to Sunday March 13, 2016.\n\nKnow of an event that’s not on the list? Let us know at <a href="mailto:hello@hoppedla.com">hello@hoppedla.com</a> and we’ll add it!\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Tuesday March 8</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Tuesdays at Tony''s - Mystery Flight Night</strong>\n<em>Burbank, 6pm</em></h3>\nThis week, the Tony''s Darts Away series brings you a chance to win free beer! All you have to do is guess each style in the mystery flight, and your next beer is on the house.\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Father''s Office </strong>\n<em>Culver City, 5pm</em></h3>\nOne more round of Pliny at Father''s Office on Helms with another 100 ticket giveaway that is sure to go quick. This is the one of the last kegs in LA!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wednesday March 9</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Transplants Brewing Tap Night at Kinetic</strong>\n<em>Lancaster, 4pm</em></h3>\nPalmdale''s newest brewery is sharing some suds with the Kinetic crew and spreading the north county love. Not a bad night when two awesome breweries come together.\n<h3><strong>One Year Anniversary at Public School 818</strong>\n<em>Sherman Oaks, 5pm</em></h3>\nPS818 is celebrating their one year anniversary with a little help from Modern Times. The brewery is bringing in Orderville IPA, Fruitlands, Lomaland, and Blackhouse Stout, while the first 50 guests who order one of these beers get free PB&amp;J Sliders.\n<h3><strong>1UP Wednesday at The Rookery</strong>\n<em>Pomona, 6pm</em></h3>\nThe Rookery is holding their monthly game + beer pairing with pours of Ommegang Abbey Ale while playing Castlevania. It''s time to channel your inner vampire slayer.\n<h3><strong>Steal the Glass Night at Eureka Hawthorne</strong>\n<em>Hawthorne, 6pm</em></h3>\nAdd another glass to your collection at Eureka Tasting Kitchen on Wednesday with Sierra Nevada''s Hop Hunter IPA. A nice beer to get you over the hump.\n<h3><strong>Three Weavers Night at Button Mash</strong>\n<em>Echo Park, 6:30pm</em></h3>\nIt''s a recipe for fun when you can enjoy six delicious Three Weavers beers while playing all of the 80s and 90s games you could want. Knotty DIPA? Yes, please.\n<h3><strong>Trivia Night at Southland Beer</strong>\n<em>Koreatown, 8pm</em></h3>\nTest your knowledge and win some prizes while having 20 taps at your disposal along with a dedicated bottle room for on-site enjoyment.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Thursday March 10</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>Select Monk 4 Release at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 5pm</em></h3>\nIn honor of Monkish''s shared anniversary with Select Beer Store, they are teaming up again for the release of Select''s anniversary beer in the form of a Belgian-style Quad. Try it first only at Select!\n<h3><strong>Firestone Night at Green Jug</strong>\n<em>Woodland Hills, 5pm</em></h3>\nGreen Jug is honoring the release of Luponic Distortion with a beer tasting that includes the new brew plus Pale 31, DBA, Double Jack, Pivo Pils, and super fresh Wookey Jack. All for just $7.\n<h3><strong>Three Weavers Night at Seoul Sausage </strong>\n<em>DTLA, 6pm</em></h3>\nThree Weavers is invading the 6 taps at Seoul Sausage''s new brick and mortar spot in Downtown LA. We don''t know about you, but a Banh Mi sausage sandwich with an Expat sounds pretty damn good.\n<h3><strong>Beer Pairing Dinner with Five Threads Brewing Company </strong>\n<em>Camarillo, 7pm</em></h3>\nFive Threads is teaming up with Mission Oaks Cafe in Camarillo to bring you a five course, five beer pairing dinner for $65 per person. Call ''em up at (805) 482-1022 to make a reservation.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Friday March 11</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>MS Fundraiser </strong><strong>+ New Beer Release </strong><strong>at Transplants Brewing Company</strong>\n<em>Palmdale, 4pm</em></h3>\nTransplants Brewing Company and the National Multiple Sclerosis Society are hosting a Meet &amp; Greet fundraiser where 10% of your purchase during business hours is donated to support programs and services along with MS research.\n\nTransplants will debut their new collab beer with <a href="https://www.instagram.com/yourpicssuck/" target="_blank">yourpicssuck</a> called Hops Are a Preservative - an "Indiana Pale Ale" they are entering into Saturday''s LA IPA Fest.\n<h3></h3>\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Saturday March 12</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>LA IPA Fest 2016 at Mohawk Bend</strong>\n<em>Echo Park, 9:30am</em></h3>\nThe LA IPA Fest is back with 50+ taps of California craft that is sure to attract all hop heads in the area. This is not a ticket event and reservations are not being taken, so you''ll want to show up somewhat early. <a href="https://twitter.com/laipafest" target="_blank">Stay on top of the participating breweries</a>, and mark yourself busy in the calendar.\n<h3><strong>Sam Fest - 3rd Annual LA Barleywine Festival at 38 Degrees</strong>\n<em>Alhambra, 11:30am</em></h3>\n38 Degrees is back for their third year of honoring LA craft beer pioneer Sam Samaniego with a day full of fresh, barrel-aged, classic and new barleywines for all to enjoy.\n<h3><strong>Pliny the Younger at Lucky Baldwin''s</strong>\n<em>Sierra Madre, 11am</em></h3>\nLucky Baldwin’s Sierra Madre location will be hosting their own Russian River event a week after their other locations. And yes, this includes another keg of Pliny the Younger. Same drill as the other events: tickets on sale at 11am and the Younger keg taps at 1pm.\n<h3><strong>One Year Anniversary Celebration at Phantom Carriage</strong>\n<em>Carson, 12pm</em></h3>\nTickets are on sale for Phantom Carriage''s one year anniversary where they will feature over 30 exclusive cellar releases, two bottle releases, and rare guest beer offerings from local breweries. <a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/463239333861952/" target="_blank">Here''s the full list of details.</a>\n<h3><strong>Craft Ale &amp; Life Drawing at MacLeod</strong>\n<em>Van Nuys, 1pm</em></h3>\nHead on out to MacLeod for a complimentary pint and drawing materials while the Gallery Girls hold the pose. <a href="http://www.facebook.com/events/1564680717192101/" target="_blank">Learn more about Instructor Cesra Torres and the Life Drawing events.</a>\n<h3><strong>BrewAsana at Lucky Luke Brewing</strong>\n<em>Palmdale, 11:30am</em></h3>\nNothing says ''namaste'' like yoga and craft beer. Join instructor Christy Alvarado for a 60-minute yoga session followed by a tour of the Lucky Luke brewhouse and a pint or taster flight.\n<h2><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Sunday March 13</strong></span></h2>\n<h3><strong>The After Party: LA IPA Fest at Mohawk Bend</strong>\n<em>Echo Park, 9:30am</em></h3>\nJust because the real fest is over doesn''t mean that the tasty beer is gone. Enjoy some of the favorites from the LA IPA Fest in pints and flights all day long. Get there while supplies last!\n<h3><strong>$1 Off Drafts for St. Patrick''s Day 5K Runners at Select Beer Store</strong>\n<em>Redondo Beach, 10am</em></h3>\nSometimes, the best thing after a run is some good beer. Select is opening up early after the 5k and is giving all runners with race bibs $1 off drafts. Happy Sunday!\n<h3><strong><a href="http://hoppedla.com/plinywatch-2016/" target="_blank">See Where the Last Kegs of Pliny the Younger are in LA</a></strong></h3>', 'Events on Tap: LA Craft Beer Events the Week of March 7, 2016', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'beer-events-march-7', '', '', '2016-05-07 10:54:35', '2016-05-07 17:54:35', '', 0, 'http://hoppedla.com/?p=2189', 0, 'post', '', 0),
